title: italian zucchini crescent quiche
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large skillet, cook zucchini and onion in margarine (about 10 minutes).
Add parsley and seasonings.
In large bowl, blend eggs and cheese.
Stir in zucchini mixture. Press dough over bottom and sides of cookie sheet.
Spread with mustard.
Pour vegetable mixture over crust.
Bake 20 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with additional shredded cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
A great way to use leftover turkey.

title: roast corn
directions: Combine butter, chives and parsley.
Brush on ears of corn. Wrap in heavy-duty foil.
Roast in coals 25 minutes.
Turn several times.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Place nuts in bottom of pan. Cut biscuits in quarters.
Roll each in a mix of cinnamon and white sugar. Place evenly in Bundt pan. Melt margarine and brown sugar.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Pour over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: swiss style pot roast - slow cooker
directions: Salt and pepper both sides of roast. Can lay carrots on bottom, then lay roast. Cut up onions in large pieces and place on top, then pour tomatoes over all. Slow cook on medium about 8 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix in bowl with dressing.

title: bear cookies
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add flour, pepper and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. These may be frozen.

title: cranberry-poppy seed muffins
directions: Line 12 medium muffin cups with paper baking cups, or grease bottoms.
Stir all ingredients except cranberries together in a bowl until moistened.
Stir in cranberries.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° until golden brown, 18 to 20 minutes. Immediately remove from pan.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in order listed (lettuce, peppers, celery, onions, peas, mayonnaise, sugar and cheese) in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Let set at least 4 hours before serving.

title: creamy chicken nachos
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread on flour tortillas or pitas.
Bake in oven at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes or until bubbly.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Moisten yeast in lukewarm water.
Add to remaining ingredients to make a light dough.
Let raise 2 or 3 times.
Make into doughnuts.
Let raise again and fry in hot lard.
This dough is also nice for five hour hot rolls.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Oil 12-inch pizza pan (or 9 x 12-inch cake pan) with butter or cooking spray.
Unroll crescents and form crust on pan (pull to cover).
Brown sausage or bacon and drain well.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and butter.
Sprinkle over crust, meat, hash browns, egg mixture and cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cinnamon ornaments(makes 18 to 25 small to medium ornaments)
directions: Combine spices blending well.
Stir in applesauce and mix well.
Mixture will be stiff.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness. Using small to medium cutters, cut dough into desired shapes.
Let ornaments dry 4 to 5 days.

title: hurry-up tuna casserole
directions: Being in Grandmother Smith's preschool Sunday School class that she taught at the back of the church.
Although she was a large lady, and over 65 years old, she perched on the same little chairs we used because she wanted to be down on our level.

title: peanut butter and cornflake candy
directions: Melt over low heat in large saucepan.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes, but do not cook hard.
Remove from heat; add cornflakes and stir well.
Form into balls or drop by spoon on buttered cookie sheets.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix and refrigerate.
This should be done 4 to 6 hours before serving or even the night before.

title: caramel bars
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, baking soda and butter (save 1/2 cup for top).
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Melt caramels and milk.
Mix chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour caramels over crust, then chocolate chips and the 1/2 cup of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: dutch apple cake(recipe of the late aunt emma wilson plumlee.)
directions: Make Rich Tea Biscuit dough, adding more milk to make a drop biscuit dough. Spread the dough 1/2 inch deep in an oblong 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Peel and pare apples; cut in eighths. Press apple slices into top of dough very close together. (It won't hurt if more than a layer thick.) Dot with butter or oleo. Mix cinnamon and sugar together.
Sprinkle over apples. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done. Serve warm or cold with Lemon Sauce (recipe follows).

title: crab mold
directions: Dissolve gelatine and water.
Heat soup (do not boil).
Add the rest of the ingredients except mayonnaise.
Heat and remove from stove; fold in mayonnaise.
Pour into a 1-quart mold.
Chill overnight.
(It's wonderful.)
Garnish with parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: english pea salad
directions: Drain peas.
Empty peas with other ingredients.
Mix with mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper as you would potato salad.

title: light cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello with hot water.
Set aside and cool.
Roll graham crackers into crumbs.
Add sugar and butter or margarine. Mix to form crust and line bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
(Save 1/2 to 3/4 cup to put on top, if desired.)
Beat Milnot until thick in large bowl.
Then mix until creamy the cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice in separate bowl.
Add cheese mixture and cooled jello to whipped cream.
Beat again until completely mixed.
Pour into crust and chill 5 to 6 hours.
Top with crumbs or cherry pie mix.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and put in pie crust.
Cover with other pie crust.
Bake according to pie crust package directions until brown.

title: puppy chow(finger food)
directions: Melt oleo, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Stir in Crispix cereal.
When cereal is well coated, mix in confectioners sugar. Cool.
Can be served in a dogs dish for conversation piece.

title: mexicali dip
directions: Mash tamales with fork.
Mix well with chili beans, onion, chilies, garlic salt and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with remaining 1/2 cup of cheese.
Put back in oven until cheese is melted.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Cut butter into 1-inch pieces.
In a small heavy saucepan, combine lemon juice and 2 tablespoons water and reduce over high heat to about one tablespoon.
Remove from heat and add 1 tablespoon cold water.
Beat egg yolks lightly and whisk into lemon water.
Over low heat, whisk in the butter, one piece at a time, making sure that each piece of butter is melted before adding more.
Continue to whisk the sauce until it is thick.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serving size 8.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine eggs, flour and sugar; beat well.
Add milk, salt and drained corn.
Melt butter in large dish.
Add corn mixture.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: spinach cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In bowl mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 9 x 13 inch baking pan. Bake for about 30 minutes until done.

title: pavlova cake
directions: Beat the egg whites with the salt and cream of tartar.
Slowly beat in the sugar, cornstarch and lemon juice.
Pour into spring-form pan lined with wax paper.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°, 30 minutes at 250° and 90 minutes at 200°.
It is important to follow this method completely.
Leave in oven overnight.

title: pete's rice pudding(smooth and creamy)
directions: Put rice, milk and 3/4 cup sugar in a large pot.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally.
When mixture has boiled, lower heat and continue to cook (uncovered), stirring constantly for about an hour or until rice is soft.
Beat the eggs in bowl. Add 1 cup milk, 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla to taste.
Beat.
Ladle small amount of rice mixture into egg mixture.
Stir.
Pour this back into pot; raise temperature to high and continue stirring until boiled.
Turn off heat.
Pour into glass casserole dish or 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature, then refrigerate.

title: spinach side dish
directions: Boil and salt spinach.
Drain and mix with all ingredients. Put into greased cake pan and bake 1/2 hour at 300°.
Can be topped before baking with Velveeta or Mozzarella cheese.

title: cherry salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Chop cherries.
Mix lemon juice with milk. Add pineapple, cherries and nuts, then add Cool Whip, cherries, lemon juice and red food color.
Refrigerate.

title: easy cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients; add sugar.
Beat.
Alternately add flour and eggs to creamed mixture, blending after each addition. Begin and end with flour.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan; bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until tests done. Delicious with ice cream or your favorite sauce.

title: apple nut dessert
directions: Mix together egg, baking powder, brown sugar, white sugar, flour and vanilla.
Then add apples and nuts; mix well by hand. Pour into a 9-inch pie plate and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
May be served with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: refrigerator dill pickles(large quantity)
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar, water and pickling salt and cool.
Put dill, few onions and garlic in bottom of a gallon jar or ice cream bucket.
Add fresh cucumbers.
Pour the cooled brine over the sliced cucumbers in the large container.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: ultimate chocolate cakes
directions: Grease and flour bottom of cake pan.
Mix first 4 ingredients and set aside.
In large bowl, with mixer at high speed, beat next 3 ingredients.
Beat for 3 minutes or until light and fluffy.
At low speed, beat in mayonnaise.
Add flour mixture in 4 additions alternately with water, beginning and ending with flour.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: a.1. derful sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Combine beef, 3 tablespoons steak sauce, egg, bread crumbs, garlic and salt.
Form into 24 meat balls.
In large skillet, brown meat balls well in oil; drain.
Add remaining ingredients except cornstarch and green pepper.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Dissolve cornstarch in 1 tablespoon water.
Stir into mixture. Add green pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Serve over rice. Serves 6.

title: mock lobster newburg
directions: Place fish in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt and lemon juice.
Heat undiluted soup and pour over fish. Bake uncovered at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Blend remaining ingredients together and sprinkle over fish.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: super bowl chili
directions: Brown beef and pork and drain well.
Add undrained beans and tomatoes, chopped onions, green pepper, garlic, chili powder, sugar, vinegar and cumin.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring often.
Ladle into soup bowls.
Spoon shredded cheese over each serving.
Makes 6 to 8 main dish servings.

title: texas millionaires
directions: Melt in microwave and stir well the caramels, water and butter.
Add pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on buttered tray.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: 4 hour slaw
directions: Chop and combine cabbage, pepper and onion.
Pour 1 cup sugar on top and set aside.
Combine celery seed, 2 teaspoons sugar, salt, mustard seed, salad oil and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Pour over salad.
Let set 4 hours.
Stir and serve.

title: pineapple icing
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Spread onto cooled Mandarin Orange Cake or Pig Pickin' Cake.
Refrigerate frosted cake.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, water and Karo until threads.
Beat 2 egg whites prior to cooking syrup.
Add eggs to syrup mixture; add pecans. Drop immediately by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Crumble bread.
Add all other ingredient, except margarine. Pour into crock-pot and dot with margarine.
Cook on high 2 hours or on low for 3 to 4 hours.
Makes about 16 servings.

title: pork and noodles
directions: Saute pork, onions, garlic and broccoli until browned.
Add broth, season with salt and pepper.
Simmer for 12 to 15 minutes. Blend soy sauce, cornstarch and water.
Add to saucepan.
Stir until sauce thickens.
Cook noodles al dente; drain.
Serve sauce over hot noodles.
Serves 6.

title: quick caramel ring
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a small saucepan, melt margarine.
Coat bottom and sides of ungreased 12-cup fluted pan with 2 tablespoons of melted margarine.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons of nuts on bottom of prepared pan.
Add remaining nuts, brown sugar and water to remaining margarine; heat to boiling, stirring occasionally. Separate dough into 20 biscuits.
Cut each in half and shape into ball.
Place 20 balls in bottom of pan.
Drizzle half of caramel sauce over balls.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Invert immediately onto waxed paper and remove from pan.
Makes 10 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken. Simmer 25 to 30 minutes over low heat. Remove bay leaf and all lemon slices.
Add chicken, stirring well. Simmer for 25 minutes longer.
Fill tortilla wrappers with chicken mixture.
Put in 9 x 13 inch dish (or larger). Spread sauce on them and cover with Jack cheese (shredded).
Put in oven at 400° until cheese is melted.

title: wassail
directions: Heat all ingredients for 15 minutes.
Remove sticks and allspice. Serve with orange floating.

title: date nut bread
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, cinnamon, mace and salt.
Cream butter until soft; gradually add sugar.
Add well beaten eggs. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Fold in dates, nuts and orange rind.
Pour into a 9-inch greased loaf pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour to 1 1/4 hours.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Remove and cool completely before slicing.

title: souper casserole
directions: Prepare dinner as directed, except using 3/4 cup milk.
Saute onion and green pepper in margarine until tender.
Add to prepared dinner with remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheesy hamburger macaroni
directions: Brown meat and drain. Meanwhile, boil 8 cups water, cook macaroni- do not rinse. Add cheese sauce and remaining ingredients to meat. Heat thoroughly; stir in macaroni.

title: flambee sundae
directions: Sauce should serve 20.
In a medium pan, blend sugar and cornstarch; stir in water and undiluted orange juice.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened. Stir in pineapple, coconut, cherries and nuts; set aside.

title: dutch babies-oven pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place butter in pan and melt.
Combine egg, milk and flour, then stir until blended.
Pour mixture over hot butter and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot with syrup, honey, jam, pie filling, powdered sugar, fresh fruit, etc.

title: lemon iced ambrosia bars
directions: Mix sugar and flour; cut in the margarine.
Press in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been lightly buttered.
Bake 15 minutes at 300°.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift flour and then measure.
Combine with remaining dry ingredients and resift 3 times.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender or rub with fingertips.
Stir in buttermilk until thoroughly mixed.
Turn dough into a lightly floured surface and knead about a dozen times.
Roll out to 1/2 to 3/4 inch thick, then cut with a floured biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits on a greased baking sheet.
Brush tops with melted shortening.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 14 to 16.

title: cut-out sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter Crisco, sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl at medium speed with mixer.
Beat in egg.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.

title: tuna ball
directions: Mix and chill.	Serve with crackers.

title: kraut salad
directions: Heat together sugar, vinegar and oil.
Pour over combined vegetables.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Very good and colorful.

title: grilled halibut with pesto
directions: To make pesto, in bowl of food processor combine basil, garlic, pine nuts, Parmesan cheese, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Process until smooth.
With the machine running, slowly pour in 1/3 cup oil.
Transfer pesto to a small bowl; cover and set aside at room temperature.

title: western stripteasers
directions: Line pan with foil.
Slice potatoes as for French fries. Arrange in baking pan.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with cheese and half the parsley.
Pour in milk.
Bake covered with foil at 425° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining parsley.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: rolls
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Add 1-1/2 cups flour and beat well.
Beat in egg and yeast.
Add remaining flour and beat well.
Put in greased bowl and let rise 1-1/2 to 2 hours.
Turn on floured board.
Shape rolls and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 400° for 12-15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen rolls.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mash hot potatoes.
Add cream cheese in small pieces.
Add butter and sour cream.
To milk, add beaten eggs, then add to potatoes.

Add salt, pepper and onion salt and beat until fluffy. Place in a greased casserole dish and refrigerate overnight. Bring to room temperature before putting in 350° oven for about one hour, uncovered, until lightly browned.
Serves 12.

title: banana apricot nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add lemon juice to bananas.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Sift dry ingredients.
Mix all and bake in loaf pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes or until tester comes out clean.

title: hilda's red cabbage with apples
directions: In 4-quart saucepan over medium heat in hot butter cook apples and onion until tender, about 10 minutes.
Add cabbage, water, red wine vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Heat mixture to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 40 minutes, or until cabbage is tender.
To serve, discard bay leaf.
Enjoy!

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour in large bowl.
Mix the first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife goes halfway in the middle.

title: dutch funnel cake
directions: Blend egg and milk in a bowl; add next 6 dry ingredients and mix well.
Heat 1 1/2 inches of oil to 375° in skillet.
Pour batter into funnel with 1/2-inch spout; drizzle batter into hot oil in 6-inch spirals.
Deep fry for 1 1/2 minutes or until golden brown on both sides.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: fruited acorn squash
directions: Cut each squash in half crosswise; remove and discard seeds. Place squash halves, cut side down, in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan, lightly coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook hamburger, onions and garlic until hamburger is done and onions are transparent. Stir in flour, mushrooms with reserved liquids, salt and pepper. Cook for 5 minutes. Add soup and simmer an additional 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat to desired temperature. Do not boil. Serve over rice and/or noodles.

title: cheese ball
directions: In small bowl, add water to minced onion.
Set aside.
Put cream cheese in large bowl.
Chop smoked beef in small pieces. Add to cream cheese.
Pour minced onion in.
Mix thoroughly with hands.
Form into ball.
Roll or sprinkle parsley on cheese ball. Refrigerate.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and margarine together.
Save out 1 cup. Then add the milk, soda and vanilla to the batter.
To the 1 cup you have saved, add the Heath bars and nuts.
Pour the first mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add the Heath bar mixture on top.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Press ground meat into bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Slice potatoes onto meat.
Add salt and pepper.
Slice onions on potatoes.
Cube cheese on onions.
Cover with soup.
Bake in covered dish for 1 hour at 350° or until potatoes are done. Serves 6.

title: raisin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla, in saucepan and cook until raisins are done (about 1/2 hour).
Thicken with cornstarch. Add vanilla and pour on crust and bake at 400°.

title: almond toffee(originally from ruth kopp)
directions: Heat and stir until boils to 250 degrees first 4 ingredients. Stir constantly until 300 degrees.
Add 1/2 of almonds and pour into 9x9 metal pan.
Cover with a layer of chocolate at once and spread.
Sprinkle balance of burnished almonds.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Add eggs and milk; mix well.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake for 50 minutes or until a knife inserted halfway between center and outer edge comes out clean.
Let cool about 1 hour before cutting.
Serve with real whipping cream.

title: yeast bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift all dry ingredients together. Cut shortening in 1/2 of dry ingredients.
Pour yeast in buttermilk; add to dry ingredients.
Roll on floured board. Freeze for later use.
Allow biscuits to thaw and rise in a warm place for 2 or 3 hours.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: surprise meatballs
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix together meat, cheeses, onion, egg replacer or egg white, oats and seasonings.
Form into 18 meatballs.
Place in a nonstick roasting tin and cook 20 minutes. Mix stock, tomato puree, sherry and corn flour.
Simmer until thickened.
Drain excess fat from meat and pour tomato sauce over. Reset the temperature to 350° and cook for 30 minutes.
Serve with hot rice.
Makes 48 meatballs; each contains 31 calories, 0.5 g fat, 4 mg chol, 41 mg sodium.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: In large bowl, beat together sugar, butter, vanilla and milk until smooth.
If necessary, add more milk until frosting is spreading consistency.
If desired, add a few drops of food coloring.
Stir to blend.
Makes enough to fill and frost 2 layer cake, 13 x 9-inch sheet cake or 2 dozen cupcakes.

title: gloria's corned beef macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Put back in pan and mix 1 can cream of chicken soup and 1 can milk and pour over macaroni; mix.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add corned beef (broken up) and mix with macaroni mixture.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with thin slices of sharp cheese.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Heat Velveeta, Parkay, chocolate and corn syrup in 3-quart saucepan over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture is melted.
Gradually add sugar to chocolate mixture, beating with electric mixer on medium speed until smooth.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Smooth surface with spatula. Cover.
Refrigerate several hours. Cut into squares.
Makes 3 1/2 pounds.

title: blue ribbon cake
directions: Stir together and pat in pan first three ingredients.
Mix cream cheese, eggs and sugar.
Pour over cake mix in pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Use 9 x 12-inch pan or dish.
Nuts if desired.

title: very berry punch
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Before serving, add 7-Up, Vichy water and ice in large punch bowl.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: crabmeat salad
directions: Put crabmeat in bowl.
Add celery, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, mayo and salad dressing.
Mix gently with 2 prong fork.
When uniformly blended, put into refrigerator and chill 1 hour.
Serve with tomatoes cut in quarters or on a bed of lettuce.

title: cookie bars
directions: Mix together and press into cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
While hot, spread with jam.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and nuts.
Cut into bars at once.

title: wine cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for 4 minutes; pour into greased and floured pan (Bundt or angel food or 9 x 13-inch pan).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Pour half of glaze on bottom; turn onto plate and pour remaining glaze on top.

title: snow white chicken
directions: Stew chicken; cool and bone, saving broth.
Saute 1 chopped onion in margarine.
Add 3 cups hot broth and salt to onion.
Add rice and cook 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water until crisp and tender; drain well.
Arrange broccoli in greased baking dish.
Place layer of chicken over top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice until well mixed; pour over chicken layer.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Combine bread crumbs with 1 tablespoon melted butter; scatter over cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: chili sauce
directions: Start meat, catsup, French dressing and water on medium heat. Keep stirred until it starts to boil.
Reduce heat; add other ingredients.
Stir occasionally.
Simmer 2 hours.
Good recipe for crock-pot.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Measure juice from pineapple and add enough water to make 2 cups liquid.
Heat to boiling on high heat, and pour over gelatin, stirring until completely dissolved.
Let gelatin cool.
Mash bananas, and combine with pineapple and strawberries.
Add fruit to gelatin and chill in fridge until mixture starts to congeal. Place half of gelatin mixture in the bottom of mold or pan.
Make a layer of sour cream and spread remaining gelatin mixture on top of sour cream.
Chill until firm.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Combine above ingredients and mix until fluffy.
Pour into pie shell.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes 2 thin pies or 1 thick pie.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix milk, eggs, sugar and butter; set aside.

title: morman bread
directions: Mix milk, oil and sugar; heat until lukewarm. Mix the remaining ingredients. Add to warm milk mixture. Mix well and pour into large dish with cover. Refrigerate overnight. Take out what is needed and return remainder to refrigerator. It will keep for several days. Turn soft dough onto floured surface and mix enough flour into dough to be cut for rolls. Cut rolls and bake at 400° until brown. Makes about 40 rolls. Also makes very good cinnamon rolls.

title: green chile and cheese casserole
directions: Place
alternate
layers of chile and cheese in greased baking dish.
Leave
enough
cheese to sprinkle on top.
Beat eggs, milk
and
salt.
Pour over chile.	Top with cheese and buttered crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes in slow oven.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Bake potatoes and peel.
Combine with bouillon and water in blender.
Add onion, parsley, cheese and flour; blend and pour into saucepan.
Add evaporated milk, salt and pepper.
Heat until thick, 3 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 2 tablespoons liquid; flake.
Combine all ingredients, except flour and oil; mix well.
Shape into 6 patties.
Coat with flour, if desired.
Pan-fry on both sides in oil until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: casserole sauce mix
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Store in airtight container. Yields 3 cups of mix (equal to about 9 cans of soup).

title: salmon loaf
directions: Beat eggs slightly, then stir in cream, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Add salmon and mushrooms. Put in casserole dish and bake at 400° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: surprise pies
directions: Fold together sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and Cool Whip. Add drained pineapple and nuts. Divide between the 2 pie crusts. Chill until firm. Keep refrigerated.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese get to room temperature then mix with Eagle Brand milk.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell and top with cherry pie filling.
Chill for 2 hours. Cherries may be substituted with another fruit pie filling.

title: shrimp fried rice(com chien tom)
directions: Put cooked rice in a large bowl to cool.
Beat eggs with 1 teaspoon salt in a small bowl.
Pour 1 tablespoon oil in hot skillet over medium-high heat.
Stir in egg mixture; scramble and break into small pieces until quite dry.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Pour remaining oil in hot skillet over medium-high.
Stir in minced onion and the shrimp.
Stir until shrimp is cooked, approximately 5 minutes.
Add rice, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper, ketchup, garlic, soy sauce, cooked eggs and m.s.g.
Stir constantly until the ingredients are well blended and thoroughly heated over low-medium heat for about 10 minutes.
Serve hot. Makes 3 to 5 servings.

title: cherry torte
directions: Beat egg whites with vanilla and salt until foamy.
Gradually beat in sugar, beating to stiff peaks.
Combine nuts, cracker crumbs and baking powder, folding into the beaten whites.
Spread mixture in well-greased 9-inch pie plate, building up sides.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes or until the meringue shell is dry on the outside.
Cool.

title: grilled canadian bacon
directions: Score bacon with knife point in 1/2-inch grill pattern.
Place meat on grill about 4 inches from coals.
Baste with mixture of orange juice, brown sugar and cloves.
Cook 40 to 45 minutes, turning often.

title: coconut bread
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients together.
Blend the next 4 ingredients.
Alternate egg mixture with flour mixture and with the buttermilk.
Add the coconut flakes and, if desired, the nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes one loaf.
Add topping, if desired.

title: artichokes adoned
directions: Cut 3 to 4 bread rounds from each slice of bread, using 1 1/2 ounce end of shot glass.
Toast bread crumbs on one side under broiler.
Combine mayo, cheese, dill and garlic.
Spread a small amount on untoasted side of bread.
Top with a piece of artichoke. Cover with additional cheese.
Broil until lightly browned. Sprinkle with paprika before broiling, if desired.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk together in large mixer bowl.
Beat at low speed on mixer for 2 minutes.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Put in refrigerator for a few minutes while peeling bananas. Alternate layers of pudding, bananas and vanilla wafers.
Keep in refrigerator.
Makes 1 (3-quart) and 1 (2-quart) dish.
Can make half, if desired.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken; debone.
Cut chicken into bite sized chunks. Add chopped celery.
Add chopped green onion.
Add grapes.
Add almonds.
Add mayo.
Add more or less to get desired texture and taste.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve on warm croissants.

title: easy baked corn
directions: Mix muffin mix with all ingredients and turn into a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake for about 45 minutes or until mixture is softly set at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften the cream cheese; drain the pineapple very good and mush everything together, forming a ball.
Roll cheese ball in the walnut pieces.
Let cool in refrigerator for a couple of hours. Garnish with a cheese and serve with your favorite crackers.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms well; remove stems and dry.
Chop stems into small pieces.
Add cheese, bacon, Miracle Whip and onions. Arrange mushroom caps in baking dish.
Fill each mushroom cap with mixture.
Place under broiler until bubbly.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; rinse and drain.
Squeeze out excess liquid. Combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill 3 hours.
Serve. Makes about 2 1/2 cups.
Serving idea:
Cut out center of unsliced loaf of rye bread and fill.
Use bread for dipping.

title: shrimp egg rolls
directions: Shell
and devein shrimp; cut into small pieces.
Combine cornstarch, salt and 4 Tbsp. soy sauce;
then add to shrimp.
Mix well.
Set aside while preparing vegetables.
Heat 4 Tbsp. oil over high heat.
Add shrimp and stir-fry until pink.
Remove shrimp from pan; set aside.
Heat 4 Tbsp. oil; stir in grated ginger root (cook for 1/2 minutes); add cabbage and stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add onions and 4 Tbsp. soy sauce.
Mix and stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add carrots; stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add bean sprouts; stir-fry for 1 minute.
Return cooked shrimp to pan; mix well and stir--fry 1 minute.
Now transfer mixture to colander to drain and cool.
Fill wrappers by following instructions on package of egg roll wrappers.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Put soup, milk and cheese in double boiler.
Let cheese melt and add pimentos and chilies.
While sauce is cooking, brown ground meat.
When meat is cooking, grate American cheese and onion in another bowl.
When meat is done, pour over cheese and onions.
Dip tortillas in grease.
Roll meat mixtures into tortillas.
After in the pan, pour sauce on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all together.
Store in covered (tight) container.
Add 2 teaspoons to each cup of boiling water (or to taste).
Good hot or cold.

title: old-time sugar cream pie
directions: Combine sugars, flour, salt and boiling water.
Add cream, nutmeg and vanilla.
Pour mixture into 9-inch pastry lined pie plate.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 minutes.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: Place half of the bread cubes in a well greased baking dish. Arrange cubed cheese and ham evenly over the first layer of bread cubes.
Uniformly top ham with the remaining bread cubes.
Combine eggs, milk, dry mustard and salt, then pour evenly over bread. Top with shredded cheddar.
Refrigerate overnight and bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: caramels
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and 1 cup cream to 238°.
Add 1 cup cream and cook to 238° again.
Add 1 cup cream and cook to 240°.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Cool. Cut in squares.
Wrap individual wax papers.

title: praline yams
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place drained yams in ungreased 2-quart dish. In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; blend well. Sprinkle mixture over yams and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: half-a-pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add one egg at a time; beat well after each addition.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk in which flavoring has been added.
Pour in greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: chicken log
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients.
Blend in next 2 and 2 tablespoons parsley.
Shape into 9-inch log.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill. Mix remaining parsley and almonds.
Use to coat log.
Makes 3 cups.

title: date banana bread
directions: Mix together salt, soda, cinnamon, cloves and flour.
Mix this with other ingredients except add the mashed bananas last.
Bake in two 8-inch loaf pans or 1 large loaf pan which has been greased. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon; save liquid.
Flake salmon.
Combine cracker crumbs and seasonings with liquid; mix thoroughly.
Pack into small greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle generously with paprika and parsley flakes.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 4.

title: low calorie congealed salad
directions: Mix 2 cups of boiling water with Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Add cottage cheese.
Drain pineapple and add.
Add pecans and fold in Cool Whip.
This makes a very large salad.

title: rum balls(no bake)
directions: Combine all ingredients but sugar thoroughly.
Shape into balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Roll in sugar.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute onion in bacon grease or cooking oil until they turn clear.
Season onions with salt, pepper, garlic powder, chili powder and season all.
Use enough of each season to coat top of onions.
Add ground beef to onions and brown.
After meat is brown, drain off fat, and return to skillet.
Pour in 2 cans of tomato sauce and let simmer.
In the meantime, I boil my noodles. While the noodles are boiling and the meat is simmering you are ready to mix cheese.
Mix container of cottage cheese with two eggs and mix well.
I also add salt and pepper to this mixture. Layer sauce and meat in bottom, then spoon some of the cottage cheese on top of sauce.
Next, add layer of mixed mozzarella and parmesan cheese.
Then layer noodles.
Start over
layers and end with mozzarella and parmesan on top.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Blend thoroughly cake mix, 3 eggs and water and fold in pie filling and pecans.
Pour mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Mix together flour, sugar, butter and cinnamon and sprinkle on top of mixture before baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: peach crunch
directions: Pour peaches and juice in pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over peaches, then sugar evenly over the mix.
Sprinkle pecans evenly on top of sugar.
Pour butter on top and bake until mix is brown.

title: nana's shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburg, drain.
Add corn and season to taste.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix ingredients well. Place in 8 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake 45 to 60 minutes.

title: callie owen's brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Beat eggs, add sugar and beat again.
Add butter/chocolate mixture, vanilla and salt, beating well.
Add flour and mix until smooth.
Stir in nuts. Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: walt's salad dressing
directions: Mix in blender and save in refrigerator.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Mix jello, pudding and sour cream together.
Fold in pineapple, marshmallows, pecans and Cool Whip.
Mix the night before serving and chill.

title: tater candy
directions: Peel and boil potato until done. Mash with fork. Add a pinch of salt and pour in powdered sugar. Mix well. This makes a stiff dough. On a well floured surface, roll out to 1/4 inch thickness. Spread peanut butter over the top of this and roll up like a jelly roll. Chill in refrigerator before serving.

title: crumb cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Cut in the butter until mixture resembles a coarse meal.
Remove 1 cup of mixture and combine with nuts and cinnamon; set aside.
To remaining crumb mixture, add milk and baking powder.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle the reserved crumb mixture over the batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tests done. Cut into squares and garnish with whipped cream.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle chocolate wafer crumbs in bottom of a 7-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.
Position knife blade in food processor.
Add cream cheese and next 7 ingredients, mixing until smooth.
Add egg and mix until blended.
Fold in chocolate chips. Pour mixture over crumbs in pan.
Bake at 300° for 65 to 70 minutes or until set.
Let cool in pan.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours. Remove sides of pan and serve.
Makes 12 servings.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and shortening.
Take out 2/3 cup crumbs for top.
To remaining crumbs add milk, egg, baking powder and nutmeg. Grease 9 x 13 cake pan; put in cake batter.
Sprinkle 2/3 cup crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, but check with toothpick.

title: classic la mancha veggies
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan and saute the bell pepper, onion, zucchini and garlic until the onion is transparent.
Add the tomatoes, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
At the end of the cooking time, turn up the heat to reduce the liquid; the vegetables should be thick, not soupy.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking soda, powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger.
Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar.
Whip in pumpkin, then butter. Beat in dry ingredients. Add nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sugarless cookies(diabetic)
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, then add remaining ingredients to moisten. Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet. Bake at 375°. If dough is too thin, add a bit more flour.

title: margarine cake
directions: Cream margarine and vanilla.
Add sugar, gradually beating all the time.
Then beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Always add flavor first and last.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix cream of celery soup and sour cream together.
Stir in corn, onion and green or red pepper.
Stir in can of nacho cheese soup.
Put grated cheese on top, then bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Cook sausage and hamburger together; drain off grease.
Add catsup, Worcestershire sauce, cheese and oregano.
Heat all together until cheese melts.
Spread on rye bread and freeze on cookie sheets.
Then place in plastic bags.
Remove what you need and put in oven until hot and not too crisp.

title: creme de voile
directions: Make cream sauce with butter, flour, milk, salt and pepper. Let cool.
Add to beaten egg yolks.
Stir in ground chicken and mix well.
Add chopped parsley.
Adjust salt and pepper to taste. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Grease mold.
Line with Reynolds Wrap; grease again.
Pack mixture into mold.
Cover with Reynolds Wrap. Cook in 350° oven in pan of water (or steamer) 1 1/2 hours.
Turn out on platter.
Serve with creamed peas and mushrooms poured over.
(Can be made ahead of time.
Freeze if desired.)

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Add rest; heat through and serve.
Makes 10 servings.

title: lemon delight
directions: Crust: Melt margarine. Add flour and pecans. Spread in 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: polish reuben casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, onion and mustard in medium bowl.
Blend well.

title: aunt marion's oatmeal cookies
directions: In saucepan, cover raisins with water; bring to boil and cool.
Reserve 5 tablespoons liquid.
In bowl, mix together sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda, vanilla and oatmeal.
Stir in drained raisins with 5 tablespoons reserved liquid.
Add melted butter. Drop by rounded teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, but the cheese and potato chips in a 9 x 13 casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese and potato chip crumbs on top.
Bake in 325 oven 45 minutes or until lightly brown.
Serves 8.

title: modeling dough
directions: Mix ingredients in a pan. Cook over medium heat until mixture pulls away from sides of pan and becomes doughy in consistency. Knead until cool.
Not edible. Stays soft much longer than play dough.
Keeps 3 months unrefrigerated.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix grated cheese with flour and salt.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix with other ingredients.
Make balls and roll in bread crumbs, using 1 tablespoon for each ball.
Fry in deep fat.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and sugar.
Put in cake pan and bake 5 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel icing
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook slowly over low heat to form a soft ball.
Remove from heat and beat until light consistency to spread.

title: fish in cucumber sauce
directions: Combine cucumber, dill and 2 tablespoons of butter.
Saute until tender.
Stir in soup, sour cream and tomato.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Do not stir. Pour sweetened peaches, or any favorite fruit, over batter.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: watergate salad
directions: In large bowl, combine fruit including juice.
Stir in pudding (you may need two boxes, depending on size of cans of fruit). Fold in Cool Whip; mix well.
Color will be mint green and very light, fluffy texture.
Fold in marshmallows.

title: curry and rice
directions: Brown beef, onion and seasonings in skillet.
Dice and add tomatoes to mixture.
Simmer over low heat for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix everything but chips in large bowl until mixed well, then add chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Drop by spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown.
Let cool, then remove from pan.

title: taco dip
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning. Put in bottom of an 8 x 8-inch Pyrex or a glass pie plate.
Pour Pace sauce on top and refrigerate.
Before serving, add lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and Doritos or corn chips to dip.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Put onion, garlic and olive oil in pan; saute for 5 minutes. Slice sausage; fry until done.
Put all other ingredients in crock-pot, then put onion, garlic and sausage all in.
Put on 1 or 2; slow cook all day.
Make spaghetti.
Feeds about 12 people. Great for working mothers.

title: collard greens
directions: Boil meat until thoroughly cooked.
Meanwhile, remove damaged leaves, roots and stems from collards.
Wash well, making certain no sand remains.
Add all ingredients to meat.
Cover and cook until collards are tender.
Drain.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Combine all the ingredients. Shape into 2 rolls. Wrap and chill overnight. Bake 1/4-inch slices on ungreased baking sheet in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Put boxes of uncooked rice in pan and sprinkle one package of seasoning over the rice.
Then, place chicken pieces on rice and add wine and water.
Take other package of seasoning found in rice and sprinkle on top of chicken.
Distribute mushrooms.
Place hunks of butter on top.
Cover with foil and cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and cook 15 minutes more or until brown.
Serves 8.

title: 12-inch cookie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 12 to 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: caramel brownie cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together brownie mix, 1 egg and water until well blended.
Spread into a greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Melt caramels in a pan with milk over low heat, stirring frequently.
Pour caramel topping over brownie crust.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed until well blended.
Add 2 eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Pour over caramel mixture.
Bake 40 minutes; cool.

title: sand cups
directions: Note:
Need 8 to 10 (7 ounce) plastic cups.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter to soft ball stage (stir constantly).
Add salt, vanilla and peanut butter and beat until thickened.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: new orleans style seafood gumbo
directions: Note: Fish, crabmeat, etc. may be added to suit personal taste.

title: corn spoon bread pudding
directions: Beat the eggs and add all the other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes at an oven temperature of 375°, or until firm and nicely browned.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and eggs together, add cornmeal, butter, salt and vanilla. Stir to blend, sprinkle pecans on unbaked pie crust. Add filling. Bake at 425 degrees for 10 min., then reduce heat to 325 and bake until light brown in color; about 30 min. and until partially set in center.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat; drain. Put Veg-All in a large dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup and cheese with Veg-All. Add hamburger meat last. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour red cabbage
directions: Shred red cabbage and boil in small amount of water (enough to cover bottom of saucepan) for about 10 minutes.
Mix flour with vinegar; add brown sugar, salt, pepper and cloves.
Add this mixture to the cooked cabbage and simmer for 2 minutes.
Bacon grease or ham grease mixed with the cabbage gives it a delicious flavor.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Add to rest of above mixture.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add rind and cranberry sauce. Stir. Chill until thick. Stir in pineapple and celery. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart mold. Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: pretzel torte
directions: Mix and press into a 10 x 13-inch pan the sugar, pretzel crumbs and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let crust cool.

title: ambrosia
directions: Cut oranges, apples and bananas into small pieces.
Add all ingredients together.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine ingredients except cheese in large bowl and stir well. Pour half of mixture into a greased 10-inch iron skillet.
Top with cheese.
Add remaining corn meal mixture.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until done.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: low-fat lasagna
directions: In skillet, brown meat until no longer pink.
Pour off any fat. Add tomatoes and spaghetti sauce.
Spread 1/3 of sauce mixture in a 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Lay on 4 of the noodles; spread 1/2 of the cottage cheese over noodles, then repeat 1/3 of the sauce mixture, remaining noodles and sauce.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash and cap strawberries; drain.
Mix together sugar, water and cornstarch; boil until clear.
Remove from stove and cool. Add strawberry jello.

title: boiled peanuts(using crock-pot)
directions: Put some good (i.e., fattening) vanilla ice cream in a blender.
Instead of milk, add apple cider (preferably fresh, sweet and pulpy).
Add cinnamon to taste.
Tastes just like apple pie ala mode.

title: spicy strawberry nut loaf
directions: In a large mixing bowl, sift together the flour, sugar, salt, soda and spices.
In a separate, smaller bowl, blend eggs and oil, then gradually stir into dry ingredients alternately with strawberries.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, dry pudding, oleo, egg and milk.
Mix like cake batter.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan.
Drain peaches and arrange over batter in pan.
Combine cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and juice; beat until thick.
Pour into center of peaches to 1 inch of sides.
Sprinkle remaining sugar (1 tablespoon) and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk, flour and baking powder alternately.
Add vanilla and salt. Grease and flour tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: out of the world dessert
directions: Crush Ritz crackers fine.
Mix with sugar and butter.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding with milk and ice cream. Pour over cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle Heath bars that are chopped fine.
Refrigerate.
Can be prepared a day in advance.
This may also be prepared in 2 pie plates.
Serves 12. Easy, rich, gooey and yummy!

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pan.
In a large bowl, combine melted butter, sugars, eggs and peanut butter.
Blend until smooth. Add 2 teaspoons baking powder, salt and flour.
Stir until blended. Mixture will be thick.
Pour into 8 x 11 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: vidalia pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: banana oatmeal cookie
directions: Cream together butter and sugars until smooth.
Beat in eggs, mashed banana and vanilla.
Add flour, salt, soda, baking powder and oats.
Form into small balls and roll in sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet 2-inches apart for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Makes 4 dozen.

title: mini blitz
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolks.
Set aside.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spray baking dish with Pam.
Bake until light brown or crusty on top.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
In a large bowl combine hash brown potatoes, sour cream soup and cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Cover with crushed cornflakes.
Bake for 50 minutes.

title: spanish hamburgers
directions: Brown ground beef and drain, reserving 1 to 2 tablespoons grease.
Add flour to pan with grease and ground beef; brown flour.
Add soup and 1/2 can of water.
Let cook until thickened. Spoon over toasted hamburger buns.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Place ground beef in baking dish.
Cover with layers of sliced onion, sliced potatoes, cheese, pork and beans.
Pour 1 can of tomato sauce over the top and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: no cook chocolate gravy
directions: Mix cocoa, flour and sugar in a bowl. Stir until well blended. Take boiling water and slowly pour into mix while stirring until you have
a paste.
Add water to thin to your liking.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate brownie shake
directions: Blend brownie ice cream or brownies and vanilla ice cream, milk and banana for 30 seconds and pour into glass.

title: carnation famous fudge
directions: Butter an 8-inch square pan.
In medium saucepan, combine butter, evaporated milk, sugar and salt.
Bring to a full, rolling boil, over medium heat, stirring constantly; remove from heat. Stir in marshmallows, chocolate morsels, vanilla and nuts.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute or until marshmallows melt.
Pour into pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: aunt rose's hard sauce
directions: Cream as for a cake; add whiskey to taste.
Fold in beaten egg white.
Pour over hot pudding.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.

Hollow out one loaf of bread so that there is a hollow "bowl" in the middle of the loaf. The sides and bottom of the loaf should be about 2-inches thick. Place dip in the center of the hollowed-out loaf.
Tear the bread that was removed from the middle, plus the 2nd loaf into bite size pieces.
Use these pieces as "dipsters."

title: party punch
directions: Mix Kool-aid as directed. Chill. Just before serving, mix all ingredients together. Garnish glass with orange, lemon or lime slices. You may also add a cherry.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Boil noodles in salted water.
Pour noodles and 2 cups of the liquid into a buttered casserole.
Save rest of liquid.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper; drain grease drippings.
Add oregano, parsley flakes, garlic salt, mushrooms, spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce and tomatoes; let simmer.
Grate Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese; set aside.
Cook lasagna noodles as per package directions.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Begin with sauce (about 3/4 cup), then a layer of noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Alternate in this way, ending with sauce on top.
Bake at 400° for approximately 45 minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except corn flakes and butter. Place in baking dish. Mix corn flakes and butter together. Put on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: texas sweet potato pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl; beat at low speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add bourbon and next 5 ingredients; beat just until blended.
Pour mixture into pastry shell.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes or until set.
Cool. Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.

title: cranberry barbecued chicken wings
directions: Place chicken wings in shallow glass dish.
Mix remaining ingredients in 1-quart saucepan.
Heat over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth; pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Remove chicken from marinade, reserve marinade. Cover and grill chicken 5 to 6 inches from medium coals 20 to 30 minutes, turning and brushing 2 or 3 times with marinade until done.

title: buttermilk cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
In a separate bowl sift flour, soda and salt together. Combine dry ingredients to creamed ingredients alternating with buttermilk.
Mix, then add by teaspoon to cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cinnamon/sugar before baking.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
(This recipe halves easily.)

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Fry hamburger and onions; drain. Mix in soup. Put in shallow baking dish. Top with cheese, beans and Tater Tots, in that order. Bake at 400° for about 1/2 hour or until the Tater Tots are hot in the middle.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix butter and sugar together, blending well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well, then add the vanilla and nutmeg (optional).
Beat until fluffy.
Slowly stir in the flour until a fairly firm dough is formed.
Knead more flour into the mix until it is firm enough to roll out.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness, cut with cookie cutters and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Sprinkle sugar (with cinnamon, if desired) onto each cookie before baking.
Bake in 350° to 375° oven for 5 to 8 minutes.
Yields approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add soup, chilies, chicken and chestnuts.
Blend well.
Tear up part of tortillas in small pieces.
Place in greased casserole; pour 1/2 of mixture over tortillas.
Add more tortillas and rest of mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients gently but thoroughly.
Spread in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Spread catsup over top.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: quick peach dumplings
directions: Bring peaches, vanilla and sugar to a boil. Pinch biscuits in tiny pieces and add to peaches.
Cover.
Cook slowly until biscuits are done.

title: westinghouse waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat egg yolks; add with milk into dry ingredients.
Beat until batter is smooth.
Add melted butter and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Preheat iron and bake 3 to 4 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together thoroughly sugar and oleo.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour, vanilla and lemon; mix thoroughly.
Pour into floured cake pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Sift together sugar and flour. Add one egg well beaten with the yolks of 3 eggs.
Add fresh cultured buttermilk.
Stir and cook until thick and creamy. Remove from fire. Add butter and lemon extract.
Let cool slightly and pour into a baked pastry shell. Cover with meringue.
Spread smoothly upon the pie.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate streusel bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar and cocoa.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add; mix well.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups.
Press remaining mixture onto bottom of prepared pan. Bake 10 minutes.

title: little pizzas
directions: Take package of biscuits and smooth and stretch each biscuit until it is about 4 inches wide, then put each biscuit on a greased cookie sheet.
Put about 1 tablespoon of tomato sauce on each pizza.
When this is done, you may put whatever pizza toppings you like on your pizza.
Set oven at 350°.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Bring to a full rolling boil.
Fill jars and seal.
Recipe x 4 = 15 quarts.
That is about 10 pounds of onions and 10 pounds of sugar.

title: oatmeal-molasses bread
directions: Mix oatmeal, boiling water and oleo.
Cool for 1 hour.
Add salt and molasses to cooled oatmeal mixture.
Stir in yeast dissolved in warm water.
Add the flour a few cups at a time. Knead.
Let rise until doubled.
Form 3 loaves.
Let rise about 1/2 way.
Put in cold oven.
Turn heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: cabbage and tomato soup
directions: Wash, drain and
shred cabbage.
Place juice in a large nonaluminum saucepan with
an
equal amount of water.
Add the cabbage and slowly bring
to
a boil.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add the
bouillon, lemon juice, salt and pepper plus any other spices
and
vegetables
you	wish.
Cover
and cook slowly for another 5 to 15 minutes, depending on the degree of doneness desired for
the
other
ingredients.
Serves 8.
For best results, reheat it very slowly.
Freezes well.

title: candy's lasagna(recipe originated with candy stotts, spring hill, florida)
directions: Brown ground beef and add Ragu sauce.
Mix cottage cheese, eggs, Parmesan cheese and spices.
Cook lasagna noodles and layer noodles, cottage cheese mixture, meat sauce and other cheeses in that order.
Make two layers of each, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until browned.
Makes 12 servings.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, green pepper and garlic.
Add rice, water, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Season with salt, pepper and chili powder.
Simmer about 30 minutes until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: hot chicken casserole salad
directions: Mix together and put in a large casserole dish: chicken, celery, onion, salt, soup, lemon juice, soy sauce, mayonnaise and rice.
Mix boiled eggs, grated cheese, almonds and crushed potato chips together and sprinkle over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and let cool.

title: special baked rice
directions: Brown rice in butter.
Add onion and lightly brown.
Add consomme and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, then roll into 1-inch balls.
Store in an airtight container for 3 days.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar over balls before serving.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches.
Cook and stir beef and onion until brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix. Spread in plate; top with chiles.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Top with sour cream, lettuce, tomatoes and cheese, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy and delicious fish
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Wash fish and pat dry. Line a baking dish with foil. Place fish skin side down in baking dish. Squeeze lemon juice over fish; sprinkle generously with salt and pepper. Spread mayonnaise evenly over fish, including the edges. Sprinkle lightly with Parmesan cheese and paprika. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until done. Run under broiler for 1 minute or until lightly browned and puffed.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Prepare popcorn according to package directions.
Place in large pan.
Bring to boil the sugar, syrup and gelatin in saucepan, stirring until sugar and gelatin are dissolved.
Pour over popcorn.
Mix until popcorn is completely coated.
Form balls quickly with hands.
Place on waxed paper.
Cool.
Makes 18 balls.

title: airy crepes
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm
water in a mixing bowl.
Stir well and add the flour.	Beat
well and let stay in warm place overnight.	In the morning, add egg, oil and honey; beat well. Let stand for a few minutes
and
then cook like pancakes on a slightly oiled grill or crepe pan.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain all cans, then combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Then place in a saucepan 1 cup vinegar, 1/2 cup sugar and 3/4 cup cooking oil.
Boil real good.
Cool and pour over vegetables. Keeps in refrigerator 4 to 5 days.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Bring soup stock to a boil.
Stir in cornstarch mixture and continue stirring until slightly thickened.
As you stir thickened stock, slowly pour in egg mixture.
Add soy sauce and sesame oil, then add green onion or spinach.
Serve immediately.

title: cardinal chicken salad
directions: Sprinkle apples with lemon juice.
Add chicken, celery, grapes and 3/4 Hellmann's.
Mix lightly.
Press mixture into 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Chill several hours.
Unmold onto serving platter.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix topping ingredients well and sprinkle over sweet potatoes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: san antonio stew
directions: In large Dutch oven, brown meat, half at a time, in hot oil. Return all meat to Dutch oven.
Add broth, hot water, picante sauce, onion, parsley, salt, cumin and garlic.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until tender.
Drain coarsely chopped tomatoes, reserving juice.
Add tomatoes and juice to Dutch oven with carrots, corn and zucchini.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Gradually add cold water to flour, mixing until smooth.
Gradually stir into stew.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute or until thickened.
Serves 8.

title: super fruit punch
directions: Follow directions on frozen fruit juice cans.
Combine all ingredients in large punch bowl.
I tried this for teetotalers and substituted rum flavoring for rum and it still tasted good.

title: picante sauce
directions: Chop or grind peppers and onions.
Peel tomatoes or use canned tomatoes.
Add onions and pepper to chopped tomatoes.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Seal in pint or half-pint jars.
Process 15 minutes, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 pints.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well and spoon into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: portuguese cognac truffles
directions: Melt chocolate in a medium bowl over nearly simmering water. Stir until smooth.
Remove from water; cool slightly.
In a small bowl, cream butter until smooth.
Heat cream in a very small heavy saucepan over medium-high heat until bubbles form around edge of pan; cool 3 minutes.
Pour cream over chocolate all at once. Whisk until blended.
Whisk in butter; cool mixture to room temperature.
Gradually stir in cognac.
Cover with a paper towel and plastic wrap; refrigerate about 5 hours or until firm.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients together and fry.

title: hollow donuts
directions: Poke hole in the center of each biscuit and stretch to about a 3-inch diameter.
Fry in preheated vegetable oil until golden brown.
Drain and coat with powdered sugar.
(Add cinnamon, coconut and/or nutmeg to the sugar, if you desire.)

title: pennsylvania dutch cottage cheese pie
directions: Combine cottage cheese, sugar, flour, salt, lemon rind and spices.
Add beaten egg yolks and mix thoroughly.
Add milk gradually and stir until smooth.
Fold in beaten egg whites
and pour into 9-inch pastry-lined pan.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: pretending-to-be-red cabbage slaw from northwoods inn
directions: Shred cabbage so it is irregular, with some fine and some coarse shreds.
Place in bowl with oil, vinegar, sugar, salt, seasoned salt, pepper, onion powder and paprika.
Mix well.

title: lemon cake
directions: Prepare cake using box directions.
Let cool.
Combine sugar and lemon juice in saucepan.
Add yolks.
Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Reduce heat and stir for 2 minutes.
Add butter a few pieces at a time.
Stir until melted.
Transfer to a bowl and cover with plastic wrap.
Chill.

title: monkey cake
directions: Boil brown sugar and 1/2 cup white sugar.
Cut biscuits in quarters
and
roll
each in nut mixture and lay in greased tube pan.
Pour	over
the biscuits the boiled sugar mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix all together and work into a ball.
Place on a floured surface and roll out.
Cut out and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cover with icing and decorate, if desired.
(These cookies are very moist if not rolled out too thin.)

title: hoecake
directions: In a bowl, combine cornmeal, flour and salt.
Add enough water to make a soft batter.
Heat bacon drippings in frying pan; pour into batter.
Cook slowly until brown.
Turn.
Brown second side. Yields 1 cake.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; stir in eggs, oil and vanilla, mixing well.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans, and let cool completely on wire racks.
Spread Cream Cheese Frosting between layers and on top of cake.
Yields one 3-layer cake.

title: armand's tuna delite
directions: Make tuna fish salad. Toast 4 slices of rye bread, and place large portions of tuna fish salad on rye toast. Add 4 strips of asparagus spears on top of tuna fish. Put 3 slices of cheese on top of asparagus and place under broiler, until cheese is melted.

title: royal spinach cream soup
directions: Combine spinach, 1/2 cup water, bouillon cubes and onion. Cover and cook until spinach is tender (do not overcook). Separate spinach with fork.
Add milk, 1 cup water, butter, salt and pepper and warm over low heat (or double boiler).
Serve when just heated (do not boil after adding milk).
Serve in small bowls.
Great for company.

title: quick tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner using package directions. Add next 4 ingredients; mix well.
Use butter to coat casserole dish and sprinkle potato chips on bottom of bowl.
Add tuna mixture.
Top with potato chips and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cherry pie
directions: Spread pie mix in pan; sprinkle cake mix on top.
Pour melted butter on top, then put the pecans on top.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Cut rhubarb and fill the pie shell about 2/3 full.
Mix egg yolks, sugar, salt and milk and pour over rhubarb.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, or until set.
Put meringue on top with the whites.

title: pear and celery salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Cover and chill. Arrange lettuce on individual salad plates.
Slice each pear into 10 slices; brush with lemon juice.
Arrange 5 pear slices on each plate.
Spoon about 1/2 cup celery mixture on each salad; sprinkle with cheese.

title: swedish meatballs(approximately 50 or 60)
directions: Melt currant jelly over low heat, stirring periodically, until all is melted.
Then add the hot ketchup and heat until it is hot. While melting the jelly, bake the meatballs in a low pan or jelly sheet for 15 minutes.
Mix meatballs and sauce together and serve.

title: marinade for london broil or flank steak
directions: Combine all ingredients for marinade.
Put meat in shallow dish.
Pour marinade over the meat.
Refrigerate and let set for 8 hours, turning at least once during this time.
Remove meat from marinade and grill according to preference.
Yields 2 3/4 cups.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Combine and let stand 20 minutes. Spoon into a 9-inch pie crust.
Dot with 1 tablespoon butter. Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: date bread
directions: Spoon soda over dates (cut up); add hot water.
Cool.
Mix shortening, brown sugar, egg, flour, salt and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cobbler pie(peach, apple or pear)
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, flour and milk.
Melt butter in bottom of pan.
Pour in batter.
Add fruit.
Sprinkle 1 cup sugar over top. Bake about 15 minutes or until brown on top.
use a 1-quart size dish to bake in.

title: swiss broccoli souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart souffle dish. Thaw broccoli. Drain well, pressing out as much liquid as possible with back of spoon.
Place in a medium bowl.

title: nora's southport breakfast shrimp
directions: In a large frying pan, combine onion, green pepper and bacon drippings.
Cook until golden.
Add shrimp.
Cook for 3 minutes, turning several times.
Add enough water to make a sauce, about 1 cup.
Cook for 2 minutes.

title: pumpkin rolls
directions: Beat eggs for five minutes until fluffy.
Add sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Mix together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Mix with pumpkin mixture. This will be thin.
Pour on greased and floured cookie sheet. Sprinkle finely chopped nuts on top.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°. While baking take clean dish towel and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Turn cake with nut side down.
Roll up with towel until cool.
Unroll and spread with filling and reroll without towel.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and diced onion.
Drain fat.
Combine cold beans and soups and enchilada sauce.
Cut tortillas into wedges. Cover bottom and sides of 9-inch pan with tortillas.
Pour in ingredients.
Grate cheese and sprinkle on top, then spread olives on top.
Bake at 375° until bubbling hot.
Use hot sauce of choice.
I use Pica Pica sauce.
Add to mix, if you like.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans until done.
Make white sauce with butter, flour and milk.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream.
Add remaining ingredients; add to beans.
Pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/2 pound grated Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry cheese cupcakes
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice, vanilla extract and eggs until light and fluffy.
Put vanilla wafer at bottom of cupcake liners.
Fill 3/4 full of cheese mixture and top with cherry filling.
Bake at 375° for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Bake the pie crusts; set aside to cool. Mix together the cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar. Spread in bottom of pie shells. Place sliced peaches on top of the cream cheese layer. Cook 1 cup sugar, water and cornstarch together until thickened. Add the jello. Cool. Pour over peach slices. Chill. Cover with Cool Whip.

title: harvard beets
directions: Trim beets 1/2 inch above the stems and place in large saucepan.
Cover with water and add bay leaf, allspice berries (if using) and the cloves.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 35 minutes or until tender.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Melt butter in square pan.
Add all the other ingredients.
Mix with fork until smooth.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve cold or warm, plain or with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: honey oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter, oil, honey, egg and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes on greased cookie sheet.
Keep cookies refrigerated.

title: maple road walnut bars
directions: Grease 8-inch square pan.
In a large bowl, beat the eggs. Add sugar and blend well.
Add melted oleo, flour and maple flavoring, walnuts and raisins.
Mix until well blended.
Spread evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares with a very sharp knife.

title: toast with tuna
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Blend in flour and seasoning. Cook, stirring, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Slowly add broth and cook for about 10 minutes, until thickened.
Stir in lemon juice and nutmeg.
Mix sauce with parsley and banana slices. Season with salt and pepper.
Lightly toast bread.
Spread tuna on toast.
Cover with sauce; top with grated cheese.
Brown in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes, or until heated through and cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Divide everything in half. Crumble half cake in bottom of bowl, spread half of pudding on cake.
Add half of other ingredients in order given.
Repeat for second layer. Refrigerate.
Garnish with cherries.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in a greased pan about 40 minutes in a 450° oven.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Put fat in saucepan.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper and mustard.
Add milk; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Blend in mayonnaise.
Add potatoes and onion.
Break up bacon and blend in. Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with crumbs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves up to 10.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Use part of margarine to grease a 10-inch deep dish.
Blend remaining margarine, eggs, milk, flour, salt and pepper in blender. Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain.
Add to blender also.
Add cheese and mushrooms.
Blend.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: catherine's shipwreck
directions: Spray crock-pot with Pam.
Slice potatoes thin; chop onions, green pepper and celery medium.
Rinse rice in hot water.
Arrange ingredients in cooker in 2 series of layers, starting with meat (raw), top with tomatoes, season to taste, potatoes, celery, onions, carrots, rice, kidney beans and top with tomato soup.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Heat water, sugar, cherries and juice to boiling.
Stir in jello until dissolved.
Cool.
Add pineapple and Coke.
Pour into 9-inch square dish.

title: cream of wheat pudding
directions: Bring milk, salt, sugar and lemon peel to a boil.
Add Cream of Wheat.
Boil gently 15 minutes.
Add 2 tablespoons water to 2 to 4 egg yolks; blend and add to Cream of Wheat mixture.
Whip egg whites to stiffness and add to mixture.
Chill.
Makes a big dish. Is good with fresh or frozen fruit.
Nourishing in hot weather or for sick children.

title: aunt mary's easter bread
directions: Put oleo in 1 cup scalded milk.
Take other 1/2 cup milk and let cool.
Add yeast and let this dissolve 5 minutes.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Mix and pour over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients; spoon onto greased muffin pan. Bake at 400° until done.

title: lemon-zucchini bread(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
With mixer, combine applesauce, apple juice concentrate, fructose, oil, eggs and lemon juice.
Beat until well blended.

title: tasty meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except catsup in bowl, mixing well. Place in greased 2-quart casserole.
Spread catsup over top (optional).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Slice zucchini and boil in water until tender; drain.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Put in double crust and bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: In saucepan, cook carrots, covered, in small amount of lightly salted water for 15 minutes or until just tender.
Add green pepper and cover and cook 3 minutes more.
Drain.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add water to make 1/3 cup liquid.

title: "monkey bread"
directions: Mix sugars and cinnamon together in large bowl. Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces, tossing each piece in sugar mixture to coat thoroughly. Pour the cut biscuits and all the sugar mixture into a well-greased Bundt pan. Melt butter and drizzle over top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Let cool for 15 minutes.

title: tony's super duper cheese dip
directions: Melt Velveeta in microwave while cooking sausage and onions together.
Mix and add all other ingredients to melted cheese. Serve with your favorite chips.

title: meatza pie
directions: Combine beef, milk, crumbs, and salt.
Press into a 9-inch pie pan.
Combine tomato sauce, oregano, mushrooms, and cheese. Layer on top of meat crust.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: rolled oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, salt and baking soda in bowl.
Add brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add oats.
Work with fingers until dough just holds together.
Roll dough to desired thickness on board or canvas sprinkled with confectioners sugar and cut into shapes.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: raisin carrot muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and ginger.
Stir in carrots, raisins and nuts.
Separately combine undrained pineapple, eggs, butter and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients until just blended.
Spoon into greased muffin cups (I line my muffin pans with paper cups).
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 to 18 muffins.

title: baked squash
directions: Parboil squash with salt and pepper.
Drain.
Mash.
