Stir eggs into cream of mushroom soup and add to squash.
Put in casserole, cover with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in moderate 350° oven.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix together.
Cover and refrigerate.
Mix 3 days.
On the fifth day, form 6 rolls (not large in diameter).
Lay rolls, side by side, on broiler pan.
Bake for 8 hours at 140°, turning every 2 hours.

title: caraway scones
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, add margarine and mix with hands until crumbled.
Add milk and egg then mix all together. Spray a baking pan with PAM.
Pat dough into an 8 inch circle on the baking sheet.
With a knife, score into eight wedges.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cut into 8 pie shaped wedges on score lines.

title: crab and cheese appetizers
directions: Mix everything together except crab meat. Mix until smooth, then add crab. Spread over English muffins. Place on cookie sheet and freeze about 30 minutes. Take out and cut into fourths. Place pieces in baggie to keep. When ready, place on cookie sheet and broil until brown and bubbly.

title: stuffed jalapenos
directions: Rinse jalapenos in cold water. Mix the cream cheese, garlic powder and pecans. Stuff jalapeno halves.

title: shrimp fettucine
directions: Saut fresh mushrooms and shrimp in vegetable oil in frying pan. Mix half and half with egg yolk and set aside. Cook and drain the fettuccine; place in large warm bowl. Pour melted butter over the fettuccine and mix well. Mix in the cream mixture; add Parmesan cheese and mix. Stir in the sauted shrimp and mushrooms. Season with pepper, garlic and paprika. Serves 4 to 6.

title: peach marshmallow icebox cake
directions: Mix butter, confectioners sugar and beaten egg yolks.
Cook over low heat until thick (stirring constantly).
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin that has been soaked in cold water 5 minutes. Cook slightly.
Add cut up marshmallows.
Cook thoroughly.
Add peaches.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites.
Place in mold, beginning and ending with vanilla crumbs.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream until fluffy the butter, brown sugar, white sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift and add flour, soda, salt and baking powder. Add oatmeal, nuts and coconut.
May add chocolate chips.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 8 to 9 dozen.

title: apple roll
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients to make dough; roll out. Put diced apples over dough; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll together.
Put into baking dish.
Add syrup made of 1 pint water and 1 1/2 cups sugar.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Coat a small nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add bell pepper and onion; cook 2 minutes stirring constantly.
Combine egg substitute and cumin; stir well and pour into skillet.
Cook until almost set stirring frequently. Stir in ham.
Remove from heat; set aside and keep warm.

Wrap tortillas in aluminum foil and heat at 325° for 15 minutes. Spread half of egg mixture down center of each tortilla and top each with 2 tablespoons cheese and 1 tablespoon picante sauce. Fold sides over; serve warm.
Contains 209 calories.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and pineapple juice.
Add pop before serving. Makes 1 gallon.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Mix chilies, soup, hamburger, cheese and chips in casserole.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potatoes and onions
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; dot with margarine.
Microwave, covered with lid or vented plastic wrap on Full power for 10 to 12 minutes, stirring twice.

title: aunt gracie's brine pickles(a salty crunchy pickle)
directions: Wash, slice or cut
or leave whole cucumbers.
Put them in canning jars.
Bring to boil water, vinegar and salt.
Add a tiny pinch of powdered alum to each jar.
Pour hot mixture over pickles and then seal.
Ready to eat in about 4 to 6 weeks.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large skillet over medium heat, saute celery and onions in butter until wilted.
Blend in flour well with mixture.
When well blended, pour in milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Add egg yolks, salt, red pepper and black pepper and cook for 5 minutes.
Place crabmeat in bowl for mixing; pour the cooked sauce over crabmeat.
Blend together well. Transfer into lightly greased 2-quart shallow casserole or 6 individual ramekins and sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Serve at once. Serves 6.
Freezes well.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat eggs in 2-quart bowl.
Add oil, brown sugar and vanilla. Beat all together.
In a 2-quart bowl, sift together wheat flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Add to egg mixture.
Fold in raisins, nuts and oats.
Put Pam or Wesson oil spray on cookie sheet.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: apple cider salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Combine liquid artificial sweetener, apple juice, lemon juice and salt.
Heat and add gelatin mixture, stirring until gelatin dissolves.
Cool until mixture begins to thicken.
Fold in applesauce.
Chill until set in individual molds.
Yield:
4 servings.
Protein 2 g, fat 0 g, carbohydrate 12 g, calories 56.
One serving = 1 fruit exchange.

title: chicken salad
directions: Tear chicken into small pieces.
Using large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Serve with Town House crackers after refrigerating.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: egg drop soup(for when you feel under the weather.)
directions: Bring chicken stock and bouillon to a boil.
Add cornstarch with cold water.
Thicken until clear.
Add scallions and stir. Add eggs, stirring gently with fork.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger and onion.
Cook and drain the noodles according to package.
Place 1/2 of the noodles in the casserole dish.
Cover with pizza sauce, then layer of meat.
Add oregano and basil.
Place more noodles, then cover that with pepperoni slices.
Add pizza sauce to cover.
Add 2 cheeses wanted.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Apple slices are used for dipping.
Dip apple slices in lemon juice before serving to keep from turning brown.
Mix all ingredients and dip apples.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Add sugar to hot sweet potatoes.
Mix with a fork.
Add Bisquick and work up with hands until right texture to roll out. Cut out with cookie cutters or glass.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: italian beef
directions: Boil meat until tender.
Keep juice and tear meat into small pieces.
Put meat back into juice, then add all ingredients to your taste.
Boil 1 1/2 to 2 hours on stove on low heat or cook in crock-pot on high for 4 1/2 to 5 hours.
Keep enough water in meat to have enough juice for your sandwiches.
Very good with mild Cheddar cheese.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Cut rolls in half (crossways).
Cook butter, mustard, poppy seed and Worcestershire sauce with onion until tender.
Layer ham and cheese between rolls.
Drizzle onion mixture over top of rolls.
Bake at 350° until rolls are brown.

title: apricot walnut bread
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Stir in oatmeal and apricots. Combine flour, brown sugar, baking powder and baking soda.
Stir in apricot mixture just until moistened.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into a greased loaf pan (8 x 4 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then remove to wire rack.

title: christmas horns(recipe from czeckoslovakia)
directions: Cream together butter and sugar well; add eggs, flour and walnuts.
Chill, then form into horns.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes, until pink.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Set aside to cool on wax paper-covered pan.

title: spicy oriental noodle salad
directions: Cook and drain linguine; return to pot.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and then beaten eggs.
Add milk, alternately with sifted flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix blueberries with 2 tablespoons of the original amount of flour. Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes 2 dozen muffins.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine pineapple, apples, bananas, pecans and strawberries in a bowl.
Mix well.
Combine reserved pineapple juice, pudding mix and Tang in a small bowl; mix well.
Pour over fruit; toss to mix.
Chill until serving time.

title: golden baked onions
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 2-quart baking dish.
Melt 1 stick butter in skillet over medium heat.
Add onions; cook until tender and translucent, stirring frequently, about 15 minutes. Transfer onions to prepared dish.
Combine soup, milk, salt and pepper; pour over onions.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Dip bread slices in butter on one side.
Arrange, buttered side up, over onion mixture to cover completely.
Bake until bread is browned, about 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Put softened cream cheese on a flat plate.
Spread cocktail sauce over cream cheese.
Sprinkle shrimp over the cream cheese and cocktail sauce.
Refrigerate.
Spread on crackers.

title: knorr spinach dip
directions: Stir 1 package soup mix, sour cream and mayonnaise until blended.
Stir in spinach and chopped onions.
Cover; chill 2 hours.
Stir before serving.
Makes 4 cups.

title: old fashioned oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix in order of ingredients above.
Form balls the size of a walnut.
Place on greased cookie sheet an inch apart.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Give each child in attendance one cookie each immediately after baking.
If they fail to eat them, do not serve to company.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Into large bowl sift together flour, sugar and baking powder. With pastry blender, cut in butter until coarse crumbs form.
Stir in pecans; set aside.
In small bowl, mix milk, vanilla and egg until well blended.
Stir in bananas until well blended.
Add milk-banana mixture to dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until loaf is golden brown
and toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove; cool on rack.
Makes 1
loaf.

title: green beans with fresh dill and scallions
directions: In a large pot bring water to a boil.
Add beans and cook over medium heat, covered, 7 minutes; drain.
In a large skillet over medium heat, melt margarine; saute scallions 3 to 5 minutes, or until wilted.
Add beans; toss with margarine and scallions.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes or until tender.
Add dill, salt and pepper; toss to completely coat beans.

title: rhubarb-strawberry preserves
directions: Bring rhubarb and sugar to slow boil.
Remove from heat; add jello (undiluted) and stir well.
Put into small jars.
Store in refrigerator.
Can also be frozen.

title: spaghetti for large crowd
directions: In large kettle, saute onions, celery and peppers.
Add tomato paste, canned tomatoes, spaghetti sauce, bay leaves and garlic. Cook for 3 to 4 hours on simmer.
In another pan, brown the hamburger.
Add to sauce and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over spaghetti noodles.

title: dijon vinaigrette salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in covered jar and shake.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple cookies
directions: On waxed paper, stir together dry ingredients and set aside. Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and orange rind.
Gradually add flour.
Gently stir in apples, raisins, oats and nuts.
Drop by level tablespoon a few inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until edges are lightly browned, about 15 to 17 minutes.

title: never fail pie meringue
directions: In small saucepan mix cornstarch, sugar, water and salt.
Cook until thick and clear (about 1 minute).
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Continue beating while slowly pouring cooked mixture. Continue beating 5 minutes.
Cover filled pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: cheesy crock pot chicken
directions: Rinse chicken & sprinkle with salt, pepper, and garlic powder. Mix undiluted soup & pour over chicken in crock pot. Cook on low all day. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: spoon bread
directions: Scald milk (do not boil).
Stir in oleo, cornmeal and salt. Cook, stirring constantly, until cornmeal comes away from sides of pan and thickens.
Set aside to cool until lukewarm.
Add beaten egg yolk; mix thoroughly.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites; mix gently but thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured 2-quart baking dish and bake at 375° for 1 hour or until top is golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Good side dish with pork and fresh vegetables.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put oleo in a 4-quart bowl.
Microwave 1 minute on High until melted.
Add milk and sugar.
Microwave for 3 minutes; stir. Microwave 2 minutes; stir.
Microwave 3 minutes; stir.
Microwave 2 1/2 minutes; stir.
Scrape sides often.
Add peanut butter, marshmallow and vanilla.
Mix all together until melted.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix by hand all ingredients until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Very moist cake.
Keeps great in covered dish.

title: mandarin orange dessert
directions: Layer ingredients as listed.

title: bacon-wrapped chestnuts
directions: Marinate water chestnuts in soy sauce for 1 hour.
Wrap each chestnut with bacon.
Secure with toothpick.
Place in pan and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve.

title: confetti cookies
directions: Cream sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Add nuts and gumdrops.
Mix well.
Put about a teaspoon of dough for each cookie on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen cookies.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 1/2 x 9-inch oblong pan.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Add sugar, shortening and salt to milk and dissolve. Add yeast and sugar in water to dissolve.
When milk has cooled to lukewarm, add dissolved yeast and eggs. Add flour and knead dough lightly. Put in greased bowl and cover lightly.
Let rise to double in bulk.
Knead dough lightly and roll out to about 1/2-inch thick. Cut with biscuit cutter and brush top lightly with melted butter. Fold over and mash edges together.
Brush tops lightly with melted butter.
Fold over and mash edges together.
Brush tops lightly with butter. Cover lightly.
Let rise until about double.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 50 rolls. Recipe can be cut in half.

title: cheese ball
directions: Save at least 1/2 cup pecans to roll ball in. Mix all ingredients together and chill slightly. Shape into ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: kielbasa (polish sausage) and sauerkraut
directions: Put sausage in pan.
Pour can of sauerkraut in bowl and mix a little brown sugar with it.
It should have a sweet and sour taste.
Then spread this over the sausage.
Cover with foil for 1/2 to 3/4 of the baking time.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh strawberries with cream dip
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sour cream, confectioners sugar and orange liqueur until smooth; chill 1 hour. Fill 8 cordial glasses or tiny cups with cream dip.
Place each on a dessert plate and surround with whole berries for dipping in cream.
Serves 8.

title: aunt cindy's potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cornflakes and 1/4 c.
butter and mix well.
Pour into a buttered 9x13x2 baking dish.
Combine corn flakes and melted butter and sprinkle over top of potatoes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves twelve.

title: salmon loaf
directions: In a bowl, combine salmon, crumbs, onion, butter and salt. Combine milk and egg.
Add to salmon mixture and mix well.
Shape into loaf in greased, shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
Serve with Piquant Sauce.

title: fannie mae mint brownies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool.

title: cobbler pie
directions: Use deep dish for baking as this really rises.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Boil water; add bouillon cubes, tomatoes, spinach and veggies. Cook ground beef and add to broth.
Boil 10 minutes.
Add pasta. Cook 15 to 20 more minutes; add salt and pepper to taste.
Enjoy! It's quick, easy and delicious!

title: chocolate chip sour cream rum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 7 minutes.
Batter will be very stiff.
Bake in a greased tube pan at 325° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Leave in pan 20 to 30 minutes to solidify before removing from pan.

title: summer squash casserole(microwave)
directions: Place squash and onion in 3-quart casserole.
Cook just until tender-crisp (5 minutes), covered.
Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots.
Fold into drained squash and onion. Combine stuffing mix with butter or margarine.
Spread 1/2 of stuffing in 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture over top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing over vegetables.
Cook 7 to 10 minutes or until heated through.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Combine meat, rice, onion and salt.
(May moisten with a small amount of water, if needed.)
Mix well and form into balls.
Place in a deep baking dish.
In same bowl used to mix meat mixture, combine tomato soup, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot; pour tomato sauce over the meatballs.

title: cool whip salad
directions: Drain all but 1 tablespoon juice from oranges and pineapple. Mix all ingredients together.
Keep refrigerated.

title: barbecue style meat loaf
directions: Mix together ground beef, crumbs, onion, beaten egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 can sauce.
Form into loaf and place in a shallow baking pan about 7 x 10-inch.
Combine rest of the sauce and all other ingredients and pour over the loaf.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix the well beaten eggs, flour, sugar, pineapple and salt together, then pour in a buttered baking dish.
Melt the butter in a separate pan and put the cubes of bread in the melted butter. Be sure all cubes are well covered.
Place the cubes over pineapple mixture and bake in moderate oven at 400° for 1/2 hour or until browned.
Serves 6.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set and brown.

title: bird's nest cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon into a large mixing bowl. Make a well in center; pour remaining ingredients (combined) into well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large dish.

title: dill carrot sticks
directions: Wash and peel carrots and cut into 2-inch strips.
Cook until almost tender.

title: pecan pie
directions: Grease pie pan.
Make crust with flour, water and crisco.
Roll out.
Put in pie pan.
Use a fork to design the edges.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Stir eggs, syrup, butter and vanilla with fork to blend well.
Stir in pecans.
Bake 50-55 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Prepare spaghetti as directed.
Add eggs and grated Parmesan cheese; mix lightly.
Line greased casserole dish with spaghetti mixture.
Spoon sour cream over spaghetti.
Brown meat and drain. Stir in herb and mix tomato paste and water.
Simmer 10 minutes. Spoon over sauce mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella cheese; return to oven until cheese melts.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, soda and salt; pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Then mix fruit cocktail, eggs, brown sugar and coconut.
Beat well; pour into cake pan on top of first mixture. Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Mix in saucepan 3/4 cup sugar, butter and condensed milk; bring to full rolling boil and boil 2 minutes.
Put holes in cake; pour 3rd mixture over cake and bake until mixture in holes boils up.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Hard-boil eggs.
Cut up 5 eggs.
Add to macaroni.
Dice pickles, green pepper and onion.
Add to macaroni. Mix Miracle Whip and pickle juice until creamy.
Then add sugar, pepper, salt, and mustard.
Add to macaroni.
Mix together.
Take the last 2 eggs and slice.
Put on top of macaroni.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix the oil, soy sauce, sunflower seeds and sugar.
Mix all ingredients together and let set for several hours or overnight.

title: waffles
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt into a bowl. Put egg yolks, milk and butter into blender. Cover and run until blended. Mix with dry ingredients. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in last.

title: forever ambers
directions: Combine candy, milk, coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased baking dish, 10 x 13-inch.
Bake at 300° for about 15 minutes until bubbly.
Stir in sugar and drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: carrot pecan cake
directions: Mix flour and next 4 ingredients; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine oil and sugar; mix well.
Add 1/2 of flour mixture; blend.
Add remaining flour alternately with eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add carrots and pecans; mix well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients.
Sift in dry ingredients together. Add zucchini.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: gnocchi siciliano
directions: Saute garlic in butter; remove garlic.
Blend in flour and salt and cook mixture on low heat until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat and slowly stir in broth and half and half.
Bring to boil over low heat, stirring constantly.
Serve over gnocchi which have been cooked according to package directions.
Sprinkle with Romano cheese.

title: coconut ice
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil and boil 10 minutes, stirring all the time.
Take off heat and beat in 1 large cup of coconut and a few drops of vanilla essence.
Stand in cold water and beat until it thickens.
Pour half into buttered plate. Color remaining half with cochineal or cocoa and pour on top.

title: linguine salad
directions: Mix all ingredients (except tomatoes) in large bowl. Refrigerate. Add tomatoes just before serving.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine Parmesan cheese, corn flakes, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
In a second dish, beat egg until foamy.
Stir in milk; dip chicken pieces in egg mixture.
Coat evenly with Parmesan cheese-crumb mixture.
Place chicken, skin side up, in a single layer in a well-greased or foil lined baking pan.
Drizzle with melted butter or margarine.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until tender. (No need to cover or turn chicken while baking.)
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheesy fried chicken
directions: Heat 1/2 to 1-inch oil in a large skillet.
Beat together eggs, milk and Tabasco sauce.
Dip chicken pieces in mixture. Cover well.
Mix flour, cheese, parsley, salt and oregano together in paper bag. Shake chicken pieces in bag until thoroughly coated. Place in hot oil.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes. Drain chicken on paper towels or bags.
Serves 4.

title: walnut and basil cheese spread
directions: Combine cheese and sour cream in a bowl; stir well.
Stir in walnuts and remaining ingredients.
Spoon into tomato shells, if desired.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Serve at room temperature with French bread.
Yield: 3 cups.

title: chicken in a blanket
directions: Blend cream cheese and margarine.
Add other ingredients, except rolls.
Combine 2 rolls.
Arrange in flat rectangular shape.
Place 2 tablespoons of filling on each rectangle.
Bring ends together to form squares; pinch to hold together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden.
Top with butter.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each.
Alternate flour with baking powder and milk, then add flavoring.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes (or 275°).

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese in pan over low heat, stirring constantly, mix in vanilla.
Pour over mixture of powdered sugar and cocoa in bowl.
Mix quickly until smooth.
Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat pecans over top.
Let stand until set.
Cut into squares.

title: egg casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine croutons and cheese.
In another bowl, combine eggs, milk, salt, mustard, onion powder and pepper.
Mix until blended.
Pour crouton mixture into pan and pour egg mixture over.
Crumble bacon on top of casserole.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Brown
chicken	and
onion
together in a 12-inch Dutch oven. Mix
juice and soup and pour over chicken.	Let come to a boil. Mix
the
rest
of	the ingredients and pour over the chicken. Bake 1 hour with 12 coals on the top and 14 coals on the bottom.

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add unbeaten egg whites, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add these, the water and extract, all at once.
Beat at medium speed 2 or 3 minutes.
Pour into 3 greased 9 x 9-inch pans and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Caution:
Do not overbake.
Cool before frosting.

title: lilliput meat balls(makes 120)
directions: Mix into balls size of small walnut.
Brown in butter.
Drain off fat.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix together; fry until brown on both sides.

title: graham cracker crisps
directions: Break crackers where sectioned; lay on cookie sheet as close as possible.
Melt butter, margarine and sugar and boil exactly 3 minutes.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Add nuts on top.
Bake 10 minutes in 325° oven.
Remove from cookie sheet as soon as they have cooled slightly.
Makes 60 quarter-crackers.

title: "water-whip" pie crust
directions: Put Spry in medium-sized bowl.
Add boiling water and milk. Beat with electric beater until smooth.
Add flour and salt.
Stir until dough clings together.
Pick up and knead until smooth, soft and pliable.
Can be rolled between wax paper or on a floured board. Makes two crusts for 9-inch pie.

title: seafood dip
directions: Stir cream cheese (softened) and add all the rest of the ingredients, except cheese. Spread in a 9-inch pie pan. Top with cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes until lightly browned. Serve with crackers, chips, etc.

title: surprise bars
directions: Mix oatmeal, sugar and butter.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter together and spread carefully over baked oatmeal mixture.
Cool. Cut into squares.

title: the oh my goodness pie
directions: Mix the lemonade with the ice cream.
Using a 9 x 13 pan, make your crust, pour in the pie mixture.
Place in the freezer. About 30 - 45 minutes before serving, remove from freezer.

title: tuna mousse
directions: Drain tuna.
Mix with celery and pimento.
Soften gelatin; add to heated soup.
Blend all other ingredients.
Add heated soup; pour into tuna.

title: guilt-free dessert(we call it "that pink stuff")
directions: Combine everything and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Enjoy with a clear conscience.

title: homemade chicken salad sandwiches
directions: Dice or tear chicken into small pieces.
Toss with celery, relish, almonds, sugar, egg (if desired) and use enough salad dressing to make good sandwich consistency.
Serve on whole wheat or favorite bread.

title: omelet supreme
directions: Beat egg whites with sugar until stiff.
In frying pan precook ingredients of choice.
Fold egg yolks into stiff whites.
Pour into pan with pre-cooked ingredients, stir occasionally gently. Cook on stove top until lightly brown on edges.
Then finish cooking in oven 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Flip onto plate, cut and serve.

title: corn bread
directions: Beat eggs;
add
oil.
Beat well. Add sour cream, salt, muffin mix and
lastly corn.
Bake in well-greased pan at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry-and-orange relish
directions: Chop the cranberries, orange and lemon.
Add the sugar, pecans and Cointreau.
Mix briefly.
Cover and let stand at room temperature 12 hours.
Refrigerate overnight.
Makes 3 cups.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Add to macaroni the pickle relish, mayo and green peas.
Mix all together and add salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish with green olives.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Combine dry ingredients; add eggs and salad oil. Stir until well mixed.
Add vanilla, pineapple, bananas and nuts. Spoon batter into large greased and floured sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: bubbles
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use thread spools, fly swatter or plastic bubble loops that make lots of bubbles.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° in a greased casserole.

title: ten minute peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and salt in a 2-quart Pyrex dish. Microwave on High setting for 4 1/2 minutes.
Stir in peanuts. Microwave on High setting for 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir mixture. Microwave 1 more minute.
Stir in vanilla, margarine and baking soda and beat until light and foamy.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: peanutty gems
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt, set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter and peanut butter until smooth. Add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well. Gradually beat in flour mixture until well combined.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 1\2 cup of sugar in shallow dish.
Roll balls in sugar to coat.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°for 10 min.
Immediatly press a candy into a center of each cookie.
Remove from sheet.
Cool on wire rack. Make about 48 cookies.

title: yogurt with fruit
directions: Take the seeds from the head and let them dry.
Them make a brine of 1 1/2 cups salt to 2 quarts of water.
Let them soak for 3 days.
Drain and put them on a cookie sheet in 300° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 250° until they are dry.
Stir seeds every 10 minutes, until they are done.
They are done when they crack when opened, which will be 45 to 60 minutes, depending on how many you have on the cookie sheet.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter
and sugar.
Add eggs and pecans.
Add dry ingredients
to creamed butter mixture alternately with mashed bananas.
Add vanilla and bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Premeasure baking soda.
Cook syrup, sugar and peanuts to hard crack stage or until peanuts turn from white to light brown in color.
Remove from heat and add baking soda immediately. Stir briskly and quickly pour into buttered cookie sheet lengthwise. Do not smooth or spread.
Cool and then break into pieces.

title: black walnut fudge
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and milk in heavy 5-quart saucepan; bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour into 3 greased 9-inch square or 2 greased 13 x 9-inch baking pans.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 6 pounds.

title: spaghetti sauce with meat
directions: Brown beef with onion and garlic; drain well.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Simmer.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion. In a bowl, mix both soups, green chilies with juice, enchilada sauce and handful of cheese. When hamburger and onion are cooked, drain grease and add to mixture. Lightly grease a glass cake pan and put a thin layer of meat sauce. Cover with flour tortillas to fit the pan, then put more meat sauce. Cover with cheese and add tortillas. Keep layering to the top, ending with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through. Cover with foil for the first 20 minutes of baking.

title: barbecue italian beef
directions: Place beef in roaster. Combine all other ingredients and pour over meat. Bake at 300° for 6 hours, covered. Shred with fork. Serve on buns.

title: chicken caesar salad
directions: Heat oil in nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
Toss chicken with lemon and pepper seasoning and garlic powder to evenly coat.
Add to skillet and cook 4 to 5 minutes or until thoroughly cooked, stirring frequently. Remove from heat. Do not drain off fat.
In a small bowl, combine vinegar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce with a whisk.
Stir into chicken mixture.
In a large bowl, toss lettuce with chicken mixture, croutons and cheese. Top with fresh grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: waldorf red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; then add vanilla and coloring.
Mix well on electric mixer.
Add eggs, flour, cocoa and buttermilk. Mix well.
Then add soda mixed with vinegar; foams up, mix well. Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 3 (9-inch) round cake pans. Pour batter equally into three pans (about 1-inch from the top) and bake 30 minutes.
Cool layers and carefully remove layers from pans to cool completely.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs, flour and then bananas.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk, ReaLime and food coloring.
In a small bowl, stiffly beat 1 egg white.
Fold into sweetened condensed milk mixture.
Turn into shell.

title: onion soup
directions: Brown onions in butter in a large deep skillet until tender. Add dissolved bouillon water and seasoning. Heat thoroughly. Place a slice of toasted bread in each soup bowl and pour soup over it. Sprinkle with cheese. Yield: 6 servings.

title: scallops with vermicelli
directions: Rinse scallops.
Combine scallops, juice and parsley in glass dish.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator while preparing sauce.

title: manicotti(stuffed shells)
directions: Boil jumbo shells 6 minutes and test.
Do not overcook. Drain.
Mix Ricotta, grated Mozzarella cheese, eggs, parsley, salt and pepper together for filling.
Put spaghetti sauce on bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Fill each shell 1/2 to 3/4 full with cheese mixture and put in pan.
Top with sauce and more grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes, covered with foil.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: pineapple icebox cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Simmer pineapple and sugar in small saucepan until sugar dissolves. Poke holes in cake with long tined fork. Cover with warm pineapple mixture and chill until completely cool, at least 1 hour.
Prepare pudding according to package directions. Stir in coconut. Spread over pineapple. Cover with whipped topping.
Sprinkle with pecans. Keep covered in refrigerator. Serve chilled. Serves 12 generously.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Grate cheese in large bowl.
Chop pimento with juice and mix with cheese.
Mix rest of ingredients and stir well into cheese.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook Minute rice as per instructions on box.

title: roast beef
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Place roast, fat side up, in an uncovered pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Roast in slow oven at 300°.
Do not baste or turn.
There will be less shrinkage than in a hot oven and the meat will be brown and juicy, never dry.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Mix sugar, butter, corn syrup, water and salt together. Microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Stir after 5 minutes.
Add soda and mix well.
Pour over popped corn and toss, coating corn and peanuts well.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add beaten egg and mix well. Add vanilla and flour in which has been sifted the baking powder and salt. Lastly, add the chopped nuts. Divide into two equal parts and make each into a 1 1/2-inch roll. Roll each in waxed paper and put in icebox overnight. Cut in 1/8-inch slices and bake at 325° for about 10 minutes.

title: a happy home
directions: First, use care in the selection.
Not too young, but tender, with a potential for growth.

title: company tuna casserole
directions: Mix mushroom soup, Cheez Whiz, pepper and milk well in bowl. (It helps to heat Cheez Whiz in microwave about 30 seconds.)
Add tuna, then cooked shells.
Put in casserole and top with cheese slices (break in half), then crushed potato chips.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Yields 6 servings.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar.
Let stand at room temperature for 4 hours.
Cover and refrigerate.
Double recipe makes 1 quart.

title: spicy baked beans
directions: Combine beans, brown sugar, chopped onion and green pepper in a 1-quart casserole. Garnish with onion and pepper rings.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: lazy wife cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, milk and cocoa.
Bring to a boil.

title: excellent molasses cookies
directions: Bake 11 minutes at 350°.
Roll in white sugar just before baking.
Chilled dough works best.
YUMMMMMM....

title: mom's chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli in a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Combine soup and milk; pour over all.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot. Makes 3 or 4 servings.
Fresh broccoli or asparagus may be used.

title: granola
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine oil, honey and vanilla in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Mixture will froth up.
Remove from heat.
Add dry ingredients.
Spread on 2 cookie sheets and bake at 350° until golden brown.
Allow to cool.
Store airtight.

title: mildred's cowboy beans
directions: Cook and drain hamburger.
Drain pork and beans.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly and bake 45 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: best ever peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir margarine, sugar and milk in heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan; bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in peanut butter chips until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Cool. When firm, cut into squares.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix all ingredients in large Dutch oven and cook over medium heat until thick and smooth, about 2 hours. Makes about 8 1/2 pints.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Add sugar and salad oil; beat well.
Stir in chocolate, vanilla and zucchini.
Sift flours, salt, cinnamon and baking soda and add to above.
Stir in nuts. Grease well two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done (tester comes out clean).

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Divide and process in blender just a few seconds on grate.
Repeat until all of the mixture has been blended.
Store in a tightly covered container and chill. Keeps well for several weeks.

title: frozen pea salad
directions: Layer in order given in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Do not stir. (Serve as is.)
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add mashed bananas and egg and beat well.
Sift together other dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture, beating constantly.
Add nuts and oatmeal.
Blend thoroughly.

title: blotkake simenstad - norway(sponge cake with cream and berries)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour 8 1/2-inch spring-form pan.
In bowl with electric mixer, beat 3/4 cup sugar and eggs until thick and pale.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt over mixture and fold in gently, but thoroughly.
Turn batter into pan. Bake cake in middle of oven for 25 minutes.
Cool on rack. Remove cake from pan and halve horizontally with a serrated knife. In a bowl with electric mixer, beat cream to soft peaks and beat in remaining 2 teaspoons of sugar and vanilla.
Beat until stiff. In a bowl, fold 1/2 berries into half of cream.
Spread mixture evenly onto bottom cake layer and top with remaining layer. Spread remaining cream on top and side of cake and arrange remaining berries on top.

title: party chicken(takes 3 hours to cook)
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with a piece of bacon.
Cover bottom of flat greased baking dish (8 x 12 x 2-inch) with chipped beef. Arrange chicken breasts on chipped beef.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over all. Refrigerate.
When ready, bake at 275° for 3 hours, covered.
Uncover the last 15 minutes.
Use more sour cream and mushroom soup if you want a sauce to pour over rice.

title: rice balls
directions: Filling:
Brown ground beef and onion (drain grease if necessary) and add sauce.
Add peas and simmer until peas are tender.
Cool to lukewarm.
Mix rice, cheese, 4 eggs and 1 1/2 cups spaghetti sauce.
Using 1/2 cup rice mix, form a cup in your hand; fill with 2 tablespoons meat filling.
Add more rice mixture, forming a ball.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon and flake.
Heat milk and add butter and bread. Mix well and let stand 5 minutes.
Add salmon liquid.
Beat until smooth.
Add yolks, pepper, onion, lemon juice, green pepper and salmon.
Fold in egg whites.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: rice and peas or beans
directions: Wash and pick over beans.
In a large pot combine meat, beans, cold water, onion, garlic, thyme, sugar, sweet pepper, hot pepper and
celery.
Cover pot.
Bring to a boil and cook until beans are
soft.	Add
salt, oil and rice. Add water if necessary.
Cook on low heat until rice is cooked and water is absorbed.

title: ice cream
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt. Gradually stir in milk until smooth.
Stir in corn syrup and egg yolks.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat, stir in vanilla.
Pour in large bowl and cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours until chilled.
Stir in cream.
Freeze in 2-quart freezer following manufacturer's directions.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour into well-greased iron skillet and bake in preheated 450° oven until golden brown.

title: dill pickled green string beans
directions: Cook beans for 8 minutes; drain and immerse in ice water. Drain and pack in quart jars endways.
Add dill and garlic per quart jar.
Bring to a boil the vinegar, water and salt.
Pour in jars to cover beans and seal.

title: peanut pie
directions: Sprinkle 1/3 cup of peanuts over baked pie shell.
Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Blend in peanut butter.
Pour over nuts in pie shell.
Sprinkle 1/3 cup of nuts over pudding. Chill until set.
Prepare 1 package Dream Whip or use frozen whipped topping, thawed.
Spread over set pudding carefully. Sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Chill.

title: icing for grandma's carrot cake
directions: Combine
sugar,
corn syrup and water in a heavy saucepan. Cook
over
medium
heat,
stirring
frequently,
until mixture comes
to
a
boil
and sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking, stirring often, until mixture reaches soft ball stage (240°). Remove from heat, but keep warm.

title: hot mustard sauce
directions: Mix mustard and vinegar; let set overnight or 8 hours.
Add remaining ingredients; cook in double boiler until thickens.
Stir constantly.
Use only 1 ounce of mustard if you want it mild.

title: granny's bean goulash
directions: After soaking beans overnight, boil with pork, bacon drippings, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook until beans are barely tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
In a large skillet, brown hamburger, onion, pepper and celery.
Brown until onions begin to turn transparent.
Add garlic powder, chili powder, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Simmer about 10 minutes and add to beans.
Cool, ladle into 1 quart freezer containers.
Label, freeze.
To serve:
Thaw and place in a Dutch oven.
Simmer until juice is thick.
Serve with cabbage slaw and cornbread.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Fry hamburger and onion; drain off grease.
In a soup kettle, mix hamburger, onion mixture and cover with 3 cups water.
Add frozen vegetables, celery, barley, V-8 juice and bouillon.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for several hours, the longer the better.
Serves 6.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut meat up and dredge in flour.
Brown meat on all sides. Add onion, salt, pepper, sugar, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer, covered, 1 1/2 hours or until meat is almost tender.
Add carrots and potatoes to meat.
Cover and cook another 30 minutes.
Add oregano and peas.
Cook an additional 15 minutes, or until meat and vegetables are done.
If desired, thicken gravy before serving.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Combine onions, vinegar, water, sugar, salt, pepper and mustard in large pan.
Bring to a boil. Add rest of ingredients and cook on low heat until heated through. Yields 6 servings.

title: carrot fruitcake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt-shaped pan.
Process prunes and water in a blender or food processor until smooth. Scrape mixture into a large bowl.
Stir in brown sugar, eggs, egg whites, orange peel, juice and oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Fill Bundt pan with mixture.
Bake for 1 hour or until a pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack 15 minutes, then remove from pan and cool completely.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt oleo with brown sugar so sugar melts.
Cool 10 minutes. Add eggs one at a time and then other ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in greased 12 x 18-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until bars are lite golden color.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar when bars are cooled.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Combine these ingredients and mix well.
Spread in long pan. Pack tightly.

title: red beans and sausage
directions: Prepare red beans ahead, following cooking directions on package.
Add onions, celery, parsley, garlic powder and sliced sausage and simmer for 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste. Serve over steamy rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot artichoke spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: true sponge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Use a 9-inch tube pan and make sure it is free of any grease. Beat egg whites until frothy; sprinkle with cream of tartar; continue beating until just stiff, but not dry. Gradually beat in 1/4 cup fruit sugar and set aside. Beat egg yolks until thick; gradually beat in cold water; then beat in 3/4 cup fruit sugar. Blend or sift together flour and salt. Sift or sprinkle the dry ingredients over the egg yolk mixture, a little at a time, combining lightly after each addition. Fold in vanilla and lemon extract. Carefully fold in the meringue. Turn into pan. Cut through batter with a knife to eliminate air bubbles. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 60 to 75 minutes. As soon as the cake is baked, invert it and allow to hang suspended until cold. To remove from pan, loosen with a knife and shake carefully from the pan.

title: cajun beans and rice
directions: Soak beans in water in a heavy kettle.
Add onion, green pepper, celery, ham, salt, red and black pepper.
Bring to a boil and then simmer gently 2 1/2 hours.
Stir in green onions and parsley.
Cook very slowly, about 30 minutes.
Serve over beds of hot fluffy rice.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix flour, sugar and butter with fingers until crumbly.
Put apples in shallow baking dish.
Mix water, vanilla and salt together. Sprinkle over apples. Sprinkle flour mixture evenly over apples.
Bake at 350° until apples are tender and top is browned, about 40 minutes.
Good with ice cream.

title: easy sticky buns
directions: Thaw dough overnight in refrigerator.
Line bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan with pecans or walnuts.
Tear 1 loaf of bread into pieces and place on bottom of pan.
Melt butter in milk, then add brown sugar and cinnamon.
Remove from burner.
Add dry pudding and stir until dissolved.
Pour over dough in pan.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, butter, eggs and mashed bananas.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Pour into batter and mix.
Blend in 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake in a greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: homemade applesauce
directions: Place the apples in a large saucepan and pour in the cider. Simmer uncovered over medium-high heat for 40 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes or so to prevent sticking.
Stir in the sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg and continue to cook, stirring to break down the apples, until it is a chunky sauce.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except shrimp.
When ingredients are thoroughly mixed, add shrimp.
Stir all together.
Spread on your favorite cracker.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put slice of cheese on each breast.
Mix soup and water and pour over chicken and cheese. Combine dressing crumbs and melted butter and sprinkle over top of chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Drain juice off 2 pints of either fresh or frozen strawberries (or use 2 cans of either blueberries or cherry pie mixture).

title: tomato chow chow
directions: Add to tomatoes, chopped: green onions, black olives, green onions, jalapenos, garlic, vinegar, oil, salt and sugar.
Put in clean jars.
Seal and keep in refrigerator.
Will keep several weeks.
Very good with chips.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix together Eagle Brand milk and cream cheese until smooth. Set aside.
Mix together pudding and milk.
Add Cool Whip to mixture and set aside.
In a glass casserole dish, alternate graham cracker crumbs, sliced bananas and pudding mixture.
Top with crumbs.

title: spicy zucchini bars
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients (dry) in medium bowl; set mixture aside.
Combine eggs, oil, sugar, yogurt and vanilla in a large bowl; beat well.
Stir in zucchini.
Add flour mixture and stir just until moistened.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes clean.
Cool completely in pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into bars.

title: potato casserole
directions: Crush up hash browns in baking dish. Saute onion and bell pepper with 1/4 cup butter.
Mix soup, cheese, sour cream and salt with onion and bell pepper.
Pour over hash browns.
Top with corn flakes.
Drizzle 1/4 cup butter over corn flakes. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: microwave macaroni and cheese
directions: Drain macaroni; rinse with hot water.
Mix all ingredients and cook in 2-quart round microwave-safe bowl.
Cover; microwave on High 11 minutes, stirring twice.
Uncover and cook 4 additional minutes.
Let stand 3 to 4 minutes before serving.

title: mom's pizza dough
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together in a mixing bowl. Gradually add flour, cup by cup, until a soft dough is formed. Dough should not be sticky, so add more flour if necessary, tablespoon by tablespoon.
Knead the dough and place in a greased bowl covered by wax paper.
Place bowl into a warm area to rise for 2 to 3 hours.
(To make dough rise more quickly, 3/4 hour, place the bowl of dough into another bowl of very warm water.)
When fully risen, knead and divide dough into 3 equal parts and stretch onto 3 greased pizza pans.
Put pizza sauce on the pizza, then bake at 400° until crust is golden, then put cheese and toppings on pizza.
Bake again until cheese melts.

title: cranberry-orange salad
directions: Grind together the cranberries, walnuts, orange, orange rind, celery and pineapple.
Stir jello, sugar and water until dissolved.
Add all ingredients.
Let jell overnight or several hours.

title: pineapple yogurt cake
directions: Mix Cool Whip, yogurt and crushed pineapple (drained) together. Refrigerate for about 2 hours.
Prepare cake as directed on box except substitute half water with half pineapple juice and maybe add some crushed pineapple.
When cake cools, add Cool Whip mixture.
Decorate with sliced pineapple and refrigerate.

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Dilute soup with water or broth.
Add diced chicken, onion, celery, nuts and 2/3 cup of noodles.
Mix all together.
Sprinkle rest of noodles over top and bake at 325° until bubbly and toasted.
It is best to wait until casserole is bubbling before putting noodles on top so that they don't scorch.

title: and then there's meat loaf
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in the olive oil until tender. Put into a large bowl with the meat, eggs, salt, parsley and pepper. Blend very well with your clean hands. Roll the mixture into a loaf shape and put into a loaf pan. You should have a little room around all sides of the meat. Pour the spaghetti sauce over the meat loaf and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together milk, eggs, sugar and oil.
Slowly add cornmeal. Blend thoroughly.
Add onion, corn, peppers and cheese.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan at 425° for 30 minutes (or until golden brown).

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
In skillet brown chicken in oil. Add onion, garlic, potatoes, pepper, salt, thyme and chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add green beans and simmer an additional 10 minutes or until done.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend first 2 ingredients well.
Beat eggs slightly and add to mixture.
Add baking soda, salt and flour.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Grease and flour large tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool and invert. Add last 4 ingredients.
Cook in saucepan to a full boil.
Beat and cool.
Spread on apple cake.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skin; cool, peel and shred coarsely.
Combine cheese and butter over low heat, stirring occasionally, until almost melted.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Fold in potatoes.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Boil undiluted soup and add softened cream cheese; stir until smooth and creamy.
Add gelatine and let thicken.
Add remaining ingredients; mix until blended and pour into greased mold.
Chill until set.
Remove from mold.
Serve on crackers and enjoy!

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator one hour before baking.
May cover top with buttered bread crumbs just before baking.
Bake one hour at 325° or 10 to 15 minutes longer is better.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: overnight cabbage salad
directions: Heat together vinegar, water and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Add seeds.
Shred cabbage; sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Toss with cooled dressing.
Let stand 24 hours.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Press into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat remaining 1/2 cup butter until softened.
Add powdered sugar; beat until fluffy. Beat in eggs.
Spread egg mixture over crumb mixture.
Slice bananas lengthwise into halves and arrange over egg mixture. Spoon pineapple over bananas.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chocolate and nuts (if desired).
Cover; refrigerate 4 hours before serving.
Cut into squares and top with a cherry.
Cover. Chill for storage.
Serves 15.

title: jelly roll
directions: Line 15x10x1 inch jelly roll pan with aluminum foil or waxed paper; grease generously.
Beat eggs in small bowl on high speed until very thick and lemon colored, about 5 minutes.
Pour eggs into large bowl.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Beat in water and vanilla on low speed.
Gradually add flour, baking powder and salt, beating just until batter is smooth.
Pour into pan.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat
eggs until frothy.
Beat in sugar, oil and vanilla until the
sugar is dissolved.
Sift together dry ingredients; toss
in nuts until individually coated.
Stir dry ingredients into
egg mixture
alternately with zucchini.
Mix gently, but thoroughly. Spoon
batter
into
to 12 greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 50 minutes to 1 hour or until cake springs back when lightly touched.

title: clergy pie
directions: Cream cheese and milk together.
Add pudding gradually; beat for 1 minute.
Pour into crust.
Chill.
Crushed pineapple may be added for variation.

title: 9 layer salad
directions: In Pyrex dish, layer the first 6 ingredients in order given. Cover with layer of mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Crumble bacon over top.
Let set for 1 to 2 hours.
Do not cook.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: company meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, eggs, bread crumbs, juice, onion and spices; mix together.
Spread hamburger mixture on top of a sheet of tinfoil; pat into a rectangle.
Place ham slices on meat mixture, then top with a second layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Use tinfoil to roll the meat loaf into a log.
Place in bread loaf pan and bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: spinach pie
directions: Saute onions in margarine in skillet.
Combine onion with spinach and seasonings in bowl, mixing well.
Spoon half the mixture into buttered pie plate.
Spread with cheddar cheese. Cover with remaining spinach mixture.
Spoon eggs over layers.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Bake 375 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream the sugars and shortening.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with pineapple.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until done.

title: italian breaded fillet of sole
directions: Lightly score fillets on skinned side.
Place fillets around outside of a 9 or 12-inch round microwave-safe dish.

title: apple pie (the best)
directions: Prepare crust for top and bottom.
Mix together sugar, cornstarch, Fruit-Fresh and cinnamon.
Pour over apples and mix gently.
Add lemon juice and put mixture into crust.
Drop margarine pieces on top.
Put on top crust and slit top crust. Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.

title: italian sausage nibbles
directions: Combine uncooked sausage with cheese, removing any casing. Knead to blend.
Add biscuit mix, fennel and oregano.
Mix well until a dough forms.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 1 inch apart on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 9 dozen.
May be frozen.
Thaw and reheat at 375° for 3 minutes.

title: zesty grilled potato wedges and zucchini
directions: Precook the potatoes and zucchini in microwave. Wedge potatoes with skins on. Wedge zucchini lengthwise.
Baste with the margarine.

Roll in a mixture of the seasoned salt, garlic powder, Accent and black pepper. Place on grill with meats about 15 to 20 minutes (depending on size) before end of cook time. Great served with Ranch dressing for dipping.

title: spice sour cream cake
directions: Cream fat and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 layer cake pans lined with waxed paper. Bake 20 minutes in moderate oven.
Frost with marshmallow frosting.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Combine jello and water.
Add pie filling and pineapple. Refrigerate.
Beat cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla well with mixer.
Spread on top of jello mixture.
Top with crushed nuts.

title: squash puppies
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoon into hot oil and brown.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix the day before and store in refrigerator.

title: 2-minute pie
directions: Mix instant pudding mix, sour cream and pineapple (with juice) in medium bowl.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Top with layer of whipped topping.
Cut and serve.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Place ground beef in Dutch oven.
Break up and add cold water to just cover.
Start cooking and break up meat with spatula until all meat is broken up fine.
Cover and cook at least 10 minutes. Add tomato soup and spices, stirring and making sure meat is broken up fine.
Simmer about 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a non metal container.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
There will be liquid.
Drain and use for salad dressing on other salads.
This needs no dressing.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs and blend.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pan, 13 x 9-inch.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
When cake is done, immediately cover top of cake with miniature marshmallows (or 1 jar of Marshmallow Cream).
Do not remove from pan.
Pour icing over cake after it is cool.

title: louisiana fried shrimp
directions: Remove heads and shells from shrimp, but leave fantail.
Split shrimp down back and remove vein.
Make a mixture of eggs, Carnation milk, baking powder and vinegar.
Marinate shrimp for at least 1 hour in this mixture.
Remove; season lightly with Creole seasoning.
Dip in flour.
Fry in 380° oil, not over 10 minutes. Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: split pea soup
directions: Add vegetables to the broth; when cooked done, I usually place the soup in blender, then I add chunks of meat.

title: raspberry peach tiramisu
directions: In food processor with knife blade attached, blend 2 cups raspberries, 3 tablespoons granulated sugar until pureed.
Pour puree into medium mesh sieve, set over bowl.
With spoon, press puree through sieve into bowl, discard seeds.
In clean food processor, process 1 1/4 cups whipping cream until soft peaks form.
Transfer whipping cream to large bowl.
In same processor, combine ricotta cheese, cream cheese, and confectioners sugar, add vanilla into food processor.
Blend cheese mixture until smooth. Add remaining 1/4 cup whipping cream, and blend until combined. Fold cheese mixture into cream in bowl.
In medium bowl, stir peaches, lemon, 1/4 cup granulated sugar until combined.
In cup, stir liqueur, remaining 1 tablespoon granulated sugar, and 1 tablespoon water until mixed.
Separate ladyfingers and brush lightly on flat sides with liqueur mixture.
In bottom of 4 quart truffle or straight sided glass bowl, arrange 1/3 of the ladyfingers.
Spoon half of raspberry sauce over ladyfingers.
Top with 1/3 cheese mixture, spreading to cover.
Spoon on half peach mixture.
Repeat layering once.
Top with remaining ladyfingers, then remaining cheese mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Before serving, sprinkle with remaining raspberries.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook and debone chicken breasts.
Cut in chunks and mix with sour cream and soup.
Put in baking dish.
Crush the crackers and mix with the Poppy seeds.
Put cracker mixture on top of chicken mix in pan, and drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° until thoroughly warm.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: mom's pudding and pie filling
directions: Heat milk while mixing other ingredients.
Beat egg well and combine with other ingredients and some of the warmed milk.
Pour into the warmed milk while on the heat and heat to boiling.
Add vanilla.
Use as pudding or pour into baked pie shell.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Slowly add sugar; beat.
Add oil and vanilla.
Add zucchini.
Sift dry ingredients; mix to previous ingredients.
Bake in 2 greased pans at 325° for 1 hour.
Check by putting knife through middle; if it comes out clean, it's done.

title: blueberry jello
directions: Mix; pour in pan and let set.

title: cream chicken
directions: Cook chicken. Cut into small pieces.
In saucepan melt butter. Add flour and milk.
Stir until thickens.
Add chicken.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Onion is optional. Serve over toast.

title: alabama chicken
directions: Saute oleo, bell pepper, celery, onion, pepper and salt. Boil spinach noodles
in
broth.
Chop cheese, olives, soup and mushrooms.
Mix all
ingredients.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover top with crushed Cheese Nips or additional cheese. Bake for 45 minutes at 300°.

title: scallop bake
directions: Wash scallops.
Chop mushrooms coarsely and mix with chopped parsley, crumbs, salt and pepper.

title: quick monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle pecans evenly in bottom of a well-greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Set aside.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll each piece in sugar mixture and layer in pan. Combine brown sugar and butter.
Pour over dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool bread 10 minutes in pan; invert onto serving platter.
Yield: One 10-inch coffee cake.

title: cheese soup
directions: In covered saucepan, cook carrot, onion and celery in butter over low heat until tender.
Stir in flour.
Add broth and salt. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in cream or milk and cheese until cheese melts and soup is heated through.
Do not boil.
Serve 4 to 6.

title: baked pineapple and cheese
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine sugar and flour; stir in reserved juice.
Add cheese and pineapple; mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Combine butter and cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot pasta salad
directions: Cut the ham in thin strips.
Place in large bowl with pecans, crumbled cheese, parsley, garlic, pepper, snipped rosemary and oil. Toss to mix.
Cover and set aside for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Pull chicken from bones and put in a baking dish.
Add Veg-All.
Heat the celery soup and two cans of the chicken water.
Pour this over the chicken and Veg-All.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Best when refrigerated for several hours.

title: overnight macaroons
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let stand overnight.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Let cool on sheets slightly, then remove.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine soup, water and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Add spaghetti, chicken, pepper and parsley.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.

title: hi-fiber applesauce
directions: Wash, core and quarter apples.
(Do not peel.)
Put in Dutch oven in water.
Cook, covered.
When partially cooked, add sugar (or artificial sweetener) and spices.
When done, process in food processor and seal in sterilized jars.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, oleo and cocoa.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Then add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until dissolved. Add oats.
Mix and drop onto a wax paper covered cookie sheet. Work fast; they set quickly.

title: sugar cookies(no roll)
directions: Stir together the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Sift together the remaining dry ingredients; gradually add to the creamed mixture.
Roll in balls; press down with a glass dipped in water, then in granulated sugar.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 6 to 8 minutes on a greased cookie sheet.

title: empanadas(meat pies)
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
When onion is transparent, add ground beef and cook until browned; drain.
Mix together ground beef mixture with chopped hard-boiled eggs, chopped olives and spices.
Cool.
Put meat mixture on 1/2 of pie round and fold over.
Crimp edges together.
Brush beaten egg over crust.
Bake in 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot or cold.

title: pork and sauerkraut
directions: Put pork in a large stew pan.
Cover with cold water.
Cook slowly for 1 hour.
Add sauerkraut, making sure there is enough liquid in the pan to cover.
Cook slowly for another hour.
Season to taste.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: To 3 egg whites beaten stiff add 1 cup sugar slowly, saltine crackers, baking powder and vanilla.
Fold together.
Pour in buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Top with ice cream or frozen fruit.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a casserole dish. Sprinkle crumbled crackers over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. This can be frozen.

title: peach pie
directions: Unroll 1 pkg. crescent rolls and put in bottom of 9 x 13 inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Flatten rolls to cover bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Mix 1 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Put on baked crust.
Add peach pie filling.
Unroll the other can of crescent rolls and add to top of pie filling.
Melt margarine and spoon evenly on top of rolls.
Mix 1/3 cup sugar with cinnamon and sprinkle on top.
Bake until top crust is brown.

title: coney island hot dog sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and minced onion.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix egg, sugar and milk, then add salt, baking powder and flour.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Cut butter into dry cake mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1/3 cup of mixture.
Press remainder into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, building up about 1/2-inch around sides.
Spoon in blueberry filling over crumb mixture.
Combine remaining mixture and pecans; sprinkle over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chipped beef ball
directions: Mix 2 packages chipped beef with other ingredients by hand. Make into 1 or 2 balls and roll into remaining package of chipped beef.

title: barbecue little wieners
directions: Cook on stove until hot.
Stir often. The longer it cooks, the better it will taste. Put toothpicks through each one and serve.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix first 3 items.
Put on bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour taco sauce on top of this.
Then add layer of chopped peppers, onions, black olives, shredded Cheddar cheese and shredded Monterey Jack cheese.
Top with chopped tomatoes.
Serve with nachos.

title: anne's beer batter
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Dip in fish. Deep fat fry in hot fryer.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cut up 5 cups raw rhubarb and place in cake pan. Sprinkle on 3 cups miniature marshmallows, 1 cup sugar and 1 box strawberry or raspberry jello. Mix yellow cake mix according to directions on box. Pour over rhubarb. Bake at 350° until done.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix and pour ingredients over chilled spinach.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Wash and dry berries.
Combine sugar and lemon juice in saucepan over medium-high heat.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.

title: baked chicken 'n rice
directions: Put cut up chicken in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours covered.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix dates in hot coffee and let stand until cool. Mix remaining ingredients into date mixture, mixing well.
Fold in nuts. Pour into 3 (1 pound) well-buttered coffee cans. Bake for 60 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix last 3 ingredients in a small bowl and pour into the large bowl.
Mix together.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.

title: big mac sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: spring vegetable soup
directions: Saute onions in butter about 2 minutes. Add potatoes and carrots and saute 2 minutes longer. Add 3 cups water and 1 teaspoon salt. Bring to a boil and simmer 12 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Add peas and cook 5 minutes longer. Add cream.
Heat gently and season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: sangria
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large container, stir and let sit for 18 - 24 hours.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring to a boil, stirring constantly for 2 minutes. Take from stove and add 1/2 cup peanut butter and 1 tablespoon of vanilla. Stir until peanut butter is melted.
Add 3 cups of oats and 1/2 cup nuts (if desired).
Cook on low heat until oats are soft. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly. Press into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour, or until meat is no longer pink.
Drain; let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat, onions and celery.
Drain off fat.
Combine rice, soup, seasoning and cabbage in skillet with meat.
Pour Ro-Tel tomatoes in blender, then add to meat mixture.
Pour into casserole dish and cover.
Bake at 350° until rice is tender or about 60 to 90 minutes.

title: sea bass stew
directions: In olive oil, saute onion, carrot and garlic.
When tender, add tomato.
Saute briefly.
Stir in clam juice and chicken broth; bring to simmer.
Add sea bass fillets, basil, thyme and other seasonings as desired.
Simmer until fish is done.
Float lemon slices on top of each serving.

title: bad byron's baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown bacon and ground beef in a large skillet until about half done.
Drain; add onion and bell pepper. Cook until onion and pepper are tender.
Add garlic and cook 2 to 3 minutes more.
Drain again and add all remaining ingredients. Stir together well and bake, uncovered, about an hour and 20 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Cook pudding according to directions, using milk.
Remove from heat; stir in margarine and cool to lukewarm, stirring occasionally.
Dissolve yeast in water and stir in pudding.
Beat in eggs and salt.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour and beat with mixer about 4 minutes.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough. Turn out onto floured board and knead 3 to 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; cover and let rise until doubles.
Punch down.
Roll dough into rectangle.
Brush with melted margarine; sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll up in jelly roll and seal edges.
Slice 1 1/2-inch slices.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Drizzle with glaze.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: 14 day cabbage salad
directions: Bring last 6 ingredients to boil and boil 1 minute.
Pour over cabbage mixture and let sit overnight.
Will keep 2 weeks.

title: frozen fruit cup
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into muffin tins lined with paper muffin cups.
Freeze until firm. Store in plastic bag. Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: tommy's frog legs a la creole
directions: Put frog legs in boiling water with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Scald for 4 minutes. Drain legs and pat dry.
Dip legs into eggs and roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in deep fat at 370° for 2 to 3 minutes, until legs are tender.
Serve with onion cream sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oven fried chicken(low-fat)
directions: Cover a baking sheet with wax paper and set aside.
Remove the skin and scrape off any visible fat from the chicken pieces.
In a large bowl, mix the flour, 1 tablespoon salt, black pepper and 2 teaspoons of the thyme.
Set aside.

title: caramel layer chocolate squares
directions: On top of stove or in microwave, combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Cook on low until melted and smooth.
Set aside. Generously grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cake mix, butter and remaining milk and nuts.
By hand, stir until dough holds together. Press 1/2 of the dough into pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle chips and nuts over baked crust.
Spread caramel mixture over chocolate chips and nuts.
Crumble reserved dough over caramel mixture.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate about 5 minutes, to set caramel layer.
Cut into squares.

title: deadly pecan pie
directions: Boil sugar and syrup together 2 or 3 minutes.
Beat eggs, not too stiff.
Pour slowly into hot syrup; add the butter, vanilla and pecan pieces.
Turn into raw pie crust and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until set.

title: spaghetti sauce italino
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and sausage; drain fat. Transfer to crock-pot.
Stir in rest of ingredients and cook on high heat setting for 5 to 6 hours.
Combine 2 tablespoons cold water and 2 tablespoons cornstarch; stir into tomato mixture. Cover, cook 10 more minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.
Cover with Parmesan cheese.

title: cocktail party ryes
directions: Brown, drain and cool meat.
Mix ingredients together and spread on buttered rye bread slices.
Place on foil lined cookie sheets and bake in hot oven until cheese is melted and starts to brown.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: "old fashioned" dumplings
directions: Put about a quart of water in a deep 2-quart pot.
Put flour and salt in bowl.
Beat egg well and add to flour with water or milk; beat well.
Add croutons to batter and mix well so bread is incorporated.
Drop in boiling water by tablespoon and stir carefully so dumplings rise to surface.
Tightly cover and boil 20 minutes.
When this starts boiling again, turn down flame to boiling over as the steam is important.

title: bombay chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch cubes.
Mix together chicken, water chestnuts and celery.
Blend together yogurt, mayonnaise, curry powder, soy sauce and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken mixture. Stir in grapes.
Chill several hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine and press into 10-inch tube pan.

title: oatmeal molasses cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening, sugar, eggs, molasses and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Let cool on sheet.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt. Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract.
Beat until creamy. Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture. Stir in chocolate morsels.
Place by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs together.
Take eggs out when hard boiled.
Completely cool down potatoes and dice into bowl.
Peel eggs and chop.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Chill.

title: easy taco dip
directions: Layer dip on small tray or platter, starting with bean dip and ending with cheese on top.

title: holiday punch
directions: Chill all ingredients.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: mountain dew punch
directions: Mash frozen orange juice in container.
Add drink.
Serves 18 to 20 people.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus reserving 1/8 cup liquid.
Mix milk, mushroom soup and liquid from asparagus together.
In buttered casserole, layer 1 can of asparagus, 1/2 of soup mixture, sliced egg, cheese, second can of asparagus and rest of soup mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Crumble potatoes chips and sprinkle on top of soup mixture.
Dot with margarine.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: quick party cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, eggs, fruit cocktail and baking soda together in a mixer for 1 minute.
Bake in an ungreased large oblong glass pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
(Can be metal pan.) Don't overbake; take from oven and add topping.

title: spice oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars until light.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
