Add sifted dry ingredients and oats in thirds with coffee, beating well after each addition.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and lightly flour Bundt pan. Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Beat until well blended.
Gradually add cake flour.
Mix until smooth.
Add 7-Up and flavor.
Mix well and pour into prepared pan.
Bake approximately 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: quick and easy cheesecake
directions: Combine in a blender the condensed milk, cream cheese, lemon juice and vanilla.
Blend until smooth and pour into pie shell. Arrange pie filling on top of cream cheese filling and cover. Refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: chicken breast casserole with stuffing
directions: Debone and remove skin from chicken.
Pound breasts.
Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place 4 chicken breasts (salted and peppered) on bottom of pan.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Boil the sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
To this mixture, add the cucumbers and onion.
Mix well.
Let stand 2 hours.
Put in containers and freeze.

title: easy microwave chicken casserole
directions: Microwave following Lipton directions.
Stir and microwave for 3 to 5 more minutes until veggies are done.
Ten minutes cooking and prep time!

title: hearty tuna casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine soup, milk, and 1/4 pound cubed Velveeta cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Stir in macaroni, peas, tuna, onion, pimento and seasonings.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with Velveeta slices.
Return to oven until Velveeta melts.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar; beat well.
Stir in flour, eggs and milk.
Beat well.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Pour into shell and bake at 350°.
Let cool before slicing.

title: easy chicken casserole(my favorite)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese and paprika, until well blended.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Garnish with cheese and paprika during the last 10 minutes of baking time.

title: old-fashioned fruit dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients except the whipping cream in a small saucepan.
Heat just to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool.
In a chilled bowl, beat the cream until stiff.
Fold in the egg mixture.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Cook and cut up chicken breasts into bite-size pieces.
Melt oleo; add onion, celery and celery tops.
Then add to bread, broth, mushroom soup, eggs, pepper, salt, poultry seasoning and sage.
Mix all ingredients together except chicken.
Layer chicken and dressing in crock-pot.
Cook 1 hour on high, then scrape loose from sides (do not stir).
Then cook on low 4 hours.

title: chicken breasts with cheese sauce
directions: Lay chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place thin slices of onion over the chicken.
Melt together the remaining ingredients and pour over the chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, covered.

title: hamburger chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger; pour off excessive fat.
Add onions, celery and green peppers.
In another pan, heat the Chinese vegetables. Use cornstarch to thicken juice of Chinese vegetables.
Combine the two mixtures.
Boil rice.
When done, serve with the hamburger mixture on top.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix ingredients together; place in a 9 x 9-inch pan and chill overnight.
Serves 9 generously.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Mix all and pour into unbaked pie shell and bake approximately 35 minutes or until firm in center in 350° oven.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Also may use Worcestershire sauce with lemon juice.

title: cheesy mushroom broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix eggs, flour, salt and pepper.
Stir broccoli, cheese, cottage cheese and mushrooms. Bake, covered, 1/2 hour or until almost set in center at 350°. (Can take 45 minutes.)

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix and spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan, ungreased.

title: mrs. wood's secret chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine first 4 ingredients in a pie plate and press over bottom and sides to form a crust.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool. Melt chocolates together over very low heat. Add 1/2 cup milk and sugar and let come to a boil.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix in pineapple and bread.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased shallow casserole.

title: gourmet carrots
directions: Place carrots in a buttered casserole.
Mix together all the ingredients except the bacon and add to carrots.
Crumble the bacon and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: glaze for strawberry pie
directions: Bring to a boil: 1 cup water, sugar and salt.
In a small bowl, mix cornstarch and remaining
water.
Stir into water/sugar mixture and cook until clear.
At once, remove from heat and add Jell-O powder and then lemon juice.
Cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients and pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix the cream cheese with milk and sugar.
Beat until creamy. Spread in pie crust.
Top with 1 cup chopped pecans.
Mix package of Dream Whip as directed and spread on top of nuts.
Top with one can cherry pie filling.
Chill at least 5 hours.

title: best-ever lemon pie
directions: Combine and stir over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickens and boils.
Put in baked pie shell.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots, green
pepper and onion over low heat until tender.
Put in casserole dish.
Combine all other ingredients. Pour over vegetable mixture and cook in 350 degree oven until warmed through.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and pudding mix. Add oil, water and poppy seeds. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well with electric mixer at medium speed. Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool for 15 minutes before turning out.

title: poor man's perogies
directions: Saute cabbage and onion until golden and clear.
Place 1/3 cabbage mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan and add 3 noodles.
Repeat previous 2 layers.
Layer potatoes, then cheese, then noodles, then cabbage.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered with foil.
Bake 15 more minutes, uncovered.
Let set before cutting.

title: paradise candy
directions: Line a cookie sheet with tinfoil.
Line saltine crackers in rows on foil.
Melt together 2 sticks butter and 1 cup sugar. Boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla to the above.
Pour mixture on crackers.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Sprinkle on 12 ounces chocolate chips.
Return to oven for 1 minute to melt chocolate.
Spread chocolate with a knife.
Add nuts; refrigerate for 2 hours.
Break into pieces.

title: farango mints
directions: Cream butter and sugar together, then add eggs and beat well. Add melted chips and vanilla until mixture is smooth.
Add extract and mix well.
Put in a 9 x 8-inch pan that has been lined with waxed paper.
Chill.
Store in refrigerator or freezer (or you can cut in small squares and wrap each separately in Saran Wrap).

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Melt butter in saucepan; add sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture gradually, mixing well.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan; cut into bars.
Makes 48.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt the can of soup, mayonnaise and egg.
Set aside.
Melt butter in a pan.
Add bread crumbs or stuffing mix.
Set aside. Butter casserole dish.
Layer 1/2 the broccoli, 1/2 the soup mixture and 1/2 the cheese.
Repeat layers and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: supreme chicken salad
directions: Combine diced chicken, pineapple, onion, celery, 3/4 cup almonds, bean sprouts and water chestnuts.

title: red cross fudge
directions: In large pan, mix sugar, milk and oleo.
Bring to boil and boil 11 minutes on medium heat.
Stir constantly.
Remove from fire and add marshmallows, nuts and chocolate chips.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: chicken-asparagus or chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Arrange asparagus or broccoli in a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish and set aside.
Salt, pepper and paprika chicken breasts after cutting into strips or nuggets.
Dredge chicken in flour.
Fry chicken in oil until almost done, not all the way. After frying, layer chicken on top of vegetables.
Mix soup, whipping cream, pimentos, milk and chili powder together.
Pour over vegetables and chicken.
Bake uncovered 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve over rice with salad and/or bread for a complete meal.
Wonderful!
My family's favorite.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Combine bran flakes and boiling water in medium bowl and set aside to cool.
Combine whole-bran cereal and buttermilk in medium bowl and set aside.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt on wax paper.
Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy in large bowl. Beat in eggs and molasses.
Stir in bran flake mixture and alternate with flour mixture until evenly moist.
Stir in buttermilk mixture.
Spoon batter into 1 or more refrigerator containers and cover tightly.
Store in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.
Preheat oven to 375° and bake 18 to 20 minutes when ready to use.

title: sweet gherkins
directions: First
Day:
Morning - Wash cucumbers thoroughly; scrub with vegetable
brush.
Stem
ends may be left on if desired. Drain cucumbers;	place
in
a large container and cover with boiling water.
Afternoon (6 to 8 hours later):
Drain; cover with fresh, boiling water.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all together and let set up.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Boil and heat peas, then drain.
Add onions and stir.
Add the rest of ingredients and stir.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: bacon dressing
directions: Cook bacon and onion together.
Brown bacon until crisp.
Add sugar, vinegar and water and heat thoroughly.
Allow mixture to cool.
Add salad dressing and store covered in refrigerator.
Use on watercress, spinach or lettuce.
Delicious served warm.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir pudding and milk together in bowl until very thick.
Add ice cream to pudding.
Spread mixture over cracker crust.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding and sprinkle crushed Heath bars on top.
Store in freezer.
Allow to soften a bit before serving.

title: tropical salad
directions: Drain pineapple, oranges and cherries. Cut fruit into small pieces. Mix fruit, coconut and marshmallows well. Sprinkle sugar over mixture. Stir in cream. Mix well. Pour into dish. Refrigerate. Let set overnight.

title: special seafood casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients but chips and spoon into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Top with chips.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 12 servings (sure, if a serving is for a midget!).

title: scalloped salmon
directions: Drain and flake salmon; save liquid.
Blend lemon juice and onion into salmon.
Combine cracker crumbs, salt, pepper and butter.
Sprinkle 1/2 of this mixture into a well-greased Pyrex dish; cover with a layer of salmon and repeat layers, ending with crumbs.
Pour heated liquid over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until brown.
Serve plain or with a sauce.
Serves six.

title: yummy swiss cheese and olive appetizer
directions: Broil or microwave bacon.
Mix in order above.
Spread on rye bread.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes or until lightly browned, before serving.

title: avocado dip
directions: Layer all ingredients in order listed. Sprinkle sliced green onions on top for color. Serve with chips.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 25 minutes in 375° oven.

title: holly taters
directions: Wash potatoes thoroughly.
Cut lengthwise into wedges. Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Shake potatoes in this mixture and lay in a baking dish.
Pour butter over the potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, turning over after 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Debone and cut into bite-size pieces.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream. Spread over chicken.
Sprinkle Ritz crackers over casserole.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: amish-style chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles and drain.

title: corn chowder with fresh herbs and smoked ham
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine broth, onion and carrot.
Tie together bay leaf and fresh herbs to make bouquet garni.
Add to saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Remove herbs.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Cook beef and onion until slightly browned.
Drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in ketchup and tomato sauce.
Heat thoroughly. Turn into 8-inch square pan or 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cut cheese into thin strips.
Sprinkle over meat.
Top with biscuits. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: kahlua
directions: Bring sugar, water and instant coffee to a boil; cool.
Add vanilla and vodka.
Must stand 72 hours before using.

title: frozen caramel delite
directions: Combine flour, butter, sugar, salt, oats and chopped pecans and form into a dough. Pat dough on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool. Crumble 1/2 of the cooked dough into a 9 x 13 pan; drizzle the jar of caramel sauce over this. Slice softened ice cream; lay on crust. Crumble remaining 1/2 of dough over ice cream. Freeze 8 hours before serving.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, spices and dash of salt.
Mix with peeled, sliced apple.
Fill pie shell with apple mixture.
Dot with butter.
Cover pie with another pie shell and crimp edges together.
Cut slits in top.
Brush pie top with milk.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.
Place pie on inverted iron skillet in a 400° oven and bake for 50 minutes.
(This will make a crisp bottom crust.)

title: holiday green salad
directions: Dissolve the first 5 ingredients over medium heat, then cool. Add the remaining ingredients; mix together.
Pour into mold. Chill overnight.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add corn, butter and sour cream.
Fold in muffin mix, salt and pepper.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or when toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: hearty beef goulash soup
directions: Cut the potatoes into 1/4 inch dices.
Coarsely chop the onion. In a large saucepan, warm the oil over medium-high heat until hot, not smoking.
Add onion and garlic and saute until onion is just translucent, 1 to 2 minutes.
Crumble ground beef into pan and cook, breaking meat up with a spoon, until meat just begins to brown, 5 to 10 minutes.
Add tomato juice, beef broth, paprika, black pepper and potatoes.
Bring mixture to a boil, reduce heat to medium-low.
Cover and simmer, stirring often, for 10 minutes.
Cut bell peppers in 1/4 inch dices.
Stir in peppers and cook until potatoes are tender, about 10 minutes.

title: kari's peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine and mix with peanut butter.
Add powdered sugar. Roll into small balls and chill.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax in top of double boiler.
Using toothpicks, dip each chilled ball in the chocolate and set on wax paper.
Be sure to use good brand of peanut butter and real chocolate chips.
This recipe freezes well and is one of our favorites at Christmas.

title: ann's pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, and continue beating. After all eggs are in, beat for 5 minutes. Gradually add flour and continue to beat. Add vanilla last.
Melt chocolate and add to 1/3 of the batter, alternating white and chocolate batters.
Zigzag with a knife.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and floured for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: spiced cabbage
directions: Put all in slow cooker.
Add a little juice and cook overnight.

title: nan's swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Mix salt and pepper with flour.
Brown steak (do not fry).
Cook just long enough to brown both sides.
Drain steak on paper towel.
Mix soup with 2 cans of water in baking dish or roaster.
Add steak.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: homemade sour cream
directions: Mix well in blender on high.
This is low in fat.

title: butter icing for sugar cookies
directions: Beat all ingredients well.
Consistency is improved by thoroughly beating.
For thinner icing, add more egg white; for thicker icing, add more sugar.
Keep bowl covered with damp towel.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Mix together in a pitcher to use later at the table.

title: nachos
directions: Spread each tortilla chip with bean dip.
Top with cheese. Place chips on a paper plate.
Cook uncovered 1 to 1 1/2 minutes at Power Level 6 or until cheese is melted.

title: dessert
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter in microwave until smooth.
Pour over corn flakes and spoon onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream
together.
Roll
in ball, mash and roll in sugar and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: In medium saucepan, combine all ingredients except wine. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove spices.
Add wine; heat through.
Serve warm; garnish as desired.

title: pizzelle
directions: Mix well.
Use 1/4 cup for each cookie.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Mix Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs together.
Flatten chicken.
Place ham and cheese on top of chicken and roll.
Tie with thread.
(Trim off excess ham and cheese.)
Roll in melted margarine.
Roll in Parmesan cheese and bread crumb mixture. Bake in baking dish for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken tostilla casserole
directions: Mix soups, milk, chilies, onion and chicken together.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange in layers, Doritos, soup mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: pineapple cheese balls
directions: Drain pineapple and pat several times with paper towels until excess liquid is gone.
Cream together cream cheese and pineapple. Add finely chopped green pepper and onion.
Stir in seasoning salt and one cup of chopped nuts.

title: salami spread
directions: Grind all in a food chopper. Refrigerate. Eat on any type crackers or chips.

title: chili pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare muffin mix by package directions.
Spread batter evenly over greased 9-inch pan.
Bake 18 minutes until brown.
Prepare beef and taco seasoning; spoon over cornbread.
Sprinkle with about half of the cheese.
Arrange the tomatoes and remaining cheese on top of the pie.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix the cream cheese, beef and dressing.
Roll into 2 balls. Roll in nuts.
Freezes well.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Lightly grease non Teflon pans.
Cream shortening, butter, eggs, sugar, milk, molasses, fruit and oats.
Add flour, soda, spices and nuts.
Press flat with palm of hand.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Bake a little longer for crisper cookie.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Place the water in a large bowl.
To dissolve yeast, add it and the 1 tsp sugar to the water and let stand for 5 minutes.
Add dry milk, butter, honey, sugar, salt, eggs and 2 cups of flour. Blend together on low speed, then beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Add the rest of the flour to make a soft dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic with bread hooks or by hand, 5-10 minutes. Place in a greased bowl, cover and let rise in a warm place until it doubles in bulk.
Punch down.

Take half the dough and roll it into a 9x12 inch rectangle about 1/4 inch thick. Spread with half of the cinnamon sugar filling (recipe to follow). Roll up like a jelly roll, starting with 12 inch side.
Cut into 1 inch slices and place on greased cookie sheets.
Cover with a towel.
Repeat process with the other half of the dough.
Let the rolls rise until they double in bulk in a warm place.
Bake at 375° for 12-15 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from baking sheets to cooling racks.
Dribble glaze (recipe to follow) over top of the warm rolls.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix together and take
half of mixture and roll between wax paper.
Place in pie plate	and
bake
at 350° until light brown. Makes 2 pie crusts.

title: cajun-style sweet potatoes
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan over high heat, bring potatoes and enough water to cover to a boil.
Reduce heat, simmer, covered, for 10 minutes until just tender.
Drain.
In a 12-inch pan over medium heat, melt butter.
Add potatoes, pecans, brown sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Cook about 5 minutes, stirring frequently, until sugar is melted and potatoes are tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese with peanut butter.
Slowly add powdered sugar and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust. Sprinkle with nuts.
Freeze at least 4 hours.

title: scandinavian salad
directions: Drain and mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add the green pepper, celery and onion.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Mix with the first mixture; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Keeps 1 week or more. Serves 6 to 10.

title: foil roasted corn-on-the-cob
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Husk the corn and wrap each ear in foil, adding 2 teaspoons of butter to each packet.
Bake for about 25 minutes or roast the foil-wrapped corn over hot coals, turning once during the cooking.

title: oven made caramel corn
directions: Combine popped corn, roasted peanuts and pecans in large roasting pan.
Melt the butter in a large pan; stir in the sugars, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes, stirring often (244°).
Remove from heat; and stir in soda.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix butter, shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and the eggs.
Blend in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.

title: fruit salad pie
directions: This makes 2 (9-inch) pies.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: pasta and vegetables
directions: Cook up onion in olive oil until it's transparent.
Saute onion and diced eggplant until soft.
Add other ingredients and cook about 20 minutes.
Cook pasta.
Add the vegetables to pasta; toss.
Serve hot.

title: onion noodle pie
directions: Cook onions in olive oil until dark brown and crispy.
Add and mix rest of ingredients except paprika.
Pour into pie plate. Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Noodles should be crispy on top.

title: bret's hamburger helpless
directions: Brown hamburger in large skillet.
Add corn and beans.
Serves 6.

title: puddin' head gingerbread men
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar and pudding mix.
Add egg; beat well. Combine flour, baking soda, ginger and cinnamon. Stir into cream mixture.
Chill.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown meat until done.
Drain grease.
Add taco or picante sauce and Mexene to taste.
Add corn; simmer until warm.
Put mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle corn bread mix over top.
Take 2 cups of water and hand dip over top.
Bake until top is brown.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Shred zucchini and set aside.
Cream sugar, butter and eggs. Mix all dry ingredients together and gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in zucchini, nuts and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans or several small individual pans.
Fill and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, until a toothpick inserted is clean.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Boil lasagna noodles. In separate bowl, mix cottage cheese with egg.

title: "best ever" persimmon pudding
directions: Mix
persimmons,
eggs, sugar, oil and both flavorings. Beat well
with	mixer.	Add
2 cups milk and beat. Add 2 cups flour and
beat.	Add
2	cups flour and beat, then add 2 cups milk and beat slowly.
Pour into 3 greased long baking dishes. Bake at 250° for 2 hours.
This can be halved.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, eggs, milk, 1/2 cup oleo and vanilla. Beat until smooth.

title: strawberry spinach salad with strawberry-poppy seed dressing
directions: Arrange spinach leaves on salad plates.
Wash strawberries; set aside to dry.
Peel eggs and separate whites from yolks.
Chop whites and sprinkle over spinach, distributing equally between plates.
Crush yolks with a fork or your hand; sprinkle over spinach and egg whites.
Reserve 1 strawberry per salad plate for garnish.
Stem, hull and slice remaining strawberries over spinach and egg.
Crumble bacon on top of salads.
Garnish with croutons and a whole strawberry.
Drizzle with Strawberry-Poppy Seed Dressing (recipe to follow).
Serve immediately.

title: old virginia applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Add beaten egg and applesauce.
Sift flour before measuring.
Use a little of the same flour to sift over the raisins and nuts.
Sift remaining flour with salt and spices.
Dissolve soda in boiling water, then add flour mixture alternately with the water to the creamed mixture.
Add the floured raisins and nuts.
Pour into cake tin or bake in mold, greased and floured.
Bake one hour in a moderate oven at 350°.

title: lo-lo chili
directions: Coat a Dutch oven with cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add ground beef; cook until browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain and pat dry with paper towels.
Wipe drippings from Dutch oven.
Recoat Dutch oven with cooking spray.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until tender.
Add ground beef and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Yields 9 servings (278 calories, 7 g fat).

title: taco salad
directions: Cook beef and drain off excess grease. Cool.
Mix in taco seasoning and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together. Serve with regular dressing, mild taco sauce or salsa.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Take pie
crusts
and sprinkle chocolate chips and some nuts in the
bottom of crusts.
Beat eggs (slightly).
To this add sugar, syrup and margarine.
Pour over chocolate chips and nuts. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Combine milk and oats in bowl and let stand at least 5 minutes.
Add the oil and beaten eggs, mixing well.
Stir in the flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix just until the dry ingredients are moistened.
Bake on hot griddle, lightly oiled.
Use 1/4 cup of batter for each pancake.
Turn when top is bubbly and the edges are slightly dry.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Put on top of pudding and bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In large pot, brown meat in oil; add enough water to cover. Add tomatoes; simmer, covered, 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Add vegetables and seasonings.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Grease a large, Pyrex dish with margarine.
In one bowl, crush Ritz.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, pecans and vanilla.
In second bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/2 cup sugar; beat until stiff. Combine 2 bowls and blend.
Pour in greased dish and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Add whipped cream.
Top with grated chocolate.
Chill.

title: chili
directions: Chop onion and saute.
Brown ground beef (drain).
Mix all ingredients together and simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Season with salt, pepper, sugar and chili powder to taste.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: Cook the cranberries in water until soft.
Add sugar; cook 5 minutes.
Pour boiling mixture over package of red Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill and when partially congealed, add chopped celery, salt and nuts.
Pour into mold.

title: tina's sausage quiche
directions: Cook spinach.
Brown meat and onion.
Blend in other ingredients, adding mead and onion last.
Pour into pie shells. Bake at 325° for 40 - 50 minutes.

title: piselli al prosciutto(peas with italian ham)
directions: Put olive oil in a heavy saucepan.
Add medium thinly sliced onion.
Cook until golden color.
Add peas; cook at medium heat until peas are firm.
Do not overcook.
Add ham and/or mushrooms. Cook another 3 to 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with minced parsley leaves, if desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: viennese crescents(from "jane brody's good food gourmet")
directions: In a medium-sized bowl, beat together butter and sugar until fluffy and well blended.
Add the vanilla and almond extracts and mix well.
Add the milk and blend for a few minutes (the milk won't go into the mixture completely).
Gradually add the flour, a little at a time, mixing well.
It's okay for the dough to be a little crumbly by the time you've added all the flour.
Add the ground almonds and mix as well as possible (break up the dough and distribute the almonds throughout).

title: frosted carrot and zucchini bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, baking powder, ginger and baking soda.
In another bowl, stir together eggs, carrots, zucchini, raisins, nuts oil, honey and vanilla.
Stir carrot mixture into flour mixture, mixing just until combined.
Spread in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes or until toothpick comes clean.
Cool on wire rack.

title: sour cream marinade(2 pounds of meat)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate meat overnight in refrigerator. Great for poultry and beef!

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Combine chicken broth, clams, carrots, potatoes, parsley, celery and onion in a large saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Combine butter and flour; blend well. Gradually add milk, stirring well, until blended.
Place over low heat and cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened. Add to vegetable mixture, stirring well.
Add salt and pepper. Serve hot.

title: eggplant dip
directions: Chop finely the eggplant, onions, green pepper, garlic and parsley.
Heat olive oil in large skillet.
Add vegetables and saute over medium heat until they are translucent.
Stir occasionally to keep vegetables from sticking.
Lower heat and cook until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill and store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Serve with sesame wafers. Makes 1 quart.

title: layer salad
directions: In 9 x 12-inch cake pan, layer ingredients.

title: elegant scalloped corn
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir in eggs, milk and butter, mixing well.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes.
Garnish with parsley and pepper rings.

title: old fashioned cream pie
directions: Heat half and half.
Mix flour, cornstarch and salt in 1 cup cold milk.
Add to half and half mixture, then add 1/2 cup butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon on top and let cool.

title: chicken strips
directions: Wash chicken; cut into strips.
Sprinkle salt over strips. Beat eggs; add to buttermilk and salt.
Pour over chicken.
Place in refrigerator for about 30 minutes, if possible.
If you don't have time, it is okay to go immediately to frying.
Take strips out of milk mixture, one at a time, and roll in flour.
Drop into greased (a deep fryer) and cook until brown.
Take out of grease and put on plate with paper towel to drain any excess grease.

title: lulu's date and nut cake
directions: Add boiling water to dates and soda and let stand.
Mix all except date mixture, then add dates.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: 5-hour stew
directions: Place all ingredients in large roaster.
Stir and cover.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: blueberry angel food cake
directions: Buy a store bought angel food cake and slice it straight across into 3 layers. Mix together with a beater the cream cheese, sugar and Dream Whip (make it up with beater, with cold milk). Mix these ingredients together until smooth.
Put between the layers of the cake, down the middle and around the sides and top. Put a can of blueberry pie filling all over the cake. Refrigerate.

title: cheese danish
directions: Combine cream cheese, egg yolks, 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla in a bowl.
Mix with electric mixer on high speed until creamy, about 3 minutes; set aside.

title: christmas present soup mix
directions: Mix beans; divide
evenly among 8 to 10 pint jars (with lids). Leave
3/4-inch
space at top.
Combine other ingredients and divide evenly among jars.

title: sad pan cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes or until cake falls.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Break up sponge cake and cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan with pieces.
Mix vanilla instant pudding with cold milk.
Add ice cream.
Pour over cake pieces.
Dissolve strawberry Jell-O in hot water; add frozen strawberries.
Pour over pudding. Refrigerate.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix eggs, oil and sugars well.
Combine all other ingredients; mix well.
Put in 3 greased loaf pans. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: diabetic applesauce cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until all liquid evaporates.
Add applesauce, eggs, Sweet 'N Low and oil and mix well.
Blend in baking soda and flour.
Add vanilla and cinnamon.
Mix well and pour into greased cake pan or muffin pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 35 minutes (muffins 25 minutes).

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soup, green chiles, sour cream and heat until smooth. Set aside.
Mix chicken, salt, garlic powder, cumin, 2 cups grated Monterrey Jack cheese and onion.
Set aside.
Put a small amount of sauce in the bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or shallow baking dish.
Put a spoonful of filling on each tortillas and top with 1 tablespoon of sauce.
Roll up tortillas and arrange in dish. Cover with remaining sauce and a layer of grated cheese.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and Ranch dressing, until smooth.
Drain and rinse shrimp.
Mix shrimp and all ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: a friend's stew
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper; sprinkle with chili powder (as salt).
Drop meat in bag with 1/2 cup flour and shake to coat all sides.
In large skillet with a lid, heat 1/2-inch oil.
Add meat and brown all pieces.
Remove meat and drain well.
Drain oil from pan; replace meat in pan.
Add vegetables, cut in pieces. Add hot water to barely cover; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Feel free to add onions, celery or whatever to this stew!

title: easy peppermint crunch candy
directions: In food processor, chop peppermint until it is the texture of large grains of sand.
Take out any large pieces.
Melt white chocolate in microwave according to instructions.
When completely melted, stir in peppermint to taste (1 1/2 parts peppermint to 3 parts chocolate).
Put immediately into Christmas candy molds and put in refrigerator until hard.
Or, spread candy 1/8-inch thick on waxed paper, put in refrigerator until hard, then break into pieces.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute onions and butter.
Set aside.
Mix together green beans, mushroom soup, mushroom pieces, almond slices and salt. Pour onion/butter into this mixture and stir well.
Put in casserole dish and top with cheese slices.
(You can break into strips.)
Bake in oven at 350° until bubbling.
Add Durkee onion rings and brown.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch dish or pan with nonstick spray.
Line bottom of casserole with Cheddar cheese.
Brown the ground beef and pour Ragu sauce into the beef.
Pour over cheese layer with Mozzarella cheese.
Top with dinner rolls (spread out).
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: crana frosty
directions: Combine cranberry juice, orange juice, ice cubes and 1/2 cup of sliced bananas in a blender container.
Process until smooth.
Pour mixture into small cups and top with remaining banana slices. Makes 6 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: baked squash
directions: Mix together squash and onion and boil for 5 minutes.
Drain in colander.
Mix sour cream and chicken soup with squash.
Melt butter or oleo.
Pour over Stove Top dressing; mix well.
Put 2/3 cup in bottom of casserole; add the first mixture, then cover with remaining stuffing.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Slice each potato in half lengthwise; scoop out centers to form a shell.
Mash potatoes and add 1 cup of cheese, milk, margarine and seasonings.
Beat until fluffy.
Stir in 1 tablespoon of chives and half of bacon; fill shells.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Toss remaining cheese, chives and bacon together and sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake 10 more minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crab-ease
directions: Let butter and cheese spread soften to room temperature.
Mix together with mayonnaise, garlic salt and seasoned salt.
Add crab meat.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, Veg-All, English peas, soups and onion.
Pour into casserole dish.
Mix flour, mayonnaise and milk together for top crust.
Pour over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot fruit toddy
directions: Combine and heat gently to simmer.
Do not boil.

title: minestrone in minutes
directions: Combine ingredients and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Great with Jiffy cornbread mix. Has 260 calories per cup.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and brown sugar together until creamy. Add vanilla and eggs.
Sift together flour, baking soda and instant pudding; add gradually.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Batter will be quite stiff.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Cook fryer in boiling water; take meat off bone and add celery, onion, a little butter, garlic, soups, 3 cups of broth from chicken, Ro-Tel tomatoes and tortillas.
Top with grated cheese.
Put in baking dish a layer of meat and a layer of tortilla strips.
Pour over the the liquids and mix with sauteed celery, onion and tomatoes (garlic optional).
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: party sandwiches
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix well with other ingredients.

title: filipino style black cod
directions: Season the frozen fish steaks lightly with salt and pepper. Place in a large saucepan with oil.
Place a layer of sliced onion, followed by a layer of tomato wedges.
Cover and simmer mixture over medium heat.
Readjust seasoning just before serving.

title: hot quesadillas
directions: Sprinkle ingredients on 1 flour tortilla and cover with another tortilla.
Place in microwave or conventional oven until the cheese melts.
Cut the quesadilla into quarters.
May be served with lettuce, tomato, sour cream or guacamole.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn.
Mix all ingredients.
Chill and serve.
Can be stored in refrigerator for several days.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, 1 egg and margarine and pat into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Cream together cream cheese, 2 eggs and confectioners sugar and pour on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add 1 egg and beat.
Add flour, soda, salt, juice, rind and sour milk.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Lemon juice and rind can be substituted.
Add juice and rind to frosting also.

title: red lobster copy-cat biscuits
directions: In a large bowl toss together baking mix and cheese until well mixed.
Add milk, stirring until soft dough forms.
Drop dough by heaping tablespoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 450° oven 8 to 10 minutes.
Melt butter and stir in garlic powder.
Brush over warm biscuits before removing from baking sheet.

title: zucchini squash nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs well.
Add zucchini to the mixture. Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients, a small amount at a time, to zucchini mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts and raisins by hand after all other ingredients are mixed together.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Pull out stems of mushrooms after washing.
Chop stems and mix with sausage; stuff into mushroom tops.
Cook 20 minutes, or until brown in 350 degree oven.
Mushrooms will turn dark during cooking.

title: chicken wings
directions: Combine sugars, juice and soy sauce. Mix well. Using large bowl pour mixture over wingettes. Marinate 8 hours, overnight. Bake in shallow pan at 350° for 50 mon.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Layer mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: 40-minute rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast, sugar, milk and warm water.
Add shortening, salt and flour.
Let set 20 minutes.
Flour board; work mixture until firm.
Form into rolls or loaf.
Let set 20 minutes, then put in oven and bake until done or brown on top.

title: beef and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Slice beef very thin in bite size strips.
Add cooking oil to preheated hot wok (high heat).
Stir-fry broccoli, carrots and onion in hot oil for 2 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Remove from wok.
Add more oil, if necessary, before stir-frying the beef strips (fry only 1/2 of the portion of beef strips at a time) in hot oil (high heat) for 2 to 3 minutes.
Return all meat to wok. Add peas, water chestnuts and bamboo shoots.

title: chow mein chicken casserole
directions: Mix all above ingredients together.
Place in baking dish and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.

title: chili warms the heart
directions: Brown the beef in a large frypan.
Drain.
Add onion and garlic and cook until tender.
Stir in chili powder and seasonings.
Add tomatoes with juice and tomato sauce.
Simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Rinse the beans and add to the chili. Cook 10 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mama's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa well. Add egg yolks and milk.
Cook until thick, stirring frequently.
Pour into cooked crusts.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: cottage cheese pancakes
directions: Mix in blender and spoon onto a medium-hot frying pan (Teflon or other nonstick pan gives a beautiful even color).
Cook until golden.
Keep warm and serve with berries or fruit with cottage cheese or yogurt.

title: fresh fruit pie(peach)
directions: Mix peaches, flour and 1/3 cup sugar together real good.
Put in small buttered baking dish.
Remove crust from bread slices and cut in 3 strips. Place on top of peaches; press down and seal sides.
Mix 1 cup sugar, egg and melted margarine; pour on top of bread. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: brussels sprouts coleslaw
directions: Put all ingredients into a bowl and mix well together.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour before serving.

title: oatmeal fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in a saucepan.
Add milk and butter. Bring to a boil and cook for 2 minutes and 30 seconds.
Remove from heat and stir in the peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: shoepeg corn
directions: Mix together in microwavable dish and heat until warm through and through.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat the margarine in a saucepan and add the onion.
Cook slowly until softened.
Add flour and cook to a pale golden color. Stir in broth and bring to a boil.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Combine with chicken and vegetables.
Add parsley and sage.
Mix and spoon into a casserole dish.

title: cheese ball 1
directions: Soften all the cheeses.
Mix by hand.
Add onions and Worcestershire sauce; then roll into the size you want.
Roll them in chopped pecans.
Another option is to place the cheese mixture into a bowl or cup for serving with.
If the cheese is too hard to mix, then add a little bit of milk; that will soften it up some.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer kraut and noodles, then onion and corned beef.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and mustard.
Pour over meat.
Sprinkle cheese over soup mixture, then cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: happy days slaw
directions: Mix and toss all ingredients.

title: diet crustless cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into deep pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cabbage cacciatore
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Put 1/2 cabbage in bottom of pan, then rice, hamburg, remaining cabbage and onion.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Pour spaghetti sauce over top.
Cover tightly and bake for 1 1/2 hours or longer.
Remove cover and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Return to oven until cheese is melted at 350°.

title: orange glazed pecans
directions: Cook sugar and orange juice for about 3 minutes.
Add orange rind and pecans and stir until pecans are well coated.
Spread out on foil.
Break apart when hardened.

title: play dough
directions: Mix together in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat for 1 to 2 minutes until gooey.
Turn onto bread board and knead color in.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Cream the butter and brown sugar well.
Blend in and mix thoroughly the corn syrup and vanilla.
Add eggs and pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 25 minutes more.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, granulated sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa and salt.
Add milk, vanilla and oil.
Mix until smooth, pour into greased 8 x 8 1/2-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over entire batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine ingredients in medium bowl.
Blend with mixer until smooth.
Serve with fresh fruit as a dip; bananas, oranges, apples, pineapple, strawberries, kiwi fruit.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix together the sugar, oil, salt, vinegar, pepper and mustard; bring to a boil.
Pour over carrot mixture and marinate.

title: dorothy's easy time squares
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each addition. Add lemon juice; then mix in flour gradually and well.
Pour into greased jellyroll pan.
Mark batter into 24 squares and place some filling in each square.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove. When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar after you've cut into 24 squares.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut skirt steak into bite-size strips.
Put in roasting pan. Add enough water to fill 1/2 pan.
Place in 400° oven until brown. Remove and drain off water.
Set aside.
Cut up peppers, onions and saute in frying pan (crisp not soft).
In roasting pan, surround meat with cooked peppers and onions.
Add soy sauce, cream sherry, garlic and onion powder and pepper to taste.
Return to oven and cook at 400°
until meat is cooked.
Serve over rice 20 to 30 minutes.

title: raisin bars
directions: Put boiling water in mixing bowl.
Add golden raisins and cooking oil.
Let this cool.
Add egg, sugar, flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and chopped nuts.
Bake in buttered and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into balls; roll in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Arrange carrots in ungreased 7 x 11 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer cauliflowerets over carrots.
Pat with butter and sprinkle with salt and nutmeg.
Cover and bake until vegetables are tender, about 50 to 55 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and garnish with parsley.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Cook ground beef until brown.
Melt Velveeta in crock-pot. Add all other ingredients and stir until heated through.
Serve over tortilla chips.

title: spetsofai
directions: Fry sausage first in a pan with oil, then add the peppers and mix altogether with the tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Put all ingredients in a Pyrex and add the cheese.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ginger-soy dressing
directions: Whisk together the mustard and oil in a small bowl.
Slowly whisk in the vinegar and soy sauce, then the ginger and pepper. Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: oven french toast
directions: Melt butter in 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan in hot oven at 425°.
Sprinkle with mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Mix eggs and orange juice; dip bread slices in the mixture until bread is well soaked.
Arrange close together in pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until set.
Invert on serving plates and serve with hot maple syrup and sifted powdered sugar.

title: overnight pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.

Drain, rinse and drain again. Cool. Place lettuce in bottom of a 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Top with macaroni and egg slices. Sprinkle with salt. Layer ham strips, thawed peas, shredded cheese in order on top of eggs.

title: sauerkraut & barley
directions: **Sauerkraut can be found in cans or packages.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a baked pie shell. Chill about 2 hours before serving.

title: pickle pepper
directions: Mix vinegar, water and salt and boil 3 or 4 minutes.
Put pepper in clean jars with 1 clove garlic and 1 hot pepper, if you like it hot.
Pour hot mixture over pepper and seal.
Turn jars upside-down for a good seal.

title: mississippi mud texas sheet cake
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, salt and baking soda and set aside. In a separate saucepan mix together water, Crisco, butter and cocoa.
Bring to a boil and pour over flour mixture and beat well. Add vanilla, eggs, and buttermilk.
Beat again and pour into well greased pan, 15 x 10 x 1. Bake for 20-25 minutes at 350°.
Ice.

title: spam-n-macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
In the same pan, add the cheese, milk, onion and celery soup.
When melted, add Spam.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cornflake crumbs and bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: orange scones
directions: Grate peel; measure juice and buttermilk.
Add egg and beat smooth.
Mix flour and dry ingredients together.
Add butter; cut in fine granules.
Add sugar, almond and orange peel.
Add egg mix.
Mix to soft dough; knead dough 5 to 6 times until well mixed.
Form dough and cut into smaller circles or shapes.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until medium brown or golden.

title: baked macaroni
directions: Boil macaroni until tender.
Drain thoroughly.
Stir in butter and egg.
Mix mustard with salt and 1 tablespoon hot water and add to milk.
Add cheese to macaroni, leaving enough to sprinkle on top.
Pour macaroni into buttered casserole.
Add milk.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is crispy.

title: raisin dressing(great with ham)
directions: Soak raisins in water long enough to plump them.
Drain.
Mix bread, raisins and sugar.
Add melted butter and mix.
Combine slightly beaten egg and cream.
Add to bread mixture.
Bake in 1-quart casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Cook the giblets, heart and neck in approximately 2 quarts water with salt, pepper and poultry seasoning to taste.
Cool and chop. Save liquid.
Mix the onions and green pepper together with corn bread and dried bread.
Mix thoroughly.
Add giblets and mix together.
Pour melted oleo over mixture and gradually add liquid from giblet water to make mixture very moist but not mushy or runny.
Season with poultry seasoning, pepper and small amount of salt to taste as liquid has salt in it.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix the egg yolks, sugar, flour and milk.
Boil on low to medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
In baking dish, put a layer of graham crackers and a layer of bananas.
Pour half the filling over this.
Put another layer of each.
Top with meringue.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Mix all together, except kisses, until blended.
With floured hands, roll into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes, until cookies look dry with tops cracked.
Remove and press a chocolate kiss in center of each.

title: no-bake summer cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Gently stir in whipped topping. Spoon mixture into graham cracker ready to use (9-inch) pie crust. Refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight. Top with fresh fruit or cherry pie filling or fresh strawberries, etc.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Mix together and form into fingers.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 275° for 40 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar and heat until dissolved. Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Add to pineapple.
Add cherry and lemon juice.
Cream the cream cheese until soft.
Put cut up cherries into it.
Add to pineapple mixture.
Let chill until slightly firm.
Whip the cream and fold into the pineapple mixture.
Mold and chill.

title: enchiladas
directions: Fry meat; drain.
Add chili con carne; heat thoroughly.
Warm tortillas as directed on package.
Onto each tortilla place 1 1/2 tablespoons meat mixture; sprinkle chopped onion and cheese. Roll; place upside down in baking dish, 9
x 13-inch, greased. Repeat until dish is filled.
Cover with meat mixture.
Sprinkle with more onions and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato wedges
directions: Place potato wedges, cut side down, on rack in broiler pan. Brush with oil; sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Set oven control to broil or 550°.
Broil with tops about 3 inches from heat until brown, about 5 minutes.
Turn; brush with oil.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Broil until tender, about 5 minutes.

title: bulgur with mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soak dried mushrooms in hot water. Heat butter in large skillet.
Saute onion and celery until soft. Push sauteed onion and celery aside and add cleaned and sliced fresh mushrooms.
Cook for 4 to 5 minutes.
Squeeze liquid from dried mushrooms and reserve liquid.
Stir bulgur into the pan and cook over medium heat until bulgur begins to color.
Stir in beef stock and 1/4 cup mushroom liquid.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and cook for 10 minutes or until bulgur softens.
Add additional mushroom liquid as needed.
Cover.
Put in heated oven for 20 minutes or until steaming.
Stir in toasted nuts and sprinkle with parsley.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter. Blend in flour and salt to the butter and onions. Gradually add sour cream to the mixture.
Stir until smooth and bubbly. Add corn and heat thoroughly.
Fold in 1/2 of bacon crumbles. Put corn mixture into a 2-quart greased casserole dish. Top with remaining bacon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: old-fashioned apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and lemon juice; mix well.
Add apples and raisins; turn into 8-inch square baking dish.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; sprinkle evenly over apples.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve warm.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown the hamburger in skillet or microwave.
Remove excess grease. Add mushrooms, onion, garlic and butter and cook until onion is tender.
Combine in a separate bowl the soup, flour, catsup, salt and pepper. Stir soup mixture into ground beef.
Heat to boiling and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir sour cream and heat through. Serve over hot, cooked noodles or rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fettucine with chicken in marsala
directions: Dust chicken with flour.
Heat oil in a wide frying pan over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook until golden brown (about 3 to 4 minutes total).
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Drain excess pan drippings.
Add onion and mushrooms and cook until onion is soft, about 4 minutes.
Add garlic and shallot and cook 1 minute. Add wine, beef broth, tomato and green onions.
Heat through and let sauce thicken.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions (no salt).
Drain. Blend in soup, cheese and egg.
Add mayonnaise and milk.
Stir in broccoli.
Put cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: molasses cake
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Blend in molasses and eggs.
Stir soda into water.
Sift together the flour, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and salt.
Add alternately with water-soda mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 275° for 20 minutes, or until center springs back to touch.

title: skillet candy
directions: Beat sugar into eggs.
Put the margarine in skillet and add eggs and sugar, cook until thickened.
Take off heat, add the chopped dates.
Let cool and add the pecans and Rice Krispies.
Add vanilla.
Stir, cool until lukewarm.
Roll into balls.
Roll in coconut.
Ready to serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Put eggs, oleo, bananas and sugar in blender.
Blend until smooth, about 30 seconds.
Pour blended mixture over sifted dry ingredients.
Mix gently until barely combined.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts, if desired.
Pour into 8 x 4-inch greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: boneless breast of chicken parmesan
directions: Flatten breasts; set aside.
In three shallow bowls, put flour and nutmeg in one, eggs in one and bread crumbs and Parmesan in one.
Dip breasts in flour mixture first, then into the eggs, then into the bread crumb mixture.
Fry in oil, butter or margarine, very slowly, until brown on both sides.
Place in baking pan.
Add water.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix hamburger with crushed rackers.
Mix 1/2 cup of the milk with hamburger mix.
Press in pan or long baking dish.
Mix other 1/2 cup milk with cream of mushroom soup in bowl by itself.
Pour over top of hamburger mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until hamburger is done.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: grandma's ginger puffs
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Stir in egg and molasses.
Mix soda and spices with sifted flour and add to the creamed shortening mixture.
With hands, roll into 1-inch balls and then in granulated sugar.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook mixture.
When thickens, pour over bananas and vanilla wafers, which have been layered in Pyrex dish.
Beat whites for icing and put over mixture.
Brown in 350° oven.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients as listed in a 4-quart salad bowl.
Seal with 1 cup mayonnaise.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Toss just before serving.

title: chess cake
directions: Heat first two
ingredients
on
low heat.
Remove from heat and add other ingredients in order given.
Put in greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Bake at 300° for approximately 40 minutes.
Cut and roll cake in powdered sugar while hot.

title: payday bars
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and press into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Take out of oven and sprinkle with marshmallows.
Return to oven for 1 minute. Heat next 4 ingredients until peanut butter chips are melted. Remove from heat and add peanuts and Rice Krispies.
Spoon over marshmallows and chill.
Cut into bars.

title: ernie's wild rice and mushroom soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, prepare rice according to directions (except omit oil or butter).
Over medium heat in non-stick pan, dry saute mushrooms.
Mix together beef bouillons and 1 c. of water.
If mushrooms begin to stick, add broth 1 tablespoon at a time.
When brown and earthy smelling, add prepared rice.
Then add mushroom soup and water and remainder of bouillon.
Simmer over medium heat until mixture is thoroughly mixed and bubbly.
If thicker soup is desired, add the Instant Roux Mix, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: toll house oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Blend together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Stir in water and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in nut meats or raisins, chocolate bits and oatmeal.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and half of butter together.
Put half of butter on bottom of baking dish.
Pour mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Croutons optional.

title: special shrimp and rice
directions: Saute sausage until brown. Add oil, garlic and peppers.
Cook until tender. Add parsley, seasonings, water and rice.
Stir well. Add shrimp and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover. Cook on low heat 25 to 30 minutes or until shrimp are pink.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Blend in rest of ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Put pie in freezer.
When ready to serve, remove and defrost before serving.

title: chile relleno casserole
directions: *I try Rosarita brand chiles, whole-roasted and peeled.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Add sugar and cocoa; stir and add milk.
Bring to boil; add butter.
Form soft ball; add vanilla, peanut butter and oats. Spoon out onto waxed paper.

title: parmesan cheese chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese, salt and parsley.
Melt butter.
Add garlic, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Dip chicken into butter mixture; then coat well with bread crumbs.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
Drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake 30 minutes, until golden brown.

title: vicky parrish's bar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg yolks and flour. Add 1 cup chopped nuts.
Divide into 2 balls (add flour if sticky).
Press one ball into 8 x 8-inch greased pan.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour and baking soda.
Set aside.
Combine butter, sugars, vanilla and pudding.
Mix in large mixing bowl and beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: peach fuzz
directions: Cut peach into small pieces.
Put all ingredients into blender.
Mix at high speed until smooth.
Serve in tall glass over ice.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let sit in refrigerator overnight.

title: fettucini alfredo with asparagus
directions: Snap the tough ends off the asparagus and discard them.
Cut the spears into 1-inch pieces.
In a large pot of boiling, salted water, cook the fettucini until almost done (about 8 minutes).
Add the asparagus.
Cook until just done, about 4 more minutes.
Drain the pasta and asparagus and toss with sauce prepared as follows:

title: easy pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Punch holes in top with a fork while warm.
Mix milk and cream of coconut and pour over cake.
Pour can of pineapple over the coconut milk mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over top of cake. Sprinkle can of coconut over top of Cool Whip.

title: mystery pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, salt, egg, cherry pie filling and vanilla together.
Pour in 8-inch square greased pan.
Mix nuts and brown sugar, sprinkle on top of batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Serve with ice cream.

title: syrup tea cakes
directions: Beat eggs; add syrup.
Stir in soda.
Place baking powder and nutmeg in butter and add egg mixture.
Add enough flour to make dough stiff enough to handle.
Roll out dough to a thickness of 1-inch; cut into circles.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: quesadillas
directions: Heat butter in a skillet.
Place 1 tortilla in the skillet. Sprinkle with half the cheese, half the diced onion, picante sauce and seasonings to taste.
When the cheese has melted and the tortilla is lightly browned, cover with another tortilla.
Flip to brown the second side.
Remove from heat; cut the sandwich into quarters.
Keep warm in a low oven.
Arrange on a plate with refried beans on the side, shredded lettuce and diced tomatoes. Serve with guacamole and/or sour cream for dipping.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, water and corn syrup until it spins a thread. Beat egg whites.
Add syrup slowly and beat until it begins to set.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: tangier island corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add milk and corn. In small dish, put cornstarch; add a little water. Stir until dissolved. Add cornstarch to eggs, milk and corn. Add salt and sugar; mix well. Dot with butter. Bake in dish at 350° for 30 minutes until set.

title: crock-pot potato soup
directions: Put all ingredients, except evaporated milk, in crock-pot. Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or on high for 3 to 4 hours.
Stir in milk during last hour.
If desired, mash potatoes with masher before serving.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers, onions and garlic.
Add salt and cover with 2 or 3 trays of ice.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain well, remove garlic.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Put in jars and cook in a canner for 5 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Cream sugar with oil.
Add eggs; beat.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Beat.
Add fruit and nuts; beat.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake about 65 minutes at 350°.
Cool 1 hour.
Remove from pan.

title: soltis easter relish
directions: Great-Grandpa Soltis' recipe from 1928.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer lettuce, cauliflower, bacon and onion in large bowl. Mix together Spin Blend, sugar and cheese to make dressing.
Pour over top of layers, but do not mix.
Cover and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Toss just before serving.

title: brandied orange bowknots
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
With hands, work in shortening until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Add eggs and orange juice.
Mix to form dough.
Shape into ball. Cover with brandy and let stand 30 minutes.
Roll out onto floured board to thickness of pie crust.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Cut slit in center and pull one end of dough through slit.
Deep fry until golden brown, about 30 seconds.
Drain on paper.
Cool and sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: pudding candy
directions: Blend dry pudding mix and sugar in medium pan. Stir in evaporated milk and butter.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Lower heat and boil gently for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Beat immediately while pudding is very hot until it becomes somewhat dull.
Pour into greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch) or drop by tablespoon on waxed paper. Cool until set.

title: pecans squares
directions: In a large mixing bowl, blend together flour, sugar, butter and salt until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press firmly and evenly into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, prepare filling.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except pecans and heat until smooth.
Then mix pecans and mix well.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: royal cashew brittle
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
In saucepan, combine sugar, syrup and water.
Cook until sugar is dissolved and without stirring to 260°.
Add nuts and salt cooking until 290°, stirring to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla and soda. Pour onto cookie sheet.
Let stand until just cool enough to handle and stretch brittle slightly with greased fingers.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil first four ingredients 5 minutes, remove from heat and stir in 1/2 teaspoon soda and pour mixture over popcorn in roaster.
Bake in 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. May freeze!

title: chili-cornbread casserole
directions: Combine chili, Ranch style beans and corn and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Prepare cornbread mix according to directions on pouch and pour over mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 425° or until cornbread is golden brown.

title: buttermilk icing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Boil slightly until a soft ball stage. Remove from heat and beat until thick enough to spread on cake. This icing gets softer after it is on cake for awhile.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well together. Refrigerate when not used.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream the cheese and margarine thoroughly.
Add pepper, sugar and mustard to flour and blend with cheese and margarine mixture. Fill a cookie press with dough to make cookies into desired shape. Place cookies on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Wash and rinse sauerkraut; add celery, onion and green pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetable mixture.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: jew bread
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Heat fat.
Add onion and cook until soft and golden, approximately 10 minutes.
Add flour; stir until blended.
Add stock slowly and stir over low heat until thick and smooth. Season to taste.
May wish to use celery and/or onion salt.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix
the
whole
thing together and drop heaping tablespoons onto
cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven (350°) for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple.
Put in sauce pan and bring to a boil. Dissolve jello in juice.
Beat cream cheese into this and then add rest of ingredients.
Congeal.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Melt butter in pan (I use a glass baking dish). Dip biscuits in butter on both sides. Bake at 400° to 425° until brown.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Chop together cabbage, onions, bell peppers and carrots.
Boil sugar, vinegar, cooking oil, salt, mustard seed and celery seed. Pour over vegetable mixture.
Pour in freezer bags.
Freeze.
Will keep 2 or 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: gale's homemade chili
directions: Cook the meat until brown, then drain.
In a big pot, put the meat, the beans and the can of soup.
Fill the can with water and add that.
Stir all the ingredients together for about 2 minutes. Add the chili powder to taste in the pot.
Put the lid on and cook chili between low and medium for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: raw broccoli salad
directions: Cook bacon, crumble and allow to cool. Mix together in a large bowl; broccoli, kernels, onion, and bacon.
Set aside.
In a separate bowl mix together vinegar, sugar, and mayonnaise. Pour sauce over broccoli mixture and mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Soften margarine or shortening.
Mix in sugar, soda, salt, cream of tartar, eggs adding flour a little at a time.
Roll into ball (teaspoon) and roll in the cinnamon, sugar mixture.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for about 10 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: winter crisp dessert
directions: Slice apples thin.
Arrange in buttered oblong pan.
Spoon cranberry sauce over apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Stir oats, flour and sugar together, then cut in butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over cranberry layer.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until top is browned and apples tender.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Place potatoes in a 2 qt. baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients except cheese; pour over potatoes.
Place pork chops over potatoes; sprinkle with cheese.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken; remove from bones and shred.
Cook shells in chicken broth and water.
(You may need to use chicken bouillon for more flavor.)
Place a layer of shells in casserole dish, then layer chicken, pimentos and mushroom soup.
Add a second layer of shells and top with Cheez Whiz.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts and soup bubbles up, about 1 hour.

title: light dilled potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, sprinkle corn oil and vinegar over potatoes; toss lightly to coat.
Combine reduced calorie mayonnaise, yogurt and mustard.
Add mayonnaise mixture and remaining ingredients to potatoes.
Toss to coat well.
Cover and chill.
Serves 14 to 16.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Brown meat, saute onions, cabbage and celery.
Add tomatoes, kidney beans, water, salt, pepper and chili powder. Heat to boil. Mix milk and Bisquick.
Drop by spoonfuls on meat mix.
Boil 10 minutes, uncovered, and 10 minutes covered.

title: almond bacon cheese dip
directions: Chop almonds fine and crumble bacon. Combine all ingredients. Mix lightly. Serve as dip for vegetables or with crackers.

title: pink salad
directions: Drain juice off fruit.
Mix all ingredients and chill 6 to 8 hours or overnight.

title: cheese dip
directions: Empty can of Ro-Tel tomatoes into crock-pot.
Cook and drain sausage.
Add to tomatoes.
Cut cheese up and add to mixture. Heat until melted; stir.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lye hominy
directions: Place scant teaspoon of lye into iron kettle (never use aluminum).
Cautiously add 1 gallon of water.
When lye comes into contact with water, it boils up and produces a solution caustic enough to cause dangerous burns to skin and flesh.
Add corn. Stir; let stand overnight.
Use only an enamelware or stainless steel spoon.

title: cheese stuffed potatoes
directions: Brush potatoes lightly with corn oil; place on a baking sheet. Bake at 400° until potatoes are tender, about 1 hour.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise, carefully scoop out potato from skins.
Mash potatoes with butter, onion, sauce and salt.
Spoon potato mixture into potato shells, top with cheese.
Put back in oven to melt cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika if desired.

title: chicken with broccoli and cashews
directions: Combine soy sauce, sherry, ginger and chicken in small bowl. Mix and let stand 10 minutes.

title: constipation recipe
directions: Grind prunes, figs and raisins in blender.
Steep tea in one pint of boiling water for twenty minutes.
Strain.
Cook ground fruit with lemon juice and brown sugar 5 minutes in senna tea.

title: halibut chowder
directions: 1. Boil water and bouillon.
2. Add vegetables and turn down to simmer for 10 minutes.
3. Add fish and simmer for 5 minutes. 4. Melt butter in large sauce pan, add flour and stir well adding milk slowly. Stir CONSTANTLY ! until thick.
5. Remove from heat. Add cheese and stir until cheese
melts.
6. Mix vegetables and sauce together.
7. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Melt oleo in a large skillet.
Add the chicken and brown on all sides over medium heat.
Add the chopped onion to the skillet and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups cider, salt, pepper and lemon peel.
Cover the skillet and let ingredients simmer 30 minutes.
Remove the chicken
and keep warm. Combine cornstarch with the remaining 1/2 cup cider and add to the skillet with the sugar and cranberries.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Return chicken to the skillet along with the sliced bananas.
Heat all ingredients to serving temperature.

title: layered mexican salad
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Let cool.
Heat refried beans. In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, spread beans on bottom.
Sprinkle hamburger over beans.
Mix taco seasoning with sour cream and spread over hamburger.
Dice tomatoes and green onions.
Sprinkle tomatoes over sour cream mixture and green onions over tomatoes. Top with cheese.
Serve with Mexican corn chips.
Great for parties.

title: cherry topped cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese and sugar until creamy.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: jalapeno salsa
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together the ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake 30 minutes, until done.
Place meatballs on paper towels to drain; set aside.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: In a skillet, combine flour, salt and paprika.
Coat 12 chicken
breast
halves.
Brown
both
sides
in butter, using large skillet.
Add
cup
water;
simmer
for 30 minutes. Arrange chicken
in serving dish.
Mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup of the half and half.
Stir into the drippings in the skillet. Cook and stir
over low heat.
Slowly add the rest of half and half, sherry,
lemon
peel and juice.
Cook until it thickens. Pour over chicken.
(May
be frozen at this point.) Heat oven to 350°. Bake
minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Put back in oven uncovered until cheese melts.
Serve hot.
Serves 12.

title: carnitas(little meats)
directions: Place lard in a heavy, deep pot over medium-low heat. Trim fat from the meat and cut the meat into 3-inch cubes and lightly salt. (Meat may be cut into 1-inch cubes for use as an appetizer.)
When the lard has melted, place the meat, orange slices and cilantro in the pot.
(Melted lard should completely cover the meat.)

Cook over medium-low heat 1 1/2 to 2 hours or 1-inch cubes, 2 to 2 1/2 hours or 3-inch cubes. The lard will begin to boil after 30 minutes. The orange slices supply the water which allows the lard to boil.
Boil gently through the cooking process.
As the water gradually cooks away, the temperature of the lard will rise, allowing the meat to brown.
If the meat has not browned at the end of the cooking time, remove the orange slices. Watch carefully and remove the meat as soon as it browns.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil and bone chicken.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add soups, milk and chilies.
Layer tortillas, chicken and sauce in large casserole.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until hot. This is much better made 24 hours before serving.

title: almond pound cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan with tablespoon of Crisco and use sugar instead of flour to dust pan.
Blend cake mix and Jell-O together in a bowl.
Beat.
Add eggs, vanilla, the water with almond extract and Crisco oil.
Beat well for 4 minutes.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Check for doneness with toothpick (don't overcook).
Remove from pan 25 minutes later. Let cool 15 minutes.
Can be wrapped in foil to keep moist or kept in cake container.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Combine all vegetables in a large bowl.
Heat together the sugar, salt, vinegar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.

title: copper kettle potatoes(servings:  8)
directions: Add all ingredients to potatoes, beating constantly.
Should be moist; if not, add cream and butter.
Bake in ovenproof serving dish, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Make the day before and refrigerate, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: date bread
directions: Pour
boiling
water
over chopped dates.
Cream melted butter and sugar together.
Add the beaten egg.
Mix the flour and dry ingredients.
Add the dry ingredients, dates and water alternately;
beat
together.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: monkey bread
