directions: Cut biscuits into quarters. Mix remaining ingredients together in a bowl. Alternate layers of biscuit pieces and brown sugar mixture, 1/3 at a time, in a greased Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Invert onto serving plate.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine ingredients.
Put 1/2 the nuts in the cheese ball and save the rest to roll cheese ball in.

title: orzo with pine nuts and feta cheese
directions: Bring large pot of salted water to boil.
Add orzo and boil until just tender but still firm to bite, stirring occasionally, about 6 minutes.
Drain well.
Return to pot.
Add oil and toss to coat.
Mix in feta and pine nuts.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Whip 4 egg whites and melt chocolate in 1/4 cup boiling water. Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Add 3/4 cup buttermilk, alternating with flour.
Dissolve soda in remaining 1/4 cup buttermilk and add to flour mixture.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and pinch of salt to chocolate and add to batter. Fold mixture of egg whites into batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian pot roast
directions: Brown roast in shortening in Dutch oven.
Pour off drippings. Add soy sauce, 1/2 cup water, pepper, ginger and onion.
Cover tightly; cook slowly for 3 hours or until roast is tender.
Drain pineapple; combine with mushrooms and celery.
Add to roast.
Cook 20 minutes longer.
Remove roast to heated platter.
Mix remaining water and flour; add to liquid in pan.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Serve with roast.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except the dates or nuts.
Add the dates or nuts last.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cottage cheese fruit whip
directions: Mix all and refrigerate several hours.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; refrigerate overnight.

title: oatmeal chippers
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and soda.
Cream sugar and margarine; add rolled oats, eggs, molasses and milk and beat well. Add dry ingredients, beating until well blended.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes, drain and mash.
Boil eggs.
Mix onion, potatoes, eggs, pickles, mayonnaise and salt and pepper to taste.

title: rosemary chicken
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, melt the butter over medium heat.
Add the taso and andouille and saute until crisp, about 5 to 8 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add the onions, celery and bell peppers.
Saute until tender, but still firm, about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally and scraping pan bottom well.

title: shamrock salad
directions: Mix jello and
water.
Let
chill
until partially set. Mix cream cheese, pineapple, Miracle Whip, lemon juice, apple, nuts and cherries.
Add this to jello and chill until firm.

title: hearty cheese chowder
directions: Combine water and bouillon cubes bring to boil; add vegetables, cover and simmer until tender.
Melt butter or margarine in heavy saucepan; blend in flour and cook 1 minute. Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Stir cheese sauce, pimiento and hot sauce into vegetable mixture.
Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated (do not boil).
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: winter vegetable parmesan(meatless main dish; 285 calories per serving)
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat in 2 tablespoons hot salad oil, cook zucchini, onions, garlic and 1/4 teaspoon salt until tender-crisp.
Discard garlic; remove mixture to bowl.
In 2 more tablespoons hot salad oil, stir broccoli and cauliflower; add water and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cover; cook until tender-crisp, stirring occasionally.
Return zucchini mixture to Dutch oven; add remaining ingredients.
Cover; cook 5 minutes or until hot. Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: spicy cheeseburger soup
directions: In large sauce pan combine first eight ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in beef and 2 cups of milk;
heat through.
Combine flour and remaining milk until smooth;
gradually stir into soup. Bring to boil, cook and stir 2 minutes or until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat; stir in cheese until melted.	Add cayenne pepper if desired.	Top with bacon before serving.	Makes 2 quarts.
6 to 8 people.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Place first three ingredients in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Over top mixture, sprinkle cubed rye bread and grated Swiss cheese.
Pour melted butter over bread.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (30 minutes with foil 15 minutes without foil).

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix crushed pineapple with juice and pudding until well mixed. Add Cool Whip, marshmallows and 1 cup chopped pecans. Refrigerate.

title: summer's end
directions: In large skillet pour in approximately 2 tablespoons oil.
Add sliced onion and sliced garlic.
Cook until onion starts to brown. Add sliced peppers and cook until slightly tender.
Add tomatoes and spices, etc.
Cook approximately 30 minutes on low to medium heat.
Serve hot.
Good as side dish or just with bread.

title: hot pineapple punch
directions: Combine all ingredients together; simmer for 10 minutes. Serve hot.
Cut thin orange slice and stick half a toothpick underneath slice to make them float.
Makes 2 quarts.
Serves 8 people.
Double for 15 or more.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast	in
lukewarm
water
into a bowl.
Sift flour into yeast	and
water and stir until all flour is dampened. Knead on
floured
board for 1 minute or 2; roll out to desired thickness
and
cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 400° for 12 or 15 minutes.
Dough can be placed in refrigerator and used up to a week later.

title: strawberry cordial
directions: In large glass bowl, stir together the strawberries and vodka.
Cover and refrigerate for 5 days.
Place a large strainer over a clean bowl.
Pour the liquid from the strawberry vodka mixture through a strainer.
Then place the strawberries, a single layer at at time, on the strainer and press them gently with the back of a spoon to let juices flow freely.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cover chicken with water.
Add bouillon cubes.	Cook until done.
Debone chicken.
Mix flour and Crisco.
Add buttermilk. Make a stiff dough.
Roll out on a floured pastry cloth.
Be sure the pastry is very thin.
Cut into squares.
Drop pastry squares into boiling chicken broth.
Let the dumplings cook on medium for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add chicken.
Stir under the dumplings.	Add sweet milk.
Cook covered for 30 minutes on low.

title: e z crescent rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water and 1/4 cup sugar.
Mix together the eggs, oil, remaining water and sugar.
Combine yeast and egg mixture.
Add flour and salt.
Knead dough until it forms a smooth ball.
Refrigerate overnight.
Divide dough into two parts.
Roll out to a circle.
Spread with melted butter or margarine.
Using a pizza cutter, cut wedges.
Roll up; bend into a crescent shape.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for half of the grated cheese.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle on remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Line bottom of pan with some margarine.
Pour crushed pineapple into pan; spread around.
Pour cherries into pan; spread around.
Pour cake mix into pan; spread around.
Sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Cut several thin slices of margarine and lay on top of nuts.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chicken salad honolulu
directions: Cook the rice. Mix together all ingredients except the almonds. Top with almonds. May be served with Thompson grapes. Chill several hours.

title: potato souffle
directions: Boil sweet potatoes for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Melt marshmallows in pot.
Mix sugar, melted marshmallows, vanilla flavoring, pecans and milk.
Bake.
Makes 15 to 20 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, add bell pepper and onion.
Saute 2 or 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, beans and rice.
Simmer until liquid is slightly reduced.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly.
Serve over Frito chips.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls. Bake in a 350° oven on cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: virginia rolls
directions: Melt margarine, add yeast to warm water and dissolve.
Add margarine, then beaten egg.
Add flour with sugar all at once and stir.
Drop by spoonful into muffin pan that has been greased. Bake.
Unused mixture may be stored in refrigerator for later use.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine all vegetables including pimentos in bowl. In a glass jar, combine oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper. Shake well to mix. Pour dressing over vegetables. Refrigerate overnight before serving; 24 hours is best.

title: frozen cranberry fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.

title: corn souffle
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 300° to 325° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour, until center is not liquidly.
Serve warm.
Test with knife in center; if it comes out dry, it has baked long enough.

title: baked fish
directions: Arrange fish on an ungreased baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Top with bell pepper rings and tomato slices. Pour lemon juice and oil over this.
Cover.
Cook on 375° for 15 minutes.
Uncover and cook for 15 minutes longer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup and broth together.
Fix stuffing as if to stuff chicken (see bag).
Layer chicken, stuffing and soup in casserole dish; save 1/2 cup stuffing to sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or chicken soup

title: lentil soup
directions: Wash lentils.
Add water, salt, onion, carrot, celery, bay leaf and thyme.
Cook slowly for about 45 minutes.
Add tomatoes, butter and meat and heat well.
(Tomatoes may be cooked with lentils, etc. if preferred.)
Yield:
6 to 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: beau monde dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill for a minimum of 3 hours. Hollow out bread; pour dip into bread.
Cut up remaining bread into chunks; use for dipping.
Delicious!!

title: peanut butterscotchers(melted butterscotch morsels on top!)
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Melt butter in saucepan; remove from heat.
Add sugar and milk.
Blend well. Blend in eggs; beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients and lemon rind and mix well.
Pour into 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan, greased and floured on bottom.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool. Spread with topping.
Let stand until set.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples into a 2-quart dish; sprinkle with spice, salt and water.
Work flour, sugar and butter together until crumbly. Spread over apples.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: apple cake with walnuts
directions: Cream together eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda and add to sugar and oil mixture.
Blend thoroughly, then fold in apples and walnuts.
Pour into 8 x 10 x 2-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Let sit in pan approximately 10 to 20 minutes, then turn out on plate.
Serve warm or cold, either plain or with whipped or ice cream.

title: broiled flounder with mustard
directions: Preheat the broiler to high.
Place the fillets on a flat surface.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and brush with oil. Arrange the fillets on a baking sheet or dish.
Blend the mayonnaise, mustard and parsley.
Brush it evenly over the fillets.

title: jello popcorn balls
directions: Bring Jell-O, white syrup and sugar to a boil for 1 minute; pour over popcorn and form into balls with butter on hands.
Wrap and store away.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Layer pie filling.
Sprinkle with a pinch of sugar.
Spread nuts on pie filling.
Mix melted butter and cake mix until crumbly.
Put on pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion.
Saute until onion is golden yellow.
Add potatoes, water, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook on low heat until potatoes are very soft.
Stir frequently. Add corn, milk and evaporated milk.
Heat, stirring frequently, until chowder bubbles.

title: warm salad
directions: Put a large pot of salted water on to boil. In a large bowl, combine scallions, parsley, dill, lemon zest, lemon juice, capers and oil. Season with salt and pepper. Peel turnips and carrots and cut into julienne cubes. Cut zucchini into julienne cubes. Snap tough ends off asparagus and slice on the diagonal. Add turnips and carrots to the boiling water and cook for 30 seconds. Add zucchini,
asparagus and peas and cook until barely tender, 2 to 3 minutes. Drain vegetables, add to scallion mixture and toss to combine. Adjust seasoning with salt and pepper. Sprinkle with feta.

title: kid's strawberry sparklers
directions: Place the ice cubes in a blender or food processor and blend until they are crushed.
Add the strawberries, concentrated limeade and water.
Puree the mixture until smooth and thick. Pour into tall glasses with flexi straws.
Serves 2.

title: miniature corn puppies
directions: For Batter:
In a medium mixing bowl, stir together flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.

title: easy irish bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat with a wooden spoon until smooth.
Pour into a large loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for at least 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake by directions on box.
Make 2 layers and after cooled, split to make 4 layers.

title: portuguese pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Put to one side.
Place all other ingredients in casserole.
Pour 1 1/2 cups mushroom soup over vegetables.
Next, place pork chops on top as well as pan drippings.
Place remaining 1/2 cup of soup over top.
Cover with aluminum foil in 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Remove foil and continue to cook for another 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unroll 1 package of crescent rolls and spread into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, sealing at seams.
In mixing bowl cream together cream cheese, sugar and flavorings, beating until smooth.
Spread cream cheese mixture over top of crescent rolls.
Unroll 2nd package of rolls and press together at seams.
Lay over top of cream cheese mixture.
Brush with beaten egg white.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mary's cookies(mexican wedding cakes)
directions: Cream the margarine and powdered sugar. Add and mix in the flour, nuts and vanilla. Form into small balls (teaspoon size). Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 275° for 40 minutes or until light brown on bottom. Tops need not brown. Roll in powdered sugar. These freeze well.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen and can easily be halved.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese, sugar, peanut butter and 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Spread into baked pie shell.
(Can use graham cracker crust for a sweeter tasting pie.) Top with balance of Cool Whip. Garnish
with
graham
cracker
crumbs if desired. Refrigerate.

title: creamy fettucine
directions: Mix cheeses, butter and milk and heat until smooth.
Pour over fettucine and serve.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar in a large mixing bowl. Add egg and vanilla; blend well. Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; blend into creamed mixture. Stir in nuts, if desired. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Do not overbake. Cookies will be soft. Cool on cookie sheet until set, about 1 to 2 minutes. Remove to wire rack to cool completely. Makes about 2 1/4 dozen.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, vanilla and sifted ingredients. Add milk.
Roll dough and cut.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: low-sugar sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add cold water, bananas, pineapple and marshmallows.
Chill in refrigerator until congealed.

title: steak soup
directions: Melt butter and stir in flour to make a smooth paste. Gradually stir in water.
Set aside.
In large skillet, saute ground chuck.
Drain and add to soup stock.
Parboil onion, carrots and celery for 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain and add to soup. Add remainder of ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
This soup freezes well.
It makes a large amount.

title: peach pie
directions: Pour peaches and juice into a dish.
Mix together the sugar and flour.
Pour over peaches.
Break up margarine over this. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tallarene
directions: Saute onion.
Add meat and cook until meat is no longer red. Add soup, water, noodles and salt.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add corn and mushrooms.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer for 30 minutes.
Good on ribs and chicken.

title: strawberry crumbles
directions: Cream oleo and add the brown sugar, flour and nuts.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
When cool, crumble and pat back into the pan.
Save 2 tablespoons of crumbles for top.

title: party quiche
directions: Separate biscuits, dividing each into halves.
Line small party muffin tins with biscuits.
Fill with bacon or ham, cheese, adding onions and peppers, if desired.
Mix eggs and milk.
Season with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Spoon milk mixture over biscuits. Place in 350° oven until "set" and pastry is lightly browned, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from pan and serve immediately.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding with milk until thickened.
Fold in Cool Whip. In a 9 x 13-inch pan put a layer of graham crackers, then 1/2 of the pudding mixture.
Repeat another layer of graham crackers and the other half of the pudding mixture.
End with a layer of graham crackers.
Spread chocolate icing on top.
Refrigerate.

title: glorious mashed potatoes(serves 4)
directions: Peel potatoes and cut them into 1/4-inch slices.
Place the slices in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add water to cover.
Set the lid on the pan askew and boil for 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain the potatoes and mash with a fork or potato masher, adding the milk to moisten them.
Mix in the butter, sour cream and cream cheese until well blended.
Season with the salt and pepper and sprinkle with the chives, if used.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onion and cheese in a large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and seasoning.
Toss.
Refrigerate at least 1/2 hour before serving.
Add crisp fried bacon just before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine butter, eggs, sugars, salt and vanilla.
Beat with a wire whip or rotary beater until smooth.
Stir in corn syrup until blended, making as little foam as possible.
Gently stir in pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: In one bowl, combine dry ingredients.
In another bowl, combine liquids and eggs.
Add flour mixture to liquids and stir just until batter is smooth.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
8 or 9 servings.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: cranberry cooler(summer delite)
directions: Mix fruit juices together, adding water to tangerine as directed on can.
Add sparkling water.
Pour over ice cubes in large pitcher.
Makes about 12 glasses.

title: applesauce yogurt delight
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in medium bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Measure 1 1/2 cups; stir in applesauce and cinnamon.
Pour into bowl or 8 dessert glasses.
Refrigerate until set but not firm.
Refrigerate remaining gelatin until slightly thickened.
Mix in yogurt; spoon over gelatin in bowl. Refrigerate 2 hours or until set.
Garnish with additional yogurt, apple slices and mint leaves, if desired.

title: apple roll
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large casserole dish, add butter, water, sugar and vanilla.
Let mixture get very hot.
Stir occasionally.
Roll out dough in a large circle.
Sprinkle with apples, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Mix this and place on dough. Roll up as a jelly roll.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch slices and drop into hot mixture.
Cook very slowly until golden brown, about 1 hour.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in baking pan laying flat (not on top of each other).
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over pork chops.
Cover with foil and place in refrigerator for 2 hours, then bake, covered, with the foil for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove foil and pour off liquid, then brown the chops about 15 minutes or until as brown as you'd like.

title: drumstick cake
directions: Mix cereal, peanut butter and syrup together.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread ice cream on top.
Set in freezer for 1/2 hour.
Take out of freezer.
Spread chocolate over ice cream. Sprinkle 1 cup peanuts over top.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart glass casserole, stir together sugar and syrup. Microwave at High 4 minutes.
Stir in 1 cup roasted, salted peanuts.
Microwave at High 3 to 5 minutes until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup mixture, blending well.
Microwave at High 1 to 2 minutes.
Syrup will be very hot and sticky.
Stir in 1 teaspoon baking soda gently until light and foamy.
This does not take long!
Pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet quickly!
Spread mixture out some by tipping pan back and forth. Cool 30 to 60 minutes.
Break into pieces.

title: orange chocolate float
directions: In blender container, place orange juice, syrup and sugar. Cover; blend.
Pour over ice in glass; top with whipped cream. Garnish with orange slice, if desired.
Serve immediately.
Makes 1 (6 ounce) serving.

title: swiss potato torte
directions: Grease 1 1/2-quart baking dish with cooking spray.
Pare and thinly slice potatoes in bowl.
Toss potatoes.
Add parsley, garlic, salt and spices in prepared dish.
Alternating with layers of potatoes, add broth.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 30 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 8.

title: quick dinner rolls
directions: Stir together and drop into muffin pan.
Bake at 400° until brown on top.

title: ranch style dip(low-fat)
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add cottage cheese and milk.
Process about 45 seconds until smooth.
Fold in yogurt and remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill thoroughly. Serve with assorted fresh vegetables.
Yields 1 1/2 cups. Contains 1.5 g protein, 2 g fat, 7 g carbohydrates.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill for 2 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Dissolve cranberry sauce in 1 cup boiling water.
Mix together and add chopped nuts. Pour half into container and let set.
Spread sour cream over set mixture.
Add remaining mixture and let set.
Cut and serve.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs and melted butter; press in 9 x 12-inch oblong pan for crust.
Place butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla in mixing bowl; beat 20 minutes at high speed.
Spread on crust.
Slice bananas, dip in pineapple juice and arrange on batter.
Spread pineapple on top of bananas.
Chill overnight.
Next day, spread Cool Whip, sprinkle nuts and add cherries.

title: cheese shrimp bites
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add eggs and mix until cheese is evenly distributed.
Stir in shrimp.
In a deep skillet or saucepan, heat oil to 375°.
Carefully drop teaspoons of batter into oil.
Fry 3 minutes or until golden, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan.
Mix 1 can beer with 3 tablespoons sugar.
Stir in 3 cups self-rising flour.
Pour into prepared loaf pan and bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fishmarket's grilled amberjack(serves 6)
directions: Preheat oil in iron skillet.
Sprinkle fish with lemon pepper. Place fish in hot skillet and cook for 4 to 5 minutes on each side.
Put lemon pepper on other side when turned.
Combine lemon juice, butter, oregano and garlic and heat in microwave.
Drizzle over fish when done.
Serve with pasta or rice and salad.
Yummy!

title: icy slush
directions: Dissolve jello, water and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Freeze in small containers.
Set out about 2 hours before serving.
Add 2 bottles (quart) of ginger ale.
This serves about 12 (generous servings).

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir meat and onion in butter until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in flour, salt, garlic, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in soup; heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat through.
Serve over noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine and cook until thick and vegetables are tender, 1 to 3 hours.
Put in hot, sterilized pint jars; seal and set aside to cool.
Mark and store in dark place.

title: venison chili
directions: Cook meat and onions in iron skillet until almost done.
Add everything else; bring to boil and reduce to low.
Simmer about an hour or remove to crock-pot and keep on low until ready to serve.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple to boil.
Stir in Jell-O and dissolve.
Remove from heat and add buttermilk.
Chill until partially congealed. Fold in Cool Whip.
Add nuts, if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken,
celery
and
onion
together for 1 hour. Cool. Skin
and debone chicken; chop into small pieces.
Save broth. Cook frozen vegetables in broth.
Mix chicken, vegetables, Wyler's
chicken stock, soup and 1 can of broth; season to taste. Use Grandma Frakes' pie crust.

title: quick chocolate ice cream
directions: Put all in ice cream freezer. Stir and then freeze.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix in blender all ingredients.
Scrape sides and mix 45 seconds more.
Pour in jar and cool until thick.
Equivalent to one can of Eagle Brand milk.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: With your hands, mix sugar and peanut butter together.
Divide into 3 equal portions; set aside.
Prepare the vanilla pudding according to package directions.
Spread 1/3 of peanut butter mixture in the bottom of the pie shell.
Spread pudding over peanut butter layer.
Spread 1/3 peanut butter mixture over pudding layer.
Spread Cool Whip over this layer.
Spread remaining 1/3 of peanut butter mixture over Cool Whip. Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.

title: boiled shrimp
directions: Follow directions on shrimp boil package to boil shrimp. Cocktail sauce is low-fat and very tasty. This is a great alternative to fried shrimp. Try placing shrimp on a saltine cracker topped with cocktail sauce. Yum Yum. Serve with vegetable and boiled new potatoes. Makes 2 servings.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: beef moussaka
directions: Pare eggplant and cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Combine bread crumbs and 1/2 teaspoon salt; coat both sides of eggplant with seasoned crumbs, reserving leftover crumbs.
Brown the eggplant in hot cooking fat, draining on absorbent paper.

title: fresh tomato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour to form a smooth paste.
Gradually add water, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add the tomatoes, parsley, salt, sugar, thyme, bay leaf and pepper; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes or until tomatoes are tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Garnish with lemon, if desired.
Yields 4 servings (5 cups).

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream the oleo.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients with sour milk.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.
One cup of raisins can be added to batter, if desired.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Combine in mixing bowl:
cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, soda, egg and yeast. Add flour.
Cover and let rise 50 to 60 minutes.
Stir down dough. Turn into well-greased 8-inch round casserole.
Let rise 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 350` for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: plucking bread
directions: Take 3 cups flour, add sugar and salt and resift.
Scald milk and cool to lukewarm.
Measure 1/2 cup milk and stir in yeast. Stir slightly beaten eggs and butter into remaining milk.
Combine egg mixture with flour, sugar and yeast mixture.
Stir well. Looks like thick syrup.
Cover with towel and let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in remaining flour and refrigerate overnight.
Grease large tube pan.
Turn dough on floured board and form into small (ping-pong) balls.
Dip each ball in melted butter and in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Form single layer on bottom of pan and cover with pecans.
Repeat until 3 layers are formed.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately and leave upside down on plate.
Best hot.

title: chocolatetown special cake
directions: Stir together cocoa and boiling water in bowl until smooth; set aside.
Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla in large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Blend in cocoa mixture.
Pour into three greased and floured 8-inch or two 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes for 8-inch pans or 35 to 40 minutes for 9-inch pans or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely.
Frost as desired.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic salt.
Drain grease.
Add flour, salt, paprika and mushrooms.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add sour cream. Heat thoroughly.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil together 5 minutes; remove from heat.
Add baking soda and vanilla.
Pour syrup mixture over 2 gallons popped corn with unpopped kernels removed.
Put in 250° oven in a large roasting pan for 1 hour.
Stir popcorn and syrup every 15 minutes.
This will keep in covered container for weeks.

title: pizza bites
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread over toasted, buttered rye or wheat bread or on buns.
Cut in bite size pieces.
Either freeze or bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add oats and nuts.
Mix and shape into rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and chill. Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Bake on ungreased pan at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: 5th sunday squash casserole
directions: Boil squash with onion, salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon water until tender. Drain. Add milk, cheese, onion, eggs, salt and pepper.
Put in casserole and top with bread crumbs and dot with butter.

title: candy cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour in large bowl.
Put margarine, Crisco, cocoa and water in pan and let come to a boil.
Remove from heat and pour into flour and sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk and 2 eggs to mixture; beat well.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon soda over batter; mix well and add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 9x13 inch pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: potato patties italiano
directions: Boil
potatoes
in
salted
water
until
tender.
Cool slightly.
Peel and mash while warm.
In a small bowl mix both bread crumbs, cheese, garlic and garlic powder.
Add to mashed potatoes.
Season with salt and
pepper.
Add mint and 2 eggs. Work mixture well with hands.
(Texture should not be too soft or stick to bowl.) Shape
into
small
to medium oval patties. Lightly press down top of
patties
to flatten a little.
Heat oil on medium and fry until
both
sides
are
a
golden brown (should not be too
dark).
Drain
on
paper
towels.
Yields about 16 medium patties.

title: smothered shrimp and okra
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add okra, sausage and bacon.
Fry well.
Mix tomatoes.
Reduce heat to low and add shrimp.

title: peanutty popcorn squares
directions: In a large bowl, combine popcorn and peanuts.
In a 4-cup measure, microwave corn syrup at High for 3 minutes; stir in peanut butter until melted.
Pour over popcorn mixture and stir to coat.
Press into greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until firm before cutting into squares.

title: pan greaser
directions: Stir
together.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator until
needed.
Coat
pans thoroughly using fingers or pastry brush.
No more flying flour or food sticking in pans. Keeps beautifully for 6 months to a year.

title: never-fail 4 minute frosting
directions: Mix egg whites, sugar, water and cream of tartar.
Beat over hot water in double boiler.
When in peaks, add vanilla.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Stir well; set aside.
In Dutch oven, saute 2 medium onions in 2 tablespoons vegetable oil.
Add pork mixture and next 10 ingredients.
Bring to a boil, cover and reduce heat.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Combine egg and sesame seed oil; set aside.
Combine water and 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Mix well. Add mixture to soup; boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in egg and sesame seed oil mixture.
Egg will form long strands. Remove from heat.
Sprinkle with green onion and serve immediately. Makes 9 cups.

title: baked fruit compote
directions: Drain cherries, reserving 1 cup juice; set aside.
Combine brown sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually add reserved cherry juice, lemon juice and orange juice; stir mixture well.

Combine cherries, peaches, apricots and prunes in a 2-quart casserole. Pour brown sugar mixture over fruit; sprinkle with cherry brandy. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until apricots are tender.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: plantation crunch cookies
directions: Melt almond bark and peanut butter together in the microwave. Stir in the peanuts and Rice Krispies.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.

title: split pea soup with franks
directions: Simmer peas, onion, salt and pepper in water 20 to 30 minutes until peas are tender.
Lightly brown the franks in butter in a frypan; add to soup.
Simmer 5 minutes longer to blend flavor.

title: bacon-cheese puffs
directions: Combine biscuit mix and bacon in bowl.
Add milk and egg; mix lightly.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin pan cups.
Make a hollow in each with spoon.
Press cheese cube deep into hollow.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: flaky candy
directions: Combine syrup, sugar and cream in pan and cook to soft ball stage.
Mix with the rest of the ingredients and put on a buttered pan to cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: This bread can safely
be
baked
in wide-mouth canning jars and when sealed
immediately
upon removing from oven, it will keep on the shelf for up to one year.

title: brussels sprouts with balsamic vinegar
directions: Trim off the stems and remove any limp leaves from the Brussels sprouts.
Blanch the sprouts in boiling water to cover for 5 minutes.
Drain and rinse under cold water to stop the cooking.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter or margarine.
Mix with flour, water and Cheez Whiz.
Beat eggs well and fold them into mixture.
Add the 2 packages of frozen broccoli, chopped and thawed.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Top with bread crumbs or pieces of bacon.

title: souper scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup with milk and a dash of pepper. In a casserole, arrange sliced potatoes, minced onion and soup sauce in alternate layers. Dab top with butter, sprinkle with paprika.

title: yellow cheese ball
directions: Blend soft cream cheese (with mixer) with rest of ingredients. Form into ball and chill.
Roll in chopped pecans.
(Can be frozen.)

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tasty ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain fat from skillet.
Add soups, tomato sauce and enchilada mix.
Add 1/2 cup water and simmer for 10 minutes.
In large casserole dish, layer Doritos, hamburger mix and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 325° until bubbly.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni, one box at a time and chill overnight, then mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Shape into bite-sized balls. Brown in butter.
Cook until done.
Heat soup (do not dilute). Pour over meatballs and serve.

title: judy's peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine 10x sugar and milk.
Bring to boil (full) over medium heat.
Boil 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased, square pan and cut into squares when cool.

title: the best mom's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: hot hominy casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: crab stuffed eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise and carefully remove yolks. Mash yolks with fork.
Add crabmeat and next 4 ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon yolk mixture into egg whites.
Garnish with pimiento slices and fresh parsley.
Yields 12 servings.

title: inside-out chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix by hand until well blended (about 2 minutes).
Pour into greased and floured 12-cup Bundt or ring cake pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until cake springs back when pushed by a finger.
Do not overbake.
Cool 15 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan and continue cooling on rack.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Slice squash about 1/4 inch thick.
Boil 3 minutes.
Mix soup, green pepper, onion and fresh tomato.
Place thin layer of cracker crumbs in bottom of dish.
Add layer of squash, half of grated cheese and half of soup mixture.
Season and repeat these layers, using remaining cheese on top.
Pour over 1/2 cup milk into which one egg has been beaten.
Bake well at 350°.

title: apple dumplings
directions: In 9 x 13-inch dish, roll out biscuits flat.
Cut apples into quarters.
Then place 1 apple quarter into biscuit and wrap. Continue until all apples are wrapped.
Melt butter; add sugar and water.
Pour over apples and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fancy baked chicken
directions: Combine butter, cheese, garlic and salt; mix well. Dip each piece of chicken in mixture, reserving remainder; coat with breadcrumbs. Place chicken in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish; spoon remaining butter mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 4 servings.

title: homemade pizza sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in large skillet.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Use as needed.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush the graham crackers into crumbs.
Mix with cut-up fruit and pecans in a large container.
Melt marshmallows in the top of a double boiler with milk.
Add the almond extract and pour over the mixture.

title: texas brownies
directions: Tip:
If you don't have buttermilk on hand, substitute 2 teaspoons vinegar or lemon juice mixed in 1/2 cup milk.

title: sweet and sour pork or chicken
directions: Brown chicken or pork, which has been cut in bite-size pieces, slowly in oil.
Add 1 cup water and bouillon cube.
Simmer until tender.

title: cocktail franks
directions: Dissolve jelly and mustard in crock-pot on medium.
Add franks. Continue cooking until completely dissolved and franks are good and hot.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook chopped broccoli as directed.
Combine all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: roman potatoes
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Arrange potatoes in baking dish. Arrange onion and bell pepper on potatoes.
Sprinkle with flour mixture.
Put pats of butter on top of flour.
Pour on a little milk.
Put cheese strips on top.
Start with another layer.
Bake about 1 hour at 400°.
Serves 4.

title: cucumber dressing
directions: Mix together.
Cover and let set in fridge overnight.
Serve over tossed salad or with just lettuce.

title: chicken delight
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and line the dish with sliced beef.
Wash chicken and dry; salt and pepper and wrap one piece of bacon around each piece of chicken.
Place on beef and cover with dressing made of the sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Cover with Reynolds Wrap.
Cook 2 hours at 325°.
Uncover and cook 1 hour or until brown.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in an unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix hash brown potatoes with all the ingredients.
Put in a buttered baking dish.
Top with crushed crackers or cornflake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mammy's cheese ball
directions: Mix well and chill.
Roll in pecans.

title: kraut goulash(weight watchers)
directions: Brown and drain the ground chuck.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
